title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake brownies; punch with a fork and pour almond extract over them.
Break into chunks and put into a large glass bowl; make mousse according to package directions.
Layer half the mousse. Add half of the candy bars and half of the Cool Whip.
Repeat each layer in order, beginning with the brownie chunks and ending with crushed candy bars on top.
You'll think you've died and gone to heaven when you see and taste this dessert.

title: rolled cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and drop in boiling water, cored end down, for 5 to 6 minutes or until leaves separate and are soft enough to roll.

title: broccoli cream soup
directions: Place broccoli and 1/2 cup milk in blender container.
Process until smooth.
Combine with remaining 1 1/2 cups milk, soup and salt in saucepan.
Heat just to boiling.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown the bacon, beef and onion.
Add the brown sugar, mustard, vinegar, ketchup and salt.
Add beans.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix and spread on tortillas.
Chill and serve.
Add black olives, if desired.

title: butter squares
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and egg together.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, confectioners sugar and eggs. Pour over top of first layer.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until golden brown and cracked on top.
Cut into squares.

title: cherry cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, water and eggs.
Add fruits and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: summer fruit crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a shallow baking dish with 2 tablespoons butter and arrange the fruit in the base.
In the bowl of a food processor, briefly combine the remaining butter with the flour and sugar until the mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle evenly over fruit.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes, until top becomes crisp and fruit collapses.
Serve warm with the creme fraiche.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together, except nuts.
Form into a ball, then roll it in the chopped nuts.
Chill and serve.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and bone one fryer.
Cut meat in small pieces.
Place meat in casserole dish and sprinkle with garlic powder.

title: ozark french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in quart size jar.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Line baking dish with chipped, dried beef.
Roll each piece of chicken and wrap with bacon slice.
Place on top of dried beef. Mix soup and sour cream.
Pour over chicken. Bake for 1 hour at 300°.

title: no bake peanut butter pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw for 10 minutes before serving.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes until tender. Take out and place in glass dish. Sprinkle sugar and butter on potatoes. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet lime pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in lime water for 24 hours.
Stir often; drain. Soak
in
cold
water for 4 hours.
Change water every hour until all the lime is gone.

title: flaky sausage snacks
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Unfold pie crusts according to package directions.
Place flattened pie crust on cutting board.
Cut each pie crust circle into 24 triangles.
Place sausage at wide end of triangle; roll up.
Place, pointed side down, on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes or until light golden brown.
If desired, serve with cocktail sauce.

title: no-bake chocolate-peanut butter-oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, milk and cocoa in a saucepan; cook at a full rolling boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and peanut butter and blend thoroughly.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper and cool until firm.

title: sweet-and-sour chicken
directions: In cup, stir together cornstarch and broth until smooth.
Set aside.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat with hot oil, fry the chicken until browned.
In same skillet, combine undrained pineapple, pepper, sugar, vinegar and reserved cornstarch mixture. Cook until mixture boils and thickens, stirring constantly. Reduce heat to low.
Cover; cook 5 minutes or until peppers are tender.
Serve over rice.

title: chocolate chip cookies by morse
directions: Beat sugars, vanilla, water, shortening and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix together flour, soda and salt to the above mixture.
Stir in chips.
Drop from spoon 2-inches apart on ungreased sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: cream sherry cake
directions: In large bowl, blend first 5 ingredients well.
Add eggs and blend well.
Add nuts and blend.
Pour into a Bundt or angel food pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: pineapple coleslaw
directions: Use 1 cup cole slaw dressing, already prepared, or make your own using 1/2 cup mayonnaise and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Combine all ingredients.

title: fudge puddles
directions: In a mixing bowl cream butter, peanut butter and sugars; add egg and vanilla.
Stir together flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Mix well.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 48 (1-inch) balls.
Place in lightly greased mini muffin tins.
(I made my balls larger and used regular muffin pans.)
Bake at 325° for 14 to 16 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and immediately make "wells" in the center of each by lightly pressing with a melon baller.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes.
Then carefully remove to wire rack.
Filling recipe to follow.

title: basic white frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients, except vanilla. Beat until foamy, 1 minute. Place bowl over simmering water, making sure bottom of bowl doesn't touch the water. On low speed, beat 10 minutes or until stiff peaks form. Remove.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef in skillet, drain off fat and put meat in crock-pot.
Brown bacon and onions, drain and put into crock-pot. Add all other ingredients, stir and cover.
Cook 4 to 6 hours on low.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, debone and chop up.
Spread chicken and chopped onions over bottom of baking dish.
Mix cream of chicken soup and cream of celery soup with soup can of milk.
Pour over chicken in baking dish.
Mix butter, broth and stuffing together.
Spread over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes (no longer).

title: reese's cups
directions: Melt butter.
Mix with rest of dry ingredients.
Press into a long cake pan.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Pour over ingredients in pan.
Let cool; cut into squares.

title: pineapple mincemeat cake
directions: Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans.
Mix cake according to box directions using pineapple liquid instead of oil and water. Add mincemeat and 1 cup of drained pineapple; mix well and add pecans, if desired.
Bake in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Remove carefully from pans and cool completely.
Place one layer on cake plate.
Spread with 1 cup pineapple and pecans.
Place second layer on top and spread with rest of the pineapple and pecans.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Mix, roll and cut biscuits as usual.
Place one stick oleo in bread pan.
Place in oven to melt.
Remove pan from oven.
Leave 1/2 oleo in pan.
Use rest to spoon over biscuits.
Bake at 375° until golden brown on bottoms and tops, about 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, salt and flour, then add 2 cups milk.
Cook very slow or over a double boiler until thick like gravy.

title: margie's meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together, place in ungreased meat loaf pan or pyrex dish and bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: uncooked chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, oleo, milk and pecans.
Spread 1 1/2 cups of this mixture in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: pineapple cream cheese squares
directions: Combine crumbs, 1/4 cup sugar and butter.
Press into the bottom of a 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes. Cool.
Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Blend cream cheese and 1/4 cup sugar together.
Fold in prepared whipped topping.
Spoon into crumb-lined pan, spreading evenly.
Chill until set.
Drain pineapple, saving the syrup.
Add water to syrup to make 1 cup.
Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add the cup of pineapple syrup and water mixture.
Chill until thickened. Arrange 9 slices of pineapple on cream cheese mixture.
Spoon jello onto this.
Chill until firm.

title: thelma's jello and fruit salad
directions: Follow directions on Jell-O package.
Cool to thick, firm. Mix in fruit.
Pour into 1 large dish or 2 smaller dishes.
Can be made a day ahead.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Peel and slice the eggplant. Soak in salted water in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Soak bread crumbs in milk. Add eggs, sage, salt and pepper. Saut green pepper, celery, onion and jalapeno in butter until tender. Boil eggplant (large cubes) until almost tender; drain. Add bread mixture and sauteed vegetables; blend. Place in greased casserole. Top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: beef casserole
directions: Lightly spray or butter 9 x 13 or larger pan.
Brown beef and onion together in skillet.	Mix sour cream, mushroom soup and shredded cheese.
This is made in layers.
In greased pan, spread layer of sliced raw potatoes, then layer of beef and onion, then layer of cheese, sour cream and soup mix.
Repeat until you have used all ingredients except crushed cereal.
Put the cereal on last.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
I usually cover this for first half hour or so, then uncover.

title: sweet cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 6 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add water, cornmeal, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake until top is brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion.
Add Ranch Style beans.
Mix Ro-Tel sauce, chilies and soup.
Heat corn tortillas in hot oil until crisp.
Put tortilla on bottom of casserole dish.
Layer hamburger mixture, then Ro-Tel mixture, then cheese.
Repeat until all is gone.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix ingredients.
Use 2 teaspoons dry preparation to 1 cup boiling water per serving.
Makes 1 quart of dry preparation. Store in tight container indefinitely.

title: creamy potato cups
directions: Peel, cut and boil potatoes in water until soft.
Drain. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Add margarine and minced onion. Mash well.
Add half of evaporated milk.
Beat well.
Add well beaten egg.
Beat.
Add remaining evaporated milk.
Whip until creamy and fluffy.
Using
potato
shaped
individual
tinfoil pans, fill each
with	potatoes
and top with cheese.	Sprinkle with paprika. Bake in 350° preheated oven for approximately 10 minutes or until cheese
is slightly brown.	I serve these with grilled steaks or barbecue
chicken.	They are a family favorite.

title: crab dip
directions: Wash and drain crab.
Mix all ingredients together and heat until bubbly.
Serve hot.

title: lou and ray broussard's fried fish or chicken
directions: Drain fish.
Shake in seasoned cornmeal and flour mix and shake in bag.
Don't mix fish ahead of time; it will not fry well.
Mix enough for one cooking at a time.
Heat oil or grease at approximately 350°.
Drop pieces of fish in oil.
Pieces will rise to the top and turn golden brown when done.
Cook chicken the same way.
This is not very pepper hot.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Combine butter and marshmallows.
Cook until melted.
Add corn, peanuts and M&M's.
Stir and press in greased tube pan.

title: yellow rice and corn
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Put butter in while hot, then add soup and Mexicorn.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese for the last 5 minutes.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Mix hamburger,	bread
crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Form into loaf.

title: pumpkin spice cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients with cake mix.
Add eggs and water and beat 2 minutes.
Add pumpkin and beat 3 more minutes.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve warm with sauce.

title: cheese cake
directions: *Let the cream cheese sit out of the refrigerator 1 hour.
It will make a creamier cake.

title: shortening bread
directions: Put grease in bottom of skillet.
Mix corn meal and cracklins well.
Mix with warm water; put salt in to taste.
Bake in iron skillet; this will make 3 large pones or 1 large cake.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour or as brown as you like.
Put grease on top.

title: cream cheese veggie spread
directions: Puree raw vegetables and blend in softened cream cheese.
This can be used for sandwiches or to fill celery.

title: peach ice cream
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Pour mixture in a gallon freezer churn.
Freeze according to directions on freezer.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat with onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat 30 minutes.
Serve on hamburger buns.
Makes 6 to 8 burgers.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients, except nuts.
Shape into ball.
Roll ball in crushed walnuts or pecans.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix the first six ingredients on slow speed until well blended and uniform.
Add the buttermilk and mix well.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pie shells and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until set and brown on top.

title: chicken liver and bacon
directions: Take 1/2 slice of bacon and wrap around chicken liver.
Put toothpick in it.
Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes on broiling pan.
If you want to freeze, cook until almost done.
Don't freeze more than 3 weeks.
Thaw, not too long, and put under broiler.

title: friendship tea
directions: Mix together dry.
Mix 1 teaspoon or to taste of mixture to 1 cup hot water.
Place orange slice in cup.

title: golden potato casserole
directions: Scrub potatoes and cook in boiling salted water until tender. Remove from water and cool.
Peel potatoes and grate with a coarse grater.
Add sour cream, cheese, onion, milk, salt and pepper. Mix thoroughly.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Smooth top with spatula.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake in a 300° oven for 50 minutes or until piping hot. Cut into squares and serve.
Makes 8 servings.

title: bacon and chive potato salad
directions: Add potatoes to boiling water; cook 14 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard in large bowl.
Add potatoes, bacon and chives; mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate bananas
directions: Cut ends from banana.
Split and peel lengthwise along with banana halfway through.
Fill with chocolate chips.
Wrap in foil. Put on coals or charcoal.
Bake approximately 5 minutes.
Open immediately and let cool.
Eat right out of the foil.
The only thing missing is - ice cream!

title: pear relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except turmeric.
Boil 30 to 40 minutes.
Mix turmeric with a small amount of water to make paste. Add at last 10 minutes of cooking.
Put into hot, sterile jars and seal.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Fry hamburger with onion.
Cook spaghetti.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add milk and corn oil all at once.
Mix well.
Press in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Put fried hamburger on top.
Then cook spaghetti, then pizza sauce.
Mix sour cream, salad dressing and grated cheese together.
Put on top. Bake.

title: bran muffins
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, shortening and milk.
Sift dry ingredients; add to mixture.
Stir in the Raisin Bran or 40% Bran Flakes and add your own raisins.
Store batter in refrigerator, covered, for up to 2 weeks and bake as needed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes in muffin tins or cake papers.

title: pistachio fruit salad
directions: Whip the cream to directions on package.
Make pudding, using drained liquid from fruit cocktail and pineapple, using 1 1/2 cups of liquid.
Combine all ingredients and pour in mold or bowl.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut eggplant in half. Boil gently until barely tender.
Remove pulp, leaving shell about 1/4-inch thick. Reserve pulp.
Saute vegetables and pulp in butter. Add ground beef and brown. Add tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, seasoning and wine.
Cover and simmer until juices are almost absorbed, about 5 minutes.
Let cool slightly.
Add bread crumbs and eggs.
Stuff eggplant shells with dressing.
Top with bread crumbs, Romano cheese, a dot of butter and a sprinkle of paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until well heated.
Serves 4.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Dice bacon; fry and drain on paper towel.

Dice bell peppers and onions; saute in bacon drippings until vegetables are soft. Combine bacon, peppers, onions, beans and remaining ingredients and simmer slowly, uncovered, for 2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serves 8.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup of the soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 patties.
In skillet over medium high heat, cook patties until browned on both sides. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: white chili
directions: Mix beans, broth, garlic and 1/2 onions in a large pot.
Bring to a boil. Reduce to simmer and cook until beans are soft (about 3 hours), adding more broth as necessary.
In a skillet, saute remaining onions until done. Add chilies and seasonings.
Mix and add to beans.
Add chicken and simmer 1 hour.
Serve topped with grated cheese, salsa and sour cream. Serves 8 to 10.

title: turkey stir-fry
directions: Cook rice according to package directions. Add butter and mandarin peel in syrup, cover to keep warm and set aside.

title: corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat eggs, melt oleo, then mix all ingredients together and bake 60 to 65 minutes.

title: oven-easy beef and potato dinner casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In 8 x 12-inch baking dish, combine potatoes, oil and pepper.
Firmly press potato mixture evenly across bottom and up sides of dish to form a shell.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Remove stems from mushrooms and reserve. Brush mushroom caps with butter and place hollow side up on baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Finely chop the stems and add to remaining butter with onion.
Cook over medium heat until onions are softened.
Remove pan from heat, stir in bread crumbs, parsley and cream.
Season with 1/8 teaspoon salt and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Fill caps and top with grated cheese.
Bake about 15 minutes until mushrooms are tender and cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: chicken minnetonka
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In skillet, saute chicken breasts in butter with seasonings until almost done.
Separate dough into 8 triangles.
Place 4 triangles on large cookie sheet.
Put one piece of chicken on each triangle.
Put other triangles on top of chicken and seal edges.
Bake about 25 minutes until golden brown.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, soup, cheese, sour cream, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Top with corn flakes and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: busy day roast
directions: Place roast (an inexpensive cut works great) in heavy-duty aluminum foil.
Sprinkle the soup mix on top.
Top that with the can of cream soup.
Completely wrap in the foil.
Cook in a 300° oven for 6 to 8 hours, depending on the size of the roast.
The meat is unbelievably tender and it makes its own gravy!

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix together well frozen lemonade, Eagle Brand milk and Cool Whip until fluffy.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust and refrigerate until set.

title: sesame seed cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and then add shortening.
Mix well.
Beat eggs and anise flavoring and then add to dry ingredients.
Add milk and mix well.
Roll a little ball and then shape into a log.
Dip log into milk and then roll in sesame seed. Put on a lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
As soon as cookies brown lightly on bottom they are done. Makes 9 to 10 dozen.

title: aunt ruby's pink fluff
directions: Mix well and serve chilled.

title: quick biscuits
directions: I use butter Crisco for shortening.
Mix ingredients.
Pour out on floured board or hard surface.
Knead lightly.
Choke off biscuit size.
Put in greased pan.
Butter the top of biscuits. Bake in oven at 400° until golden brown.

title: fresh stuffed animals
directions: To freshen dusty stuffed animals, put in dryer.
Set on Air and add several fabric softener sheets.
Run dryer on Air or Fluff for 20 minutes.

title: apple nut bread
directions: Combine and mix together in order given.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: meat loaf with dried milk
directions: Break bread in bowl; pour milk over bread. Add eggs and mix well. Add meat, salt and catsup.

title: crock-pot candy
directions: Cook in crock-pot in order listed.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours on high.
Drop on wax paper 1 teaspoon at a time.

title: chicken and stove top dressing
directions: Lay chicken in a 9 x 13 pan and cover with slices of Swiss cheese. Mix 1 can cream of chicken soup and 1/4 cup water. Pour over cheese. Add one box Stove Top dressing mix (chicken or herb and onion is good). Sprinkle on soup.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions; drain well. While spinach is cooking, combine sour cream and dry onion soup mix and set aside.
Combine spinach and sour cream mixture.
Turn into buttered 6-cup baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs, then with cheese.
Drizzle with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes or until heated through and top is lightly browned.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef and add taco seasoning.
Follow packet instructions.
In a Pyrex or casserole dish, layer cooked rice then cooked taco meat, then Cheddar cheese, and build with everything else on the list.

title: upside down apple pie
directions: In 9 inch pie pan, combine pecans, brown sugar and margarine; spread evenly over bottom of pan. Prepare pie crusts according to package directions for two crust pie, placing bottom crust over pecan mixture in pan. Heat oven to 375°. In large bowl, combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon and nutmeg, mixing lightly. Spoon into crust lined pan. Top with remaining pie crust; fold edge of top crust under bottom crust. Press together to seal; flute edge. Cut slits in top crust.

Bake at 375° for 40-50 minutes or until apples are tender and crust is deep golden brown. Cover edge of crust with strips of foil after 15-20 minutes of baking to prevent excessive browning. (Place foil or cookie sheet on lowest oven rack during baking to guard against spills.) Cool pie upright in pan for 5 minutes. Place serving plate over pie; invert. Carefully remove pan. Some nuts may remain in pan; replace on pie with a knife. Cool at least 1 hour before serving.

title: my favorite dish
directions: Pour ingredients into bowl. Bake 1 hour covered at 375 degrees. Enjoy!

title: caesar salad
directions: Mix oil and garlic and let set overnight.
Mix wine vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, salt, dry mustard and lemon juice; chill. Clean and tear romaine.
Chill in bag with paper towel.
Place salad in bowl; add dressing.
Add croutons, cheese and black pepper.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate walnut torte
directions: Note:
Need 8 or 9-inch spring-form pan.

title: tostado salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: chicken-herb rice mix
directions: Bring 2 3/4 cups water to a boil in medium saucepan.
Add 1 tablespoon butter or margarine (optional).
Add rice blend and return to boil.
Cover and simmer over medium-low heat 15 to 18 minutes until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot fat 15 minutes.
Add onions and garlic.
Season with salt and pepper.
Dissolve cube in boiling water.
Add to meat.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper and cook 10 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch in 1/4 cup water.
Add soy sauce.
Stir into mixture and simmer 30 minutes on low heat.
Stir occasionally to keep from sticking. Serve over rice.

title: fannie mae fudge
directions: Combine milk, sugar and butter in large pot, stirring it and bringing it to a boil.
Cover and let boil for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and start adding other ingredients until melted.
Pour quickly into well buttered large sheet pans or baking dishes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and cut in cubes.
Reserve 2 quarts of broth and cook spaghetti in this until tender.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in oleo in skillet until tender.
Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup of cheese.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 3-inch oblong dish and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cauliflower in cheese sauce
directions: Cook cauliflower for 8 minutes. Drain and remove from pan. Melt butter. Stir in flour and pepper. Add milk; cook until bubbly. Add cheese, cauliflower and mushrooms.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook beans according to package directions; drain.
Combine soup, milk (undrained), pimento and cheese in saucepan.
Cook over low heat until cheese melts.
Layer beans, then soup mixture 1/2 at a time in buttered baking dish.
Top with cracker crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 300°
until bubbly.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix pudding with milk according to package and cook.
Allow mixture to cool; add coconut, 1/2 cup nuts and butterscotch morsels.
Pour into pie crust; garnish with remaining nuts.

title: salad dressing(kid's recipe)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, vinegar, mustard and butter in saucepan. Bring to a good boil, stirring constantly.
Set aside and let cool. Add mayonnaise to cooled mixture.
Good for any type of pasta or potato salad.

title: wienie surprise
directions: Boil noodles.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan add all other ingredients.
Add noodles when done.
Stir all together. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pistachio nut torte
directions: Layer 1:
Mix flour, butter, sugar and 1/4 cup nuts; press into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°. Cool.

title: chocolate marble cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add vanilla and eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk; beat after each addition.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir in 1/3 of the batter; alternate light and dark batters by spoonfuls in greased and lightly floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Zigzag spatula through batter.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes. Cool; remove from pan and cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour 2 bread pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) or 4 (5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch) pans.

title: butter nut balls
directions: Cream sugar and shortening and add rest of ingredients.
Bake in balls at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cool, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: impossible french apple pie
directions: Heat
oven to 325°.
Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch. Mix apples,
cinnamon and nutmeg.
Turn into pie plate.
Beat milk,
2 tablespoons margarine, the eggs, granulated sugar and 1/2
cup baking
mix
seconds in blender on high speed, 1 minute with wire whisk or hand beater or until smooth.

title: easy rice
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Use a casserole dish with tight fitting cover.
Stir once with fork while baking.

title: date nut bread
directions: In a small saucepan bring water and shortening to a boil; pour over dates in bowl.
Stand for 15 minutes.
Stir.
Add nuts, eggs and vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda and salt.
Stir into date mix.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 65 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup pecans on top before baking.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
While baking, prepare icing.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In skillet, saute onion, celery and carrots in butter.
Add chopped broccoli and chicken broth.
Cook 30 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Put into blender or processor.
Blend until smooth.
Add half and half.
Blend.
Serve warm or chilled.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all together and roll in small balls. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peach's broccoli salad
directions: Beat together condensed milk, vinegar, egg, mustard and onion until thick.
Pour over broccoli and bacon.
Chill.

title: hearty hamburger soup
directions: In a large saucepan, brown beef. Drain. Add the next 10 ingredients. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes or until potatoes and carrots are tender. Add beans. Cover and simmer 15 minutes longer or until the beans are tender. Yield: 8 servings.

title: spinach rolls
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a large bowl.
Then spread over the tortilla shells.
Then roll each shell, then refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Then slice each roll into moderate sizes.
Then serve on a platter.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Blend cornstarch and sugar. Combine with water and cook until thick. Add Jell-O while hot and stir until dissolved.
Allow to cool before pouring over strawberries in crust.
Chill 2 or 3 hours. Serve with whipped cream.

title: evelyn's creamy yogurt pie
directions: Blend yogurt, Cool Whip and condensed milk. Add frozen strawberries. Pour into pie crust. Place in freezer for 30 minutes or until frozen. Cut and serve.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; drain and cool.
Finely chop onion, celery and bell pepper.
Add to cold spaghetti and salad dressing.
Mix well.
Chill overnight.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Coarsely chop up artichoke hearts in food processor.
Blend in rest of ingredients. Spread in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat
egg white stiff.	Mix in sugar and vanilla.
Beat until stiff.
Stir
in
pecans
and coat good.
Grease cookie sheet
and spoon onto sheet about 1 inch apart.
Bake at 250° for 20 to 30 minutes until light golden brown.
Let set for 30 minutes and store.

title: party carrots
directions: Cook carrots and reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Put carrots lengthwise in narrow strips in baking dish.
Set aside.
Combine cooking liquid, mayo, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Pour sauce over carrots.
Sprinkle with parsley and paprika.
Dot with butter and bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: roast beef in a crock-pot
directions: Place all the ingredients in a crock-pot early in the day. Place the crock-pot on low temperature for 6 to 8 hours.
you will have a great supper with a delicious gravy.

title: pecan sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add water and vanilla.
Mix well; blend in flour and nuts.
Chill 3 hours.
Shape in balls or fingers.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 325° for 20 minutes. Remove from pan; cool slightly.
Roll in 10x sugar.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all together in bowl.
Chill for 1/2 hour.
Make balls walnut size.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Good cold too.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, soft butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell, then sprinkle pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
(This is less sweet than traditional pecan pie.)

title: lemon steak surprise
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Cover steak with mixture. Using large skillet, brown steak on both sides in shortening.
Add lemon juice, water and remaining ingredients.
Cover, cook over low heat, about 45 minutes or until steak is tender.
Stir often. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sticky cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine confectioners sugar and cream. Divide between 2 greased 9 in. square baking pans; set aside. Roll each loaf into 12 in. by 8 in. rectangle. Brush with margarine. Combine brown sugar & cinnamon. Sprinkle over margarine. Roll up -- cut each loaf into 12 slices. Place in pan. Cover & refrigerate overnight. Next day, remove from refrigerator; cover and let rise until double (about 2 hours). Cover loosely with foil. Bake at 375 degrees for 10 minutes. Uncover & bake 8-10 minutes longer.

title: easy cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk; cook over medium heat until hot and bubbling, stirring often.
You may microwave, uncovered, on High 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring halfway through heating.

title: crab and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions until barely done.
Arrange in bottom of 1-quart casserole.
Saute onions in butter; stir in salt and flour.
Gradually add milk, stirring constantly.
Add cheese and cook over low heat until thickened. Stir in lemon juice.
Add crab meat and pour over broccoli.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes until bubbly and browned.

title: creeping crust cobbler
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add milk; mix well.
Melt butter in a 10-inch baking pan.
Spoon dough over melted butter. Spoon fruit over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or crust is done.
Serve hot or cold.

title: grape salad
directions: Blend vanilla, sugar, sour cream and softened cream cheese until smooth.
Pour over grapes.
Keep chilled.
(Can substitute low fat cream cheese and sour cream.)

title: mary's pickle recipe
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack whole in jars.
Place 1 tablespoon mixed pickling spices on top of packed cucumbers and put 3 grape leaves either in the bottom or the top of each jar.
Add 1 tablespoon salt.
Heat to the boiling point 1/2 cup vinegar and 1/2 cup water (per jar).
Pour over cucumbers and seal.
If the jars do not seal, you may process them in cold pack canner for 5 minutes. Let stay in jars at least 2 weeks before using them.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium to large mixing bowl, put pork and beans.
Finely chop onion and green pepper; add to pork and beans.
Fry bacon crisp, then crumble into mixture.
Finely chop eggs and add to pork and bean mixture.
Add barbecue sauce and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all above ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until done.

title: baked manju
directions: Cream
together
butter
and
sugar.
Add eggs and beat well. Mix
in
milk, baking soda and flour.
The dough should not be too sticky (as it will spread while baking).
Roll out and knead dough on well floured board.
Cut into pieces about the
size
of walnuts.
Flatten dough and cover prepared "An" with it,
pinching the dough together on the bottom to seal it so that
the
"An" will
not
leak through.
Place on greased cookie
sheets,	coat tops
with	beaten eggs and sprinkle on sesame or poppy seed. Bake in 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes. It will be lightly browned.

title: crispy "sweet" pickles
directions: Cukes to be cut long ways in spears.
Pour boiling water over; stand overnight.
Boil syrup 5 minutes.
Pour over cukes in jars. Process in boiling water canner for 5 minutes.
This fills approximately 6 pints.
If you want sweeter, double the sugar.

title: low calorie vegetable soup
directions: Bring water to boil and add bouillon, garlic powder and pepper.
Add onion, celery, carrots, cabbage and potatoes.
Boil gently until vegetables are tender.
Add tomatoes and V-8 juice until heated through.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain and rinse shrimp and set aside.
Beat cream cheese with an electric mixer to soften.
Add mayonnaise, ketchup and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl and mix again.
Add shrimp and beat on low just enough to blend in shrimp.
Cover and refrigerate a few hours or overnight for a better flavor.
Makes about 2 cups.

title: orange julius
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in order.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: "cracker jack"
directions: Saute the peanuts in 2 Tablespoons of butter for 5 minutes, drain on kitchen towels. Sprinkle with salt to taste. Spread the popped corn in a large shallow baking pan stir in the peanuts and put into a 250°f. 120°c. gas mark 1/2. oven to keep warm. Combine 1 cup butter with the brown sugar, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2 qt. saucepan. Cook the mixture over a medium heat, stirring constantly until the sugar dissolves. Cook to firm ball stage about 248° on a candy thermometer, and remove from the heat at once. Stir in the baking soda, allowing mixture to foam. Remove popped corn from the oven and drizzle it with the hot foaming syrup in a fine, steady stream. Stir lightly to mix well.
Return to the oven for almost 1 hour, stirring about every 10-15 minutes. Cool thoroughly and serve. Store in an airtight container in a cool place. Makes about 5 qt.

title: christmas suet pudding
directions: Sift dry ingredients (first 7 ingredients) together.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Beat brown sugar with egg yolks and add suet.
Add bread crumb mixture to egg mixture.
Add all sifted ingredients, candied fruit and almonds together, then add to moistened mixture and mix well.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Place in bag or container and steam 3 1/2 hours.
This can be kept up to 8 weeks in refrigerator.

title: chocolate crisps
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt.
Cream butter with sugar; beat in egg, melted chocolate and vanilla.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Add nuts.
Shape in rolls and chill overnight.
Slice 1/8-inch thick and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°. Makes approximately 10 dozen.

title: russian tea 1
directions: Strain syrup.
Add orange, lemon and pineapple juices.
Bring all of this to a boil, then add it to tea.
Reheat when ready to serve.
Keep in refrigerator.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: nacho casserole
directions: Brown beef with chili powder and onion. Drain beef.
In a large skillet, place beef, refried beans and jalapeno relish. Heat until bubbling on medium heat.
Line bottom of a casserole dish, 3 to 5 chips deep.
When beef and bean mixture bubbles, pour over chips.
Place cheese over mixture and bake until cheese melts (5 to 10 minutes).
Top with tomatoes and sour cream.
Preheat oven to 450°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream the sugar and Wesson oil.
Add eggs and beat one at a time.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture.
Fold in carrots and pecans.
Bake in 3 layers about 30 minutes or until done.

title: heavenly waffles
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake in a preheated waffle iron.

title: old-fashioned raisin bars
directions: Heat water, raisins and oil until boiling.
Set aside to cool. When cool, add sugar and slightly beaten egg.
Add to mixture 1 3/4 cups flour and the spices.
Beat until smooth; add nuts.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
When cool, sprinkle powdered sugar over all.
Cut into squares.

title: ricotta puffs
directions: Heat vegetable oil in a deep saucepan.
Mix ingredients all together except for powdered sugar.
Add a rounded tablespoonful of batter at a time to hot oil.
Balls will form puffs and turn golden brown.
Drain on a paper towel and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Serve warm with a dessert dish of jelly for dipping.
Makes about 2 dozen puffs.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Then mix all ingredients in a large bowl and chill 4 hours to overnight.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in pan you are going to bake it in, then add apple pie filling on top.
Then slice 1 stick of butter on top; sprinkle with sugar.
Add pecans with apples, if desired. Bake at 400° until brown.

title: easy sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Shape into meatballs and place on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
In a crock-pot, combine apple jelly and chili sauce. Add meatballs.
Cook at a simmer for 1 hour or so.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and cool.
Add celery, pepper and onion.
Beat well the soup, sugar, vinegar and oil; pour over pasta.
Refrigerate. Keeps well.
You may halve recipe, if desired.

title: spicy cole slaw
directions: In a small saucepan, combine honey with vinegar, onion and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool and pour the cooled dressing over prepared vegetables; toss lightly

title: crown chicken salad
directions: Mix above ingredients except almonds and chill.
Garnish with almonds and serve on bed of leafy lettuce.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serves approximately 25 with chips.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine corn meal and water over a low fire until water is cooked down.
Add milk, oil, eggs and onion.
Mix in all dry ingredients with corn meal mixture.
Drop spoonfuls into 375° oil and fry until crispy golden brown.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: apple tuna salad
directions: In large bowl, combine lettuce, apples, tuna, oranges and nuts.
Toss together.
Combine mayonnaise, soy sauce and lemon juice.
Mix well; toss dressing gently with salad ingredients.

title: peanut blossom bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, combine sugar, brown sugar, butter and peanut butter; beat until light and fluffy. Add milk, vanilla and egg; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.
Add flour, baking soda and salt; mix well.
Press dough in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 19 to 24 minutes or until edges are golden brown. Immediately press candy kisses into bars, forming 5 rows of 8 kisses each.
Cool 1 hour or until completely cooled.
Cut into bars with 1 kiss in center of each.
Yield:
40 bars.

title: apricot brandy slush
directions: Combine water and sugar in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Mix lemonade, orange juice and brandy to water mixture and freeze.
To serve fill glasses 3/4 full.
Fill with sprite or 7-UP.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Brown and crumble beef (4 minutes, plus 4 minutes).
Stir in spaghetti sauce and water.
Meanwhile, combine Ricotta cheese, egg and black pepper.
In oblong baking dish, spoon 1/2 cup sauce, alternating layer of noodles, egg mixture (spread on noodles), Mozzarella cheese and sauce, forming 2 layers.
Heat, covered, 8 minutes on High.
Microwave 30 to 32 minutes on Medium-low or until noodles are tender.
Top with Parmesan; let stand 15 minutes.
Keep covered.
Can freeze.
Serves 6.

title: cheesy pineapple delight
directions: Drain pineapple.
Pour in glass dish.
Mix sugar and flour and pour over pineapple.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over it.
Then sprinkle Ritz crackers on top.
Put 10 pats of margarine in different spots of dish.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: holiday fruit alaska
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Mix the fruit and syrup together and chill.
Prepare meringue in a large bowl by beating egg whites until soft peaks form.
Gradually add sugar, about 2 tablespoons at a time.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Portion the fruit into custard dishes of ovenproof serving dish.
Top and seal each dish with a generous dollop of meringue and place on cookie sheet and bake 3 minutes.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cream butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla until fluffy; blend in eggs.
Combine cocoa, flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in bowl; add alternately with milk to batter.
Blend well.
Pour into pan. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and frost as desired.

title: nuggets
directions: Mix cereal and peanuts.
Melt almond bark and 1 teaspoon shortening.
Microwave.
Place almond bark in a microwave dish. Microwave for 1 1/2 minutes; then stir.
Continue to microwave until product is completely melted.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring lightly.
Cover and chill several hours before serving.

title: christmas wreaths
directions: Easy, fun, family or scout holiday treat!
Our family favorite!

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on box.
Add crushed pineapple and bake.
When cake is done, stick holes in it with wooden spoon handle, 1 inch apart.
Mix Eagle Brand milk, creme de coconut and pecans. Pour over cake while hot.
Cool cake.
Frost with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate overnight.
I mix 1 teaspoon pineapple juice with sour cream before adding.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Bring to boil sugars and corn syrup.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix until melted.
Pour mixture over corn flakes.
Add peanuts and stir well. Put in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: crust for strawberries
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend with a pastry blender. Place on dough board (flour well); roll out like pie crust.
Cut with glass or any size desired.
Grease cookie sheet.
Cook about 20 to 25 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve.

title: perfect roast beef
directions: Place roast in crock-pot.
Pour dry onion soup mix over roast.
Pour soup over roast and onion soup mix.
Cook on low all day while you are at work or play.

Forty-five minutes to an hour before eating, place all desired vegetables in an aluminum oven bag with salt and pepper and garlic (optional) and a little oil (2 tablespoons) and bake for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: frango na pucara(or portuguese jugged chicken)
directions: Rub chicken with oil.
Place 1/2 Prosciutto, onions, tomatoes, carrots and spices in ovenproof clay pot (or casserole with cover). Then add chicken.
Then pile the rest of the veggies on top. Combine wines, brandy, mustard and pepper.
Pour over chicken. Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
After removing from oven, drain off liquid and make it into a gravy with Wondra flour.
Cover chicken and veggies to serve.
Great with a side dish of rice!

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until crumbly.
In small bowl, beat with fork:
water, vinegar and egg.
Combine two mixtures until moistened.
Divide dough in flat round patties and wrap in wax paper.
Freeze.
(To glaze a pie crust, brush top with beaten egg yolk.)

title: golden cornbread
directions: Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add milk, egg and shortening.
Beat until fairly smooth, about 1 minute.
Bake in greased 8-inch square baking dish in preheated hot oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: salmon croquettes
directions: Mix all ingredients except oil well.
Heat oil.
Roll croquettes in bread stick forms; put in hot oil.
Brown, then turn until all sides are brown.
Can be served hot or cold.
(These croquettes can be baked if oil is a problem.)

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream sugars and margarine until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat until pale yellow.
Add vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Add raisins or chocolate chips and walnuts.
(This recipe is also good with coconut.)
Add oatmeal and mix well.
Spoon onto cookie sheets.
Bake for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Check often the first time you make these and adjust cooking time to your own oven.
If they brown too fast, cook at a lower temperature (325°).
If the cookie monster lives at your house, double this recipe!

title: strawberry fluff salad
directions: Combine Cool Whip and instant pudding mix until well blended by hand.
Add strawberries and mix well.
Garnish top with strawberries.

title: ruth's fruit salad
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: onion fried tenderloin
directions: Slice tenderloin in 1/4 inch thick slices, then in the middle of each slice put a small cut.
This is so that the edges will not curl while cooking.
Salt and pepper.
Put in skillet with some oil.
Cook until done.
Add onion on top of meat and cover.
Put on low heat.
Let this cook for about 1/2 hour.
Serve.

title: bridal punch
directions: All ingredients must be at room temperature when mixing. Freeze until ready to serve in a plastic jug.
Needs to thaw approximately 4 hours before ready to serve.

title: sauce for potato salad
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and beat.
Add mustard, water, vinegar and butter.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Store in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken.
Boil cut-up bell pepper until tender.
Drain pimentos, bell pepper and water chestnuts.
Combine all ingredients in casserole dish (except onions).
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: preserving children
directions: Thoroughly mix together children and the dogs, stirring continually.
Pour a pinch of brook over the pebbles; sprinkle the field with flowers.
Spread over deep blue sky and bake in a hot sun.

title: graham zucchini muffins
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; fold in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in grated zucchini and orange rind; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to creamed mixture in thirds, blending only until well mixed.
Overbeating makes muffins tough. Spoon into papered muffin tins or small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes for muffins and 40 minutes for loaf.

title: pork and bean bread
directions: If raisins are desired, plump in 1 cup of water.
Cream eggs, sugar, oil and pork and beans with mixer.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Drain raisins; add with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Makes 3 loaves.

title: jean's chicken soup
directions: Put chickens in large pot
and cover with water.
Bring to boil; then lower heat to simmer.
When chickens are tender, remove from heat and let cool.
Cut
meat
into
bite
sizes.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Heat drained hominy and sour cream in casserole dish in oven until bubbling.
Add chili peppers; season with salt and pepper to taste.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top; let melt before serving.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: Pour boiling water over all-bran.
Set aside.
Cream together sugar and shortening in a 6-quart bowl.
Add eggs; beat well. Blend in buttermilk, Bran Buds and soaked all-bran.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.

title: chipped beef casserole
directions: Mix all together the day before and refrigerate.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Combine ingredients.
Place on 8 buns.
Wrap in foil.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: ujhazy's chicken soup
directions: Cut up the boiling fowl and sprinkle with salt.
Place in a large pan with a small amount of water and bring to the boil.
Then pour off the water.
Cover the fowl with fresh water.
Boil it and then simmer gently.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook bacon in saucepan; add flour and stir.
Add clam juice and stir until thick.
Grind clams and add with vegetables and seasonings.
Add enough water for chowder consistency.
Cook 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: easy turkey casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing by box directions.
Warm soup and gravy together.
Layer dressing, turkey and gravy in a casserole dish. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together and pour over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: corn fritters
directions: Combine corn, egg, sugar, salt, pepper and butter.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Stir into first mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls into a little hot oil, browning both sides.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread ready to serve Frito-Lay beans in 3-quart Pyrex pan or something similar.
Then spread the mashed avocados.
Pour taco seasoning into sour cream and mix thoroughly.
Spread over avocados.
Chop scallions very thin and add a thin layer, then add olives.
Slice the tomato very fine and add to dip.
Shred cheese for final layer.
(All ingredients should be layered one on top of the other.)
Chill if desired.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix salt and water mixture.
Let set overnight or 6 to 8 hours over zucchini.
Mix vinegar, pickling spice and sugar.
Tie spice in a cloth and bring last 3 ingredients to a boil for 5 minutes. Remove spice bag; add squash.
Bring to a boil.
Place in sterilized jars and seal.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add baking powder to flour with salt.
Alternate milk flour into sugar and butter.
For the topping.
Peel and slice 4-6 apples.
Spread over cake and sprinkle with 3/4 c. sugar and 1 tsp. cinnamon.
Dot with butter.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Fry hamburger and onion together.
Add your taco seasoning and cheese together and mix together, then mix salsa.
Serve with taco chips.

title: lattice-top chicken bake
directions: Combine soup,
milk, salt, chicken, vegetables, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spread mixture in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 425° for 10 minutes.

title: saute of veal marengo(a good party dish.  may be made ahead.)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Dry the veal on paper towels.
Heat oil in skillet (10 or 12-inch).
Brown meat on high heat, a few pieces at a time, and arrange in 4-quart casserole.
Lower heat to moderate and brown onions lightly in skillet 5 or 6 minutes.
Toss meat with flour, salt and pepper and heat 3 to 4 minutes to brown the flour lightly.
Remove from heat.
Add wine to onions in skillet and pour all into casserole and bring to simmer, stirring. Stir tomatoes into casserole; add herbs, garlic and orange peel. Again, bring to simmer; season lightly.
Set in oven, covered, for 1 1/4 or 1 1/2 hours to simmer.
Add mushrooms, basting, and return to oven for 15 minutes.
If necessary, skim fat off the sauce.
Then, also if necessary, thicken the sauce.
Correct seasonings.
Top with 2 tablespoons minced parsley or tarragon. Serve with noodles or rice for 6.

title: chopped beef and potato casserole
directions: Brown meat slightly.
Spread in bottom of flat baking pan (9 x 13-inches).
Sprinkle onion over meat.
Spread soup over onion. Put cheese slices over soup to cover.

title: cream of broccoli soup(original recipe)
directions: Cook broccoli in water and butter until tender.
Then add Cheez Whiz and stir until melted.
Mix flour, milk and onion powder; add.
Simmer until slightly thickened.
Do not
boil.
Add salt to taste.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour into 2 lightly greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° (top will crack).

title: spinach-artichoke dip
directions: Preheat broiler.
In a medium-sized bowl, combine the mayonnaise, cheese, chiles, spinach and artichoke hearts.
Pour mixture into 9-inch pie pan.
Place 6-inches under broiler and cook until lightly browned, about 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips or large corn chips.

title: microwave peanut-pretzel pie crust
directions: Microwave butter in 9-inch pie plate at High for 30 to 60 seconds.
Combine nuts, pretzels and sugar with melted butter. Press evenly in pie plate.
Chill before serving and fill with favorite filling.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add partially thawed strawberries, crushed pineapple and diced bananas.
Put half of mixture in oblong pan.
Refrigerate until set, approximately 2 to 3 hours.
(You can leave it in longer though.)
Spread with a thin coat of sour cream.
Add remaining half of mixture and put in refrigerator until set.

title: refrigerator strawberry ice cream(makes 3 quarts)
directions: Combine 1 cup sugar, salt and flour in saucepan; gradually stir in milk.
Cook, stirring until mixture thickens and bubbles. Remove from heat.
Stir half the hot milk mixture into eggs in bowl; stir back into saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, 1 minute; do not boil.
Pour into large bowl; cool.

title: filled cookies
directions: Dough is soft.
Flour board good and roll to less than a 1/4-inch thickness.
Then cut circles with a cookie cutter or floured glass.

title: brown sugar short bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Gradually stir in flour. Turn onto lightly floured surface. Knead until smooth, about 3 minutes. Pat into a 1/3-inch rectangle measuring 11 x 8-inch. Cut into 2 x 1-inch strips. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheets. Prick with a fork. Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until bottom begins to brown. Cool 5 minutes and remove to a wire rack. Cool completely. Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: mulled cider
directions: Bring to a boil.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Remove spices and reheat.
Serve hot.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Mash potatoes; mix with oleo, sugar, raisins and pineapple. Add enough pineapple juice and potato syrup to moisten.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with marshmallows.
Broil until slightly melted and brown.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: maryland crab soup(4 to 6 servings)
directions: Place the oil in a soup pot.
Add the carrots and onions. Cover the pot and cook the vegetables over low heat just until softened.
Add the broth, potatoes, tomatoes and Old Bay seasoning. Simmer just until the potatoes are tender, approximately 10 minutes.
Add the crabmeat and parsley and heat through.

title: strawberry shortcake jello
directions: Chill jello until it begins to thicken. Blend in strawberries and Cool Whip. Add chunked cake until it is covered with the strawberry mixture. Chill.

title: fruit curry
directions: Drain fruit.
Alternate fruit in layers with sliced pineapple and cherries on top.

title: cabbage burgers(runza)
directions: Brown cabbage in skillet.
Brown beef, then combine beef and cabbage.
Add salt and pepper.
Let cool.
Place thawed bread dough in greased bowl.
Let rise in warm place until doubled in bulk, about 30 minutes.
Roll dough into rectangle about 1/4-inch thick; cut dough into 8 (5-inch) squares.
Place about 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of meat mixture in center of each square.
Bring 4 corners together and pinch.
Place seam side down on greased baking sheet.
Let rise in warm place 20 minutes.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: arlington brunch
directions: Put 6 slices buttered bread on bottom of casserole dish.
Top with ham and cheese.
Top with rest of bread.
Combine remaining ingredients, except cornflakes.
Pour milk mixture over bread. Refrigerate overnight or several hours, then top with crushed cornflakes.
Bake at 300° for 75 minutes or 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: southwestern chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken and onion.
Cook and stir until chicken is cooked through.
Stir in beans, salsa, corn and broth; bring to boil.
Stir in rice. Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Garnish as desired.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: creamed onions
directions: Melt butter over medium heat, mix cream and flour and add to butter, stirring for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add salt to taste.
Arrange onions in a baking dish, cover with the cream sauce and bread crumbs.
Top with grated cheese and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot (may use Vidalia onions).
Makes 6 servings.

title: flora smith's coleslaw
directions: The amounts may be modified to your tastes.

title: christmas fruit cookies
directions: Mix soda and hot water.
Pour over dates.
Let stand while mixing other ingredients.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Mix fruit with dry ingredients.
Add dates to fruit mixture.
Put both mixtures in a large bowl and mix by hand until well mixed.
Drop on cookie sheet with small spoon.
Cook 12 minutes at 375°.
Will keep like fruit cake.
Freezes well.
Makes about 7 dozen small cookies.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Preheat oven to
In
roasting pan (or cake pan), mix uncooked rice, 2
cans
cream
of
mushroom soup and 1 1/2 cups of water.
Mix well.
Place seasoned pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Top
with
onion
slices and bell pepper rings. Bake 30 to 45 minutes
until
pork chops are brown and rice is tender.

title: candy buckeyes
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and vanilla.
Blend in sugar and mix well.
Easiest to blend with hands.
Form into quarter size balls and refrigerate while dip is made.

title: pound cake
directions: Let butter get soft at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix well.
Add flour slowly.
Add whipping cream; add flavoring.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except oleo and bread crumbs.
Place in 9 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Brown bread crumbs lightly in oleo and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except bread crumbs, in large bowl.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with bread crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple and dissolve jello in it.
Cool.
Add buttermilk and cool whip.
This fills an 11 by 7-inch pan very full.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Chill until ready to serve.

title: orange cream fruit salad
directions: Drain first 3 ingredients well.
Combine bananas and apples. Mix with other fruit.
Combine pudding, milk and orange juice. Beat 1 to 2 minutes.
Beat in sour cream.
Fold in fruit.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce.
Serves 10.

title: healthy pancakes
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Combine buttermilk, sour cream and eggs.
Mix with dry ingredients and cook on lightly greased griddle.
Batter may be kept up to a week in refrigerator. Makes 36 pancakes.

title: topping for angel food cake
directions: Whip cream adding vanilla and sugar.
Add Eagle condensed milk and juice of 1 lemon.
Whip all ingredients a little more.
Set in refrigerator until mixture is thickened.
Use as a topping over angel food cake.

title: choco-peanut butter bars
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix shortening, peanut butter and sugars.
Stir in water, flour, soda, baking powder, salt and 1 package chocolate chips.
Spread in pan and bake about 20 minutes.
Remove from oven; immediately sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over the baked layer.
Place a baking sheet over the top to contain the heat and melt the chocolate chips.
Spread softened chocolate chips evenly and sprinkle with peanuts.

title: golden stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Halve baked potatoes and scoop out pulp.
Whip pulp with carrots, parsley, chives, horseradish, yogurt and butter.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Refill potato halves.
Top with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes, or until cheese melts and mixture is hot.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix half cake mix, butter, vanilla and eggs until smooth. Add rest of cake mix, chocolate chips and nuts. Drop dough with teaspoon 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheets. Bake 10 to 12 minutes. Centers will be soft.

title: barbecue wieners
directions: Cut wieners in small bite size pieces. Fry wieners (not much oil). In a pint jar, fill half full with barbecue sauce. Add ketchup. Fill jar the rest of the way full with water. Shake until well mixed. Pour over wieners. Simmer.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Place frozen rolls in well-greased Bundt pan (or angel food pan).
Sprinkle 3/4 of pudding over rolls.
You may add nuts, raisins, etc.
Melt butter and brown sugar together; let bubble a few seconds.
Pour mixture over the rolls.
Cover with foil and a towel and let stand on the counter overnight.
In the morning bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Turn out of pan immediately.

title: german potato salad
directions: Add onion to potatoes.
Cube and fry bacon until golden brown. Remove bacon from pan.
To bacon fat, add butter and flour.
Stir and cook and add vinegar, water, sugar, salt and pepper.
Let come to a boil and pour over potatoes.
Add bacon cubes.
Serves about 6 people.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Set in refrigerator for 20 minutes. Roll into 2 balls.
Roll in pecans or walnuts.
Top with a cherry.

title: fruit pizza
directions: *Canned or frozen fruit may be used.
Drain well to prevent crust from becoming soggy.

title: orange cream salad
directions: Drain canned fruits well.
Combine fruits together, well drained.
Beat all other ingredients for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: tex-mex mix
directions: Mix together the sour cream and taco mix; set aside.
Mound up refried beans.
Pour mixture of sour cream and taco mix over mound.
Dice tomatoes and onions; put on top of mound, also. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Now, dip chips.

title: pecan pie
directions: In saucepan, mix brown sugar, flour, syrup, butter and salt. Heat until butter melts.
Beat eggs with vanilla.
Stir in syrup mix and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake below oven center at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: In large boiler, boil chicken in 2-quarts water with salt. Boil until tender and meat begins falling off bones.
Remove from heat, remove chicken from broth and cool.
Remove skin and meat. Tear meat into bite-size pieces.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash all the cucumbers and slice.
Add all into large stock pot.
Bring to a boil, stirring carefully, until all cucumber slices have changed color.
Makes about 7 pints.
Holds a long time in refrigerator, or they can be hot packed and sealed.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In a large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients.
Stir in a large amount of cracked ice.
Let stand 3 hours; drain well.
Remove garlic.
In a large kettle, combine remaining ingredients.
Add drained mixture.
Bring to a boil.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Dissolve the jello in 2 cups of boiling water.
Add the sugar and thawed strawberries.
Place in refrigerator until begins to thicken.
When mixture is mushy, fold in Cool Whip.
Break cake up into little pieces in bowl, alternating layers with strawberry mixture.

title: hot cranberry tea
directions: Heat to boiling.
Steep tea.
Add other ingredients and boil. Serve hot.

title: old granny's egg pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a large bowl, beat eggs for at least two minutes on low speed.
Add milk and flavoring blending well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 300 degrees and bake for 30-35 minutes longer.

title: pan seared salmon(prep time: 15 minutes; cooking time: 12 minutes.)
directions: In a small saucepan, bring wine, vinegar, sugar and citrus juices to a boil over high heat. Continue to boil until reduced to about 3/4 cup, 10 to 12 minutes; remove from heat and stir in black pepper.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a casserole dish, layer stew first with the hamburger.
Salt and pepper each layer.
Slice potatoes and celery and chop onion.
Place on top of hamburger.
Open kidney beans; do not drain.
Pour on top of potatoes.
Open tomato soup; do not add water.
Mix with Worcestershire, salt and pepper; pour on top
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours; stir after 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugars, margarine, peanut butter and egg.
Stir in flour, oats, soda and salt.
Spread in greased rectangular pan.
Bake for 17 to 22 minutes.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Cook 1 potato in 2 1/2 cups water; drain potato.
Let cool and add remaining ingredients.
Put in large bowl and keep in refrigerator taking out enough dough each time to make the number of biscuits desired.
Brush with butter and let rise 1 hour before baking at 450°.

title: diabetic fruit cake
directions: Combine raisins, dates or prunes, figs, apricots and orange rind in small bowl.
Set aside.
Cream oleo until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour, soda, baking powder and spices.
Pour in fruit mixture and meat until blended.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool and store in upright container for 3 days.
Freezes well.

title: orange delight salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add pineapple and drained oranges.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and chill.
Beat pudding and milk until smooth.
Fold into whipped cream.
Spoon onto gelatin.
Chill.
Add nuts, if desired.

title: rosemary breadsticks
directions: Let dough double in size.
Punch down and add or knead rosemary and garlic.
After a second rising, cut dough into small pieces.
Roll into sticks about 16 inches by 3/8 of an inch.

title: surprise brownies
directions: Heat oven according to directions on brownie mix.
Prepare as directed.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together the margarine and peanut butter. Add white and brown sugar.
Stir in egg, vanilla, flour and baking soda.
Place dough, a teaspoon at a time, on cookie sheet.
Press each spoonful flat with a floured fork. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Cool a minute or two before removing from cookie sheet.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: summertime green beans(serve room temperature or cold.)
directions: Drain beans and spoon sauce over them.
Good left over and stuffed in tomatoes.

title: deviled crab casserole
directions: Combine eggs, mayonnaise, Worcestershire, onion and hot pepper sauce.
Stir in crab and put in casserole.
Combine bread crumbs and butter.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix sugar, molasses, hot coffee and soda.
Add and mix rest of ingredients.
Chill.
Drop on cookie sheet and put jam in a small hole in center of cookie; sprinkle sugar on and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Drain and chill fruits; reserve juice.
Chop apricots. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add 1 cup juice from fruits. Chill until slightly congealed.
Fold in fruit and marshmallows. Pour into 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until set.
Spread with frosting as follows:
Combine sugar and flour.
Blend in beaten egg.
Gradually stir in juices.
Cook over low heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in butter. Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and spread over Jell-O.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Makes 12 servings.

title: best ever chicken stew
directions: Put whole chicken in 3 1/2 quart water in large Dutch oven. Put bay leaf, ham bone, chicken cubes, onion and parsley.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Take whole chicken out of water and remove bones.
Put all chicken back in pot.
Add remaining ingredients and cook on low 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with cornbread.

title: german chocolate sheet cake
directions: Spray a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with Pam or other nonstick coating.
Scatter coconut and pecans over bottom of pan.

title: creole meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ground beef, rice, onion, bell pepper, salt, thyme and egg.
Add 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Blend. Shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Pour off fat.
Meanwhile, heat oil and cook celery until tender.
Add remaining 1 1/2 cans tomato sauce.
Add parsley.
Simmer over low heat while baking meat loaf. After pouring off fat, top loaf with sauce.
Return to oven and bake for 10 minutes.
Serves six.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Mixture will be thick.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Prepare pastry for two crust pie.
Line bottom of 9-inch pie plate with pie pastry.
Coarsely crumble Ritz crackers on pastry. Combine and boil the water, sugar and cream of tartar.
Boil 15 minutes, gently.
Add lemon juice and zest.
Cool.
Pour over crackers and dot generously with butter.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add onions, Worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper and salt; mix well.
Chill.
Shape into ball and roll in nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown beef and drain fat.
Add all remaining ingredients. Simmer for 2 hours, uncovered.

title: apple cake
directions: Thoroughly mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Sift together all dry ingredients and stir in oil mixture.
Mix apples, walnuts and vanilla.
Pour into a 13 x 18-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until cake pulls loose around edges.

title: lo-cal spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with no-fat cracker of your choice or freshly cut vegetable sticks.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello with boiling water.
Let cool in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Add pineapple and blueberries.
Mix all and let jell.
Mix sour cream, cream cheese, vanilla and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and spread over jello mixture.
Top with a few crushed pecans.

title: streusel crunch topping
directions: Mix together flour and sugar.
Cut in butter.
Crumble over pie or cake.
Enjoy!!

title: butter ball cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar, vanilla, egg and salt.
Add flour and nuts. Roll in balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool and roll it in powdered sugar.

title: rhubarb piglet
directions: Roll the dough out, not too thin, like a pie crust.

title: shrimp marinara with fettuccine
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
In large saucepan, saute garlic in hot oil for 1 minute.
Add tomatoes and parsley; simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.

title: red velvet pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add food coloring.
Add dry ingredients with milk and vanilla.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325°.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan.

title: hamburger vegetable hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease.
Add potatoes, carrots, rice, corn, soup and water.
Bake 1 to 2 hours at 325° (until vegetables and rice are done).

title: jumbles
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a bowl beat butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg.
Combine flour and baking soda, blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in M & M baking bits, raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon on greased cookie sheet. Bake 13 - 15 minutes.

title: french coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box, using a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Remove from oven and while hot, drizzle creme of coconut over top, after poking cake full of holes.
Then drizzle can of Eagle Brand milk over cake.
Set aside and completely cool. Then spread Cool Whip over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with thawed coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: pretzel jello salad
directions: Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Cool.

title: john's meatballs
directions: Saute onions in 1/4 cup oil.
Add tomato sauce, garlic and basil.
Simmer 5 minutes before adding meatballs.
Mix eggs, ground beef, cheese and bread crumbs in large bowl.
Form into 1-inch meatballs and add to sauce.
Simmer for 15 minutes without stirring, then simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally. Serve alone or over pasta.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all together and let set.

title: chicken curry
directions: Brown chicken in teriyaki sauce and peanut oil.
Add all ingredients except onion.
Bring to a boil, then simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add onions.
Cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Serve over white rice.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Grease small bread pan; pour in fruit.
Sprinkle on dry cake mix; sprinkle on nuts and then drizzle on melted butter.
Bake at 325° until done.
Double for a large size 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix gelatin, cherry jello, lemon jello, sugar and hot water. Stir until dissolved.
Add cranberries, celery, pineapple and nuts.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: fudge marble pound cake
directions: Blend vanilla pudding mix, oil, eggs and water with the large packet of cake mix in a large bowl, then beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour 3/4 of the batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Blend contents of the small packet in the remaining batter.
Spoon the fudge batter here and there over the light batter.
Pull a knife through the batter in wide curves several times.
Bake at 350° for about 45 to 55 minutes, until center springs back when touched lightly.
Cool right side up for about 25 minutes, then remove from pan.
If desired, dust top of cooled cake with confectioners sugar.

title: corn bread muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients (corn meal, flour and sugar).
Add oil, egg substitute and milk.
Stir together by hand until moistened. Bake in muffin pan sprayed with cooking oil.
Bake in 450° oven for 15 minutes.

title: marshmallow brownies
directions: Melt Crisco over low heat; add cocoa, sugar and eggs.
Beat together.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix all together; add nuts.
Spread in pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done. Spread 1 pint Marshmallow Creme over hot brownies.

title: crispy baked chicken(low calorie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line a baking pan with foil and lightly spray foil with vegetable oil.
Rinse chicken and pat dry, set aside.
Pour milk into a shallow bowl.
Combine cornflake crumbs, rosemary and pepper in another shallow bowl.
Dip chicken pieces first into milk and then into crumb mixture.
Allow to stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Arrange chicken in prepared pan so pieces do not touch.
Bake 45 minutes, or until done.
Crumbs will form a crisp "skin."

title: marian's baked eggs
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish with butter.
Break bread into pieces and place on bottom of dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top of bread and bacon on top of cheese.
Add chilies and green onion. Whip eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over all. Refrigerate overnight.

title: barbecue sauce for spareribs
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onion and cook over low heat until onion is tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat.
This sauce may be used in several ways, on chicken, steak or hamburgers, too.

title: kahlua
directions: Save 1/2 cup water to dissolve coffee.
Make a syrup of sugar and water; bring to a boil.
Cook slowly for 8 to 10 minutes. Make coffee and add to syrup.
Bring to a boil; remove from heat and cool.
When cool, add vanilla and vodka.
Store in dark bottles.

title: quesadillas con salsa de tomatoe
directions: Take 2 tortillas and cut some thin slices of cheese.
Cover 1 tortilla with cheese and put the other tortilla on the top (like if you were making a sandwich).
Make as many as you want and put them aside.
In a small pan put the tomatoes to boil in water.
When they are ready, put them in a blender for about 30 seconds until the liquid is thick.
In another pan, put the vegetable oil on medium-high heat with the sliced onions.
Add the tomatoes.
Add some salt, pepper and garlic salt to your taste.
Cut some jalapenos in small circles to add.	Mix and let it cook for a couple of minutes.

title: apricot brandy pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add extracts. Add dry ingredients, alternating with sour cream and brandy. Bake in greased tube pan at 300° to 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie
