directions: Mix all together and pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: congo squares
directions: Melt shortening or oleo in saucepan (or microwave).
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and vanilla.
Transfer to large mixing bowl.
Allow to cool.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water, stirring 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes; stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 or 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using a wire whip, blend in whipped topping, then whip until smooth. Chill if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie crust.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with fruit, if desired.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add blueberries and pineapple.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: peppermint stick dessert
directions: Mix and put Oreos and oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: parmesan baked chicken(low carb)
directions: Choose quantity of chicken you desire.
Soak in Italian dressing in baking pan.
Mix bag of pork rinds, cup of parmesan cheese and 1/4 cup of soy flour together in food processor.
Blend until texture is similar to bread crumbs.
Place mixture in baggie, add chicken and shake.
Place chicken pieces back in baking pan with the Italian dressing.
Bake for 45 minutes at 375 degrees.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Line baking sheet with tinfoil.
Remove stems from mushrooms and clean.
Beat egg and add remaining ingredients.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps, dividing evenly. (At this point, mushroom caps can be refrigerated for up to an hour before you bake them.)
Bake for 5 minutes, then broil for 5 to 7 minutes 8-inches from the heat source.
Serve hot.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together in small bowl. Add butter and nuts last. Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until they are not juicy in the middle and do not shake.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except potato chips.
Top with the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 400° for 20 or 25 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Put first 4 ingredients into heavy saucepan and boil 4 minutes.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Drop on wax paper to cool.

title: knock you nakeds
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine dry cake mix, pecans, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and melted butter.
Press half of the batter into the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 8 minutes.

title: dirt cake(use a plastic flowerpot)
directions: Mix cream cheese, margarine and confectioners sugar using a mixer.
Into another bowl, mix 3 1/2 cups milk with the 2 boxes of pudding; add Cool Whip to pudding.
Gradually add cheese mixture to pudding mixture.

title: butterscotch bundt cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients.
Stir in butterscotch morsels.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake 55 minutes or until done.

title: supreme burgers
directions: Combine ground chuck, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup cream.
Shape into six patties.
In large skillet, add oil and pan-broil burgers over medium heat to desired doneness.
Remove to heated platter. Keep warm in oven while preparing sauce.
Cook shallots and mushrooms in pan drippings until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and cook for 3 minutes.
Pour sauce over patties.

title: 10 pound fruitcake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix sugar, eggs, butter and milk well. Roll nuts in 1 cup of flour, then add to creamed mixture.
Pour batter into Dutch oven and tie waxed paper over top.
Put Dutch oven into dishpan with water and boil for 2 hours.
Then put in oven and bake for 30 minutes at 300°.
Half all ingredients if you want a 5 pound cake.

title: potato salad
directions: Grate potatoes; add sour cream and all ingredients except bread crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole and top with bread crumbs.
Bake 50 minutes at 300°, uncovered.
Good with turkey.

title: rhubarb dumplings
directions: Chop first 5 ingredients in a blender or processor.
Add milk. Makes a stiff dough.
Roll to 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Spread with 2 tablespoons soft margarine, 2 cups finely chopped rhubarb and 1/2 cup sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Roll up from long side.
Cut in 12 one-inch slices.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut 2 pieces of aluminum foil and place a chicken breast in center of each.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Wrap well and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade soap
directions: Bring water and lye to a hard boil in "black wash pot."
Add the grease.
Keep at a slow, rolling boil, stirring with a long paddle.
Cook until the soap thickens and falls rope-like when lifted out of pot or until jell sets in a saucer.
Let cool in pot. When set and firm enough to handle, cut in hunks.
Push out and cut into smaller pieces.
Place on a table or board in sun to dry.

title: pecan pie
directions: Less 1 egg:
Replace with 2 ounces fudge.

title: down home beans
directions: Use a large Dutch oven or large frying pan.
Brown the beef with the diced onion until meat is no longer pink.
Spill off all the drippings.
Add the beans, ketchup, mustard and brown sugar and simmer for about 1/2 hour.
Cook the bacon until crispy; drain on absorbent paper, then crumble into beans.
Stir; simmer another few minutes and serve.

title: sunday dinner strawberry ice cream
directions: Whip together all ingredients except cream at low speed on mixer for 20 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into tray and freeze.
Yields 6 servings.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: (If using self-rising flour, omit salt and soda.)

title: can't fail corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, baking powder, salt, soda and sugar.
Add buttermilk and egg and beat thoroughly.
Add melted bacon drippings and beat again.
Pour into smoking hot skillet (8 x 2-inch).

title: bean soup
directions: I use my crock-pot and set on No. 3 or low setting for 6 hours. On stove top, simmer all ingredients for 2 to 3 hours.

title: dutch oven doughnuts
directions: You will need paper towels.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Shred Cracker Barrel cheese very fine.
Mix all ingredients together with mixer, except nuts. Shape mixture into ball.
Roll in crushed nuts.
Make day before to let flavor blend.

title: just for kids play putty
directions: Pour glue into a small bowl.
Gradually add starch and color. Let stand for 5 minutes.
Mix with hands until smooth and rubbery. If it is gooey, add more starch; if it is hard, add glue.
Store in an airtight container in the refrigerator for continued use.

title: easy chicken 'n rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook rice.
Mix soup, chicken and cheese together.
Drain rice well; toss with butter to taste.
Stir rice into soup mixture.
Put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve warm.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Place coconut and pecans in bottom of cake pan.
Pour cake mixture on top.
Mix remaining ingredients and drop by spoonfuls over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: paradise found
directions: Melt the sugar in the corn syrup over medium heat.
Do not overcook as it will harden.
Add peanut butter and remove from heat. Stir well. Add the Rice Krispies and press evenly with wax paper in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt all the chips and pour over the Rice Krispies.
When set, cut into squares and serve.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli.
Melt margarine and add to stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of stuffing mix in bottom.
Add the broccoli, then rest of stuffing mix.
Stir slightly.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 50 minutes.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together first 3 ingredients and add Crispix.
Mix to cover
cereal.
Pour
into	grocery
bag with 2 cups sugar. Shake to coat.
Serve in dog dish for effect (optional).

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Melt shortening and margarine.
Mix well.
Add brown sugar and sugar; add soda, vanilla flavoring and egg.
Mix for 5 minutes with a mixer.
Add flour and nuts to mixture; stir well.
Drop small balls of dough on ungreased baking sheet.
Place two chocolate chips on top of each ball and press chips in.
Don't flatten the dough.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: janet's waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery, grapes and walnuts in medium bowl. Set aside.	Combine sour cream and lemon juice.
Whip cream and sugar.
Fold into sour cream mixture and pour over fruit mixture. Stir gently.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: roly-poly candy
directions: Let butter soften in bowl.
Mix in powdered sugar, using hands.
A dab or two of evaporated milk may be used to help work mixture.

title: celestial snow cake
directions: Lightly grease and flour 3 (8-inch) cake pans.
Set aside. Combine all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Blend until moistened.
Beat at medium high speed for 4 minutes.
Spread batter evenly in the 3 prepared pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Let cool completely on wire rack.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and potato chips; turn into shallow buttered casserole.
Combine cheese and potato chips and spread over top.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: sunday rolls
directions: Scald the 2 cups of milk.
Add sugar, lard and salt.
Let cool to lukewarm.
Add the yeast, dissolved in the 1/2 cup of warm water.
Add flour and stir good.
Place in greased bowl; cover and let rise to double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Place dough on floured surface.
Knead and make into biscuits.
Place in greased pans and let rise again about 1 hour.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Enough to feed your Sunday company.

title: "chewier" brownies
directions: Melt unsweetened baking chocolate and sticks of butter in double boiler.
Cool slightly.
Beat in sugar.
Blend in beaten eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and salt, then stir in flour and chopped pecans.
Bake in 400°
oven for 35 to 40 minutes, or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost them, if you want, but they're so good, need no glossing over.

title: quick rolls
directions: Melt butter.
Add cream with sugar.
Add beaten egg.
Soften yeast in warm water and add to mixture.
Add flour until thick, but not stiff.
Spoon into greased muffin cups about 3/4 full. Bake at 450° until brown.
Rolls rise in oven.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Mix together eggs and milk.
Add in sugar, flour and nutmeg. Mix together.
Put rhubarb into pie crust.
Pour the mixture over the fruit.
Dot with butter.
Crisscross with strips of pie crust. Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: 8-layer mexican bean dip
directions: Layer in order shown.
Serve with chips.

title: pumpkin custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Heat milk to boiling.
Mix sugar, spices and milk.
Add to pumpkin, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Cook 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Mix graham crackers and melted margarine together.
Pat in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: chocolate covered cherries
directions: Beat butter until creamy; gradually add powdered sugar. Add milk and liqueur. Mix until blended. Shape sugar mixture around cherries. Coat completely and put on wax paper. Microwave chocolate in 2-cup glass measuring cup at High 1 1/2 minutes or until melted. Stir twice. Dip coated cherries by stems into chocolate. Allow excess to drip off. Place on wax paper. Let stand until firm. Store loosely covered in cool place 1 week or until centers soften. Yields 3 dozen.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Fry bacon in large skillet; drain fat. Combine with rest of ingredients.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken pie
directions: Spread chicken on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Mix 1 2/3 cups of broth and soup (also vegetables, if desired) and pour over chicken. Slice egg on top.

title: chimichangas
directions: In a skillet, brown beef, onion and garlic.
Drain liquid. Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and chilies.
Simmer for 20 minutes or until most of liquid evaporates.
Place 3 tablespoons of meat mixture on each tortilla; roll to make a cylinder.
Secure with a wooden pick.
Deep fry chimichangas in 375° fat until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Keep warm in 350° oven. Serve with condiments.

title: shipwreck stew
directions: Slice onion, potatoes and carrots.
Grease baking dish.
Layer in order listed.
Season to taste.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 2 hours.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When baked, punch holes in top with toothpick and bring to a boil water and sugar and pour over cake.
Let cool.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip, powdered sugar and
1/4 package coconut.
Spread over cake.
Sprinkle remainder of coconut over top.

title: lemon poppy seed pound cake
directions: Soak poppy seeds in water about 30 minutes. Combine poppy seeds, cake mix, instant pudding, lemon extract, vanilla extract, lemon zest, sour cream, oil and eggs in a large mixing bowl and beat until smooth. Pour batter into 12-cup Bundt pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and lightly dusted with flour. Bake at 325° until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven and place on slightly damp dish towel until cool. When cake is completely cool, invert onto serving platter. Serve with Lemon Curd Sauce.

title: carrot marinade salad
directions: Boil carrots in salted water until almost tender. Cool. Put carrots, peppers and onions in a dish. Blend rest of mixture and pour over carrots. Refrigerate 12 to 24 hours.

title: chop suey
directions: Cut meat into small pieces; brown in frying pan.
Add a little water after browning for gravy.
In medium kettle, cut up celery and onions in small pieces.
Add juice from sprouts and 2 tablespoons molasses.
Cook this all together until vegetables are done.
Add sprouts; cook 3 minutes more, then thicken.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar. Chill until thick (1 1/2 hours).
Pour 1/2 cup of thick Jell-O into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Put 3 pineapple rings in 1 cup of thick Jell-O.
Fold in banana slices and spoon into pan.
Chill until set, but not firm, about 15 minutes.
Blend mayonnaise in rest of Jell-O until smooth.
Stir in celery and spoon into pan.
Chill until firm, 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold and slice.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: tapioca fruit salad
directions: Mix juices from fruit and add water to make 3 cups.
Add to tapioca pudding and cook until thick.
Cool.
Add fruit when ready to serve.
Add 3 bananas.

title: quick and easy cookies(chocolate)
directions: Beat with fork egg; add oil and water.
Mix well and add to dry cake mix.
Add oatmeal, nuts and chips.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost with chocolate chips.

title: chocolate sugar plums
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl. Mix well. Roll into 1-inch balls. Chill for 10 minutes. Melt together chocolate chips and paraffin. Dip each ball in chocolate, using toothpick. When balls are covered, place them on wax paper to cool. Makes 8 dozen.

title: pineapple delight cake
directions: Make cake as directed in 9x13 pan.
After removing from oven, punch lots of holes on top of cake with fork.
Let stand to cool. Combine condensed milk and pineapple juice and mix well.
Pour over top of cake.
Then spread Cool Whip on top of cake and garnish with crushed pineapple.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: elegant stuffed onions
directions: Peel onions, removing thin outer layer only; slice off tops. Reserve.
Cover onions with boiling, salted water in saucepan. Simmer for 30 minutes until tender.
Drain; cool.
Chop onion tops to make 1/3 cup of finely chopped onions.
Saute in butter until golden.
Chop olives; add bread crumbs, parsley, salt, poultry seasoning, sage and pepper; toss.
Scoop out center portions of onions (reserve and chop centers for use in flavoring peas for another meal).
Do not cut through bottom of onion "shells."
Fill shells with stuffing.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover; bake 10 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cheese and olives on rye
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spread on party rye bread. (This will do a little less than one loaf.)
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: roast cornish hen
directions: Dice onion and stuff in both birds.
Mince garlic and stuff in birds.
Pepper inside of bird to taste.
Place in roasting dish and roast at 350° for one hour, uncovered.
Serves two.

title: fresh lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and boiling water. Stir until sugar dissolves. Add lemon juice and cold water. Mix well. Chill. Serve over ice.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease tube pan well.
Open biscuits and cut into fourths and coat with sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Place in tube pan.
Melt brown sugar and oleo; bring to a boil.
Boil only 1 minute.
Pour over biscuits and bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Let stand 10 minutes before removing from pan.
Better when eaten warm.
Just pinch pieces with fingers and enjoy.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook meat, onions and green peppers.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, salt, chili powder and pepper; heat through.
Pour into casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: miracle cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add sifted flour alternately with eggs.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into a sheet cake pan or a tube cake pan.
Bake at 325°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: swedish platter
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, salt and cream.
Add flour gradually. Beat with beater as you add until smooth.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake
cake
according
to package directions in 2 round layers.
After
cake has cooled, split into 4 round layers and fill with the following mixture.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat with onion, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.
Layer Doritos, meat mixture and spread grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: karen's nachos
directions: Brown ground turkey with onion and mushrooms; drain.
Spread chips on cookie sheet.
Spoon salsa over chips.
Cut olives in pieces and arrange over salsa.
Put meat mixture over olives. Layer Cheddar and Mozzarella cheeses on top.
Warm under broiler until cheeses are melted.
Serve immediately.

title: sally lunn bread
directions: Blend Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Place in 9-inch square pan which has been rubbed with Crisco and bake in hot oven at 400° about 25 minutes. Makes 18 pieces.

title: cappuccino
directions: Makes 4 servings.
Pour milk into 4-cup glass measure and cook on high for 3 to 3 1/2 minutes or until hot, but not boiling. Stir in chocolate, sugar and coffee until dissolved.
Pour into 4 mugs.
Add 1 ounce brandy into each mug.
Top with whipped cream. Serve warm.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Cook giblets from turkey or chicken; save broth.
Mix cornmeal, oil and enough water to blend thoroughly.
Bake mixture at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove and cool.
In large bowl, mix cooled, baked cornmeal mixture with stuffing mix.
Add sage, celery and onion.
Pour in broth.
Dressing should be moist. Whisk the eggs through mixture.
Stuff turkey and bake.

title: frances madden's strawberry mousse
directions: Place mixer bowl and beaters in freezer to chill.
Wash and cut up strawberries.
Add sugar and mash well with a fork.
If strawberries are not tart enough, you may add a little lemon juice to taste.
Remove bowl from freezer and add whipping cream and a little vanilla.
Whip the cream and fold in strawberry mixture. Pour into a container and freeze.
This is better than any strawberry ice cream I've ever tasted!
Recipe easily doubles or triples.

title: oreo chocolate cookie
directions: Blend Oreos with the butter.
Press 1/2 the mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Whip the cream.
Add Fluff and liqueur and top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze and enjoy.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup, salt and pepper. Alternate layers of potatoes, soup mix, cheese, onion and ham. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in flour, baking powder and orange juice.
Pour half of batter in a greased pan.
Peel and thinly slice 3 large apples.
Put apples on top of batter.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon mixed together.
Then add rest of batter and sprinkle with more cinnamon-sugar mixture on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Enjoy.

title: aunt donna's chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle thin layer of cornbread mix into bottom of Pam-coated baking dish.
Shred chicken breasts.
Place 1/2 chicken pieces over cornbread mix.
Mix together soups, melted oleo and chicken broth; pour 1/2 mix over chicken.
Layer dry Stove Top stuffing mix, remainder of chicken pieces and soup.
Top with cornbread mix. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: simple skillet dinner
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve syrup.
In large skillet, saute ham in butter until lightly browned.
Add enough water to pineapple syrup to make 2 cups liquid; add to skillet.
Stir in contents of rice mix.
Bring to boil.
Cover; simmer 5 to 10 minutes until liquid is absorbed.
Fold in pineapple.
Sprinkle with parsley to serve.
Serves 4.

title: strawberries
directions: Mix the Jell-O, milk and coloring together in a large mixing bowl.
Add the coconut and nuts.
Mix well and chill overnight or several hours.
Roll in shape of strawberries.
Roll in red crystal sugar and chill while mixing ingredients together for leaves.

title: sunday biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
(I always sift this mixture 3 times for a finer textured biscuit.)
Add oil and milk.
Knead dough 5 to 6 times. Roll out on a floured surface and cut with a round cutter.
Pour about 3 tablespoons oil in bottom of pan.
Put biscuits in pan, no room between them; bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with butter and honey.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix together the sugar and cornstarch.
Add the boiling water. Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Gradually add jello.
Line baked, cooled crust with fresh strawberries.
Pour above mixture on top.
Refrigerate.
After the pie sets, top with Cool Whip.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together and set aside.
Cream together butter, shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add one egg to butter mixture and cream until fluffy.
Stir in dry ingredients until mixture is smooth.
Blend in milk.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of water glass, which has been dipped in sugar.
Bake in 400° oven.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and place rhubarb, dry Jell-O, sugar and marshmallows evenly over bottom.
Mix cake mix as directed. Pour over all.
Bake at 350° for 50 or 60 minutes.
Invert onto serving tray.
Before serving, top with whipped topping.
Can be frozen.

title: tempting bananas
directions: Cut bananas in half and place in shallow baking dish.
Pour in wine.
Mix together brown sugar and white sugar.
Sprinkle the sugar mixture over the bananas and dot with dabs of butter. Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar cheese potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes 1/8 inch thick.
Mix soup, butter, milk, onion, salt
and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Cook in 2 quart casserole dish in microwave for 45 minutes.

title: old fashion sugar cookies
directions: In a large mixing bowl cream together butter, sugar, egg, milk and vanilla.
Stir in flour and mix well.
Cover dough and let chill two to three hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
After chilling, roll dough into small balls, placing on a lightly greased cookie sheet two inches apart.
Flatten tops lightly with a buttered glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.
Makes about three dozen.

title: betsy's (#1) icebox pie
directions: Mix and pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar and milk 1 minute; remove from heat and add oats, vanilla, margarine and peanut butter.
Beat until thick enough to drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a heavy 4-quart pan.
Stir in milk. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil, without stirring, until it reaches 234° (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it thickens. Add nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.
(Be careful not to overbeat.)

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and beat until fluffy.
Add 7-Up and beat well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
While cake is hot, pour over pineapple icing.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Melt 1 stick of margarine; put in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Mix together the flour, milk and 1 cup sugar; pour over melted margarine, but don't stir.
Mix together the blueberries and 1 cup of sugar; pour over batter.
Do not stir!
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: franks and cheese casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Simmer milk and salt over low heat just below boiling point.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Pour liquid over cooked noodles and wieners into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: orange nut bread
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, sugar, salt and soda.
In separate bowl, combine egg, orange peel, orange juice, lemon peel, lemon juice and oil.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Fold in nuts.
Put batter into a greased loaf pan. Bake at 350° for about 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool in pan at least 10 minutes.
Freezes beautifully.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: italian cookies
directions: Soften cream cheese with 1/2 cup milk; mix well until well blended and smooth.
Add instant pudding and remaining
1 cup milk.
Beat slowly 1 to 2 minutes, scraping sides of bowl.
Spread mixture over top of cooled cake (in pan).
Sprinkle well drained pineapple on top of pudding mixture.
Top with Cool Whip; spread evenly to cover.
Keep chilled.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Shred cabbage; brown meat, onion and garlic.
Place in large casserole dish.
Place cabbage in bottom, then layer of rice and meat mixture.
Dilute soup with water.
Season to taste.
Pour over top; do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Check to make sure liquid has not cooked away; add more water if needed.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine water and sugar.
Boil for 30 minutes.
Then add juices.
Freeze
until ready to use.
About 1/2 hour before serving, slush frozen mixture and add 7-Up and strawberries. Serves about 40.

title: chili with beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain excess grease, then return to a crock-pot.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer all day on low heat in a slow cooker.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate.
Will keep 2 to 3 days in refrigerator.

title: mini-cheesecakes
directions: Mix together cream cheese, eggs, lemon juice, vanilla and sugar until fluffy.
Place 1 vanilla wafer in tassie pan cup. Fill 3/4 full with cheese mixture.
Bake in preheated 375° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool.
Top each with 2 cherries.

title: corn willy
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brush shell with mustard.
Bake 5 minutes.
Remove shell from oven; retain oven temperature.
Melt butter in heavy medium saucepan over medium-high heat.
Add mushrooms and onion and saute until just tender, about 1 minute. Add livers and saute 1 minute.
Reduce heat to low; cover and cook 15 minutes.
Blend in sour cream and sherry and stir until mixture is heated through.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spoon mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with bacon and grated cheeses.
Whip eggs lightly; add cream, cayenne, sugar and pepper and blend well. Pour over cheese.
Bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 400° and continue baking until tester inserted in center comes out clean (about 20 minutes).
Let quiche cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: hamburger surprise
directions: Brown hamburger. Make a layer of Tater Tots, layer of hamburger and a layer of cheese.
Heat soup with water.
Pour over layers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
When well dissolved, add sour cream and whisk until well blended.
Add crushed pineapple.
Cool in refrigerator until partially set.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch dish; return to refrigerator until completely set.
Serve when firmly set.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Cook as your regular corn bread.

title: fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except soda, buttermilk and spices.
When mixed well, add 3 teaspoons soda with the buttermilk and add to mixture, then add all spices.
Mix well.
Dip out by teaspoon.
Bake 20 minutes at 300°.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Toss before serving.
Recipe can easily be doubled.
Can use 1/2 fat free dressing, 1/2 regular dressing if desired.

title: artichoke pizza
directions: Unroll dough into rectangles and press on bottom and sides of 15 x 10 x 1 or 2-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Mix altogether in large bowl and then pour in greased 10 x 17-inch cake pan.
Then put one layer pizza cheese (2 cups), one layer of Parmesan cheese.
Top with layer of chopped pepperoni. Cover with foil and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Very good.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together shortening, sugar, molasses and eggs.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and cinnamon and add.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by spoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly oiled cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in a moderately hot oven (400°). Good!

title: frozen lemon pies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and put in a graham cracker crust. Freeze.
Makes 2 pies.

title: apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425° (hot).
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Mix lightly through apples.
Heap up in pastry lined pie pan.
Dot with butter. Cover with top crust which has slits cut in it.
Seal and flute.
Cover edge with 1 1/2-inch strip of aluminum foil to prevent excessive browning.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until crust is nicely browned and apples are cooked through (test with fork). Serve warm or cold.
May be topped with cream, whipped cream or ice cream. Or serve with a slice of cheese.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: coconut pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs in medium bowl.
Add brown sugar; stir until brown sugar dissolves.
Add next 6 ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into pie shell.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until center is puffed.
Cool.
Chill until serving time.
Serve with whipped cream and chopped pecans.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together well first two ingredients.
Add all other ingredients, except nuts.
Mix and chill.
Shape into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 2 small loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cherry cola dessert
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Measure syrup and add water if necessary to make 2 cups.
Heat syrup to boiling.
Pour over jello, stir until dissolved.
Add Coke.
Chill to consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Combine cherries, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in and chill until firm.

title: old-fashion oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat together margarine, sugars, eggs, water and vanilla until blended. Combine flour, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add to mixture and mix well. Stir in oats. Chill dough at least 1 hour. Make small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: gazpacho
directions: Chop all vegetables very fine.
Put in large jar or covered container.
Cover with tomato juice.
Add rest of seasoning to taste.
Refrigerate at least 6 to 8 hours before serving.

title: judy's scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° until top is brown, about 1 hour.

title: banana fritters
directions: In a deep mixing bowl, stir the flour and sugar together.
Beat the eggs one at a time.
Using a whisk add milk to eggs beating constantly.
Beat batter until it is smooth and elastic.
Mash bananas to a smooth puree.
Stir the banana puree into the batter and let the mixture rest at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a pan to 375°.
Drop about 1/4 cup of batter into oil and fry on each side until golden brown.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: gramma's clam chowder
directions: Slice
pork
and cut into tiny pieces.	Fry until crisp and golden; watch carefully.
Remove and drain.
In fat, cook onion, until tender.
Cut potatoes into 1/2-inch cubes and add to onion, then
add
water to cover.	Cook until potatoes are almost done. Add
clams	with
juice and cook 5 more minutes. Add milk
or half
and
half.
Season
with
salt and pepper. Bring to boiling, but do not boil.
Add butter and serve warm with crackers.
Sprinkle salt pork on top for more flavor.

title: beans - no gas!
directions: In the morning, wash the beans.
Then place them in the amount of water needed for cooking them.
Let them soak all day.
Before going to bed, place them in the freezer.
Cook them in the same water that is now ice, but do not add salt.
Add meat tenderizer with Papain or Papaya enzyme tablets.
Add mustard, molasses and onion.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar, beaten eggs and margarine well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour	into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lemon baked sole
directions: Rinse fillets thoroughly in cold water; pat dry with paper towels and set aside.
Combine melted margarine and lemon juice in a small bowl.
Combine flour, chopped parsley and pepper in a shallow container.
Dip fillets in margarine mixture and dredge in flour mixture.
Transfer fillets to a nonstick baking sheet and drizzle any remaining margarine mixture over fish.
Sprinkle fillets with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until fish is golden brown and flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: lemon jello salad
directions: Set Jell-O, slice bananas on top.
Drain pineapple, add water to juice to make 1 cup.
Cook together.
Cook until thick, let cool and add crushed pineapple.
Spread over bananas, top with Cool Whip and nuts.

title: swiss cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Serve with assorted crackers or breadsticks.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: baked cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage into 1-inch squares.
Put in casserole dish. Mix sugar and flour. Combine with cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over cabbage.
Cover with raw bacon. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered. Remove cover and bake until bacon is crisp.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Mix ingredients and cook slowly over medium heat until thickened.
Remove from heat and pour over a dish of finely chopped cabbage.
Can also be served over string beans or mashed potatoes.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except nuts, parsley or dried beef.
Form into one large ball or two small balls and roll in nuts, parsley or dried beef.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature with crackers.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Spoon sherbet by tablespoon into a large punch bowl.
Slowly pour in chilled lemon-lime beverage; stir gently to mix.

title: coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs. Beat well. Combine dry ingredients. Add to sugar mixture alternating with buttermilk and beating well after each addition. Stir in nuts, flavoring and coconut. Pour into well-greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Pour hot Coconut Syrup over hot cake.
Let set 4 hours. Wrap well.

title: andrea's dip
directions: Mash corned beef and mix with all ingredients.
Serve inside large dip bread or with crackers.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli until desired tenderness (do not drain).
Melt butter and mix together all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate icing
directions: In a 2-quart pan, bring to a boil the first three ingredients and then the last three.
Pour hot icing over cake.

title: coconut dream bars
directions: Mix first four ingredients well and put into 9 x 12-inch ungreased pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until slightly browned in moderate oven.
Blend the remaining ingredients and spread over first layer.
Bake in moderate oven 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut while hot.

title: apple dessert griddlecakes
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, salt and cinnamon.
Combine milk and maple syrup and add this mixture to dry ingredients. Stir in beaten egg and melted shortening.
Add chopped apple. Drop by rounded tablespoonful onto hot greased griddle.
Bake until top is bubbly and underside is golden, then turn and brown other side.
Serve with 10x sugar or with warm, spicy applesauce.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until frothy.
Beat in oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Beat for 4 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and walnuts. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes in two greased loaf pans.

title: cajun fried potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in cubes and cook in boiling water until just tender (about 7 minutes).
Drain and cool.
Combine all other ingredients in a bowl.
Add potatoes and toss to coat evenly.

title: simply super cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 12-inch pan according to package directions.
Remove from oven and with a fork, punch cake full of holes.
Pour condensed milk over hot cake.
Let cool and spread undrained crushed pineapple on cake.
Frost with whipped topping and sprinkle with toasted coconut.
Serves 24.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs for 5 minutes, then gradually add the sugar.
Stir in the pumpkin and lemon juice.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to pumpkin mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 15 x 10-inch pan.
Top with the chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Turn out on a towel which has been sprinkled with confectioners sugar.
Starting at the narrow end, roll towel and cake together. Cool.
Unroll.
Fill with filling; re-roll cake.
Chill before cutting into slices.

title: my man cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Blend into sugar mixture.
Add oatmeal and mix.
Add coconut and pecans. Drop by spoons onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: black and white cheesecake brownies
directions: Brownie base:
Preheat oven to 350°. Melt Toll House Little Bits semi-sweet chocolate.
Stir until smooth; set aside.
In large bowl, combine sugar and butter. Beat until creamy.
Add eggs, vanilla extract and salt; mix well.
Add melted morsels and flour; mix well.
Spread into foil lined 9-inch square baking pan.

title: spicy beef dip
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Add ground beef and brown. Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Spoon off fat.
Add cayenne (red pepper).
Take off burners and add cheeses.

title: okra fritters
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients. Stir in okra. Pour oil to a depth of 2-inches in a Dutch oven. Heat to 350°. Drop mixture by tablespoons into oil. Cook until golden brown, turning once. Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with salt if desired. Serve immediately. Serves 4 to 6.

title: bourbon street baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees in a 10 inch skillet over medium heat fry bacon until crisp. Crumble. Saute onion in the bacon fat. Using a slotted spoon, carefully lift onion from the fat and place in a 1 1/2 qt. baking dish.
To baking dish add all other ingredients except bacon. Gently stir to
mix thoroughly. Sprinkle bacon on top. Bake 1 hour. Beans should be bubbly and thick.

title: 7 layer cookies
directions: Melt oleo or butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then layer graham cracker crumbs, chips and coconut.
Drizzle Eagle Brand milk over top with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: super creole sauce
directions: Cook finely chopped onion and green pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomato sauce, fresh or canned mushrooms, water, pepper, salt and garlic.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve over fish and chicken.

title: fat-free strawberries in snow
directions: In large bowl, crumble angel food cake into bite-size pieces. In a different bowl, combine sugar, milk, cream cheese and Dream Whip (will be soupy).
Pour over cake.
Combine strawberries and glaze and pour over top of cake.
Let set overnight before serving.
(Keep refrigerated.)

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except
Ritz crackers and margarine. Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and melted margarine.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake the potatoes until done. Brown the ground beef, then drain. Add salsa to ground beef. Slice the potatoes in half. Fluff, do not scoop out.
Add ground beef mixture on potatoes. Layer with grated cheese, sour cream, tomato and lettuce. Delicious and quick.

title: two-tone bites
directions: Over hot, not boiling water, combine butterscotch chips, butter and water.
Stir until chips melt and are smooth.
Add nuts.
Mix well.
Press into foil-lined 8-inch square pan.

title: mexican salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients. Add crumbled Fritos just before serving.

title: french chicken
directions: Boil chicken and
onion.
Take	chicken off bone.
Cook soups and Ro-Tel tomatoes for 10 minutes; add chicken and cook 10 minutes more.

title: salsa mac
directions: Brown meat in large skillet; drain.
Stir in salsa and water. Bring to a boil.
Stir in macaroni.
Reduce heat to medium - low. Cover and simmer until macaroni is tender.
Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: sausage and peppers italiano
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat; add green peppers, onions and garlic and cook until peppers are tender-crisp; drain off fat. Stir in soup, water and vinegar. Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in mixing bowl.
Beat until thick and smooth.
Makes 4 cups.
Spoon 1 1/2 heaping tablespoons of icing into pint size freezer bags.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
When you are ready, snip "tiny" bottom corner of bag. This serves as individual decorating bags.
Makes 4 to 5 decorating bags.

title: zucchini crescent pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
In a 10-inch skillet, cook zucchini and onion in margarine until tender, about 10 minutes.
Stir in parsley and seasonings.
In a large bowl, blend eggs and cheese. Stir in vegetable mixture.
Separate dough into 8 triangles. Place in an ungreased quiche pan or a 10-inch pie pan.
Press over bottom and up sides to form crust.
Spread mustard on crust and pour vegetable mixture evenly onto crust.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until knife comes out clean.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt pan or angel food pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes in 350° preheated oven (30 minutes at 375° for 2 loaf pans).

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo. Mix beaten eggs, sugar and oleo. Add coconut, raisins, nuts and vinegar. Pour into unbaked crust. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix
ingredients and slowly add 1 cup salad oil.
Allow to stand
a
day at room temperature before serving.
Makes 1 pint.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Peel, then grate potatoes in large bowl.
After all potatoes have been grated, squeeze most of the liquid out with a ladle. Add crushed garlic, eggs, caraway seed, salt and pepper to potatoes and mix well.
Heat oil in a frying pan on medium-high. Fill one ladle full of the potato mixture, spread it like a pancake and fry until golden brown on both sides.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Make pie crust for 9-inch pie pan and bake.
Combine all ingredients and add a little butter or margarine.
Cook until thick. Add vanilla.
Let pie cool read good.
Whip 1 pint whipping cream and spread on cold pie.
Add small can of coconut on top of whipped cream and serve.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Beat egg yolks and add to butter and sugar.
Sift together flour, mace, baking powder and cinnamon.
Cut fruits into pieces. Pour 2 cups brandy over fruit and let stand all night.
Coat nuts with flour, then add to creamed mixture.
Then add 4 teaspoons milk and 2 teaspoons fruit juice.
Beat stiff 7 egg whites and blend well.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours or until firm.

title: munchskins
directions: Mix soup mix, spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise and chopped chestnuts.
On cookie sheet, bake 20 potato skins (cut side up) at 425° for approximately 14 minutes.
Add filling mix and top with cheese and bacon bits.
Bake for an additional 10 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook pasta.
Melt butter; blend in flour.
Add chicken broth and half and half.
Cook until thickened and bubbly.
Add remaining ingredients, except the Parmesan cheese.
Top and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Put in a blender and slowly add oil. Blend constantly until thick; add poppy seed and beat a few more minutes.

title: buttermilk pralines
directions: Combine sugar, salt, soda and milk in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until soft ball stage.
Stir often to prevent burning. Remove from heat; add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Beat until thick; pour into a serving dish.

title: london broil
directions: Place steak in shallow glass dish.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours, turning meat occasionally.
Set oven control at broil and/or 550°. Remove steak from marinade.
Broil 2 to 3 inches from heat for 4 minutes.
Turn; broil 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Cut meat diagonally across grain into thin slices.
If desired, salt before serving. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: play dough recipe
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a saucepan.
Put liquid ingredients together in a cup and add to dry ingredients.
Stir constantly with wooden spoon over medium heat until mixture forms a ball and leaves the side of the pan.
Cook until very firm and somewhat dry.
Dump onto counter and knead well when dough is cool enough to handle.
Store in Ziploc bags when cool.

title: cheese dip
directions: Put all ingredients in microwave safe dish and heat until melted.
Stirring occasionally.

title: green beans and red potatoes
directions: Pour beans in a casserole dish.
Scrub red potatoes and quarter.
Add bacon grease or ham bits along with quartered potatoes, mixed into the beans.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour.

title: apple coconut custard pie
directions: Mix pie filling and spices.
Pour into pie shell.
Beat eggs; add salt, sugar and coconut.
Add hot milk while stirring.
Pour over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat egg yolks; brush on crusts.
Put in oven at 350° for 5 minutes.
(This will prevent crusts from cracking.) Remove from oven.
Spread fudge on crusts bottoms while hot (about 1/4-inch thick); let cool.

title: granola
directions: Combine first four ingredients and coconut in a large bowl. Combine honey, oil, sugar and vanilla in a small saucepan.
Heat, but don't boil.
Add to oats mixture; stir until well blended. Spread evenly in two oiled cookie pans.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from oven.
Stir in raisins.
Cool.
Store in tightly closed container or seal in plastic bags.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: old fashioned scrapple
directions: In a large saucepan, combine pork, cornmeal, chicken broth, thyme and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer about 2 minutes or until mixture is very thick, stirring constantly.
Line an 8-inch square pan with waxed paper. Extend 3 to 4-inches above top of pan.
Spoon pork mixture into pan. Cover and chill in refrigerator 4 hours or overnight.
Unmold. Cut into squares.
Combine flour and pepper. Dust squares with flour mixture and brown on all sides in hot oil. Can put in loaf pan and slice before flouring and browning.

title: creamy onion dressing
directions: Measure 3 cups flour into large bowl; answer telephone; take large bowl off small son's head; sweep up flour.

title: chesapeake bay blue crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients except crab, flour and butter (or oil) and adjust seasoning.
Gently fold into crab meat.
Portion into 3 1/2-ounce cakes.
Lightly flour and saute in butter (or oil). Serve immediately with "Cocktail Sauce From Hell."
Serves 6.

title: chocolate clair
directions: Layer 9 x 13 dish with graham crackers. Combine pudding mix, milk and Cool Whip. Layer 1/2 of pudding mixture over graham crackers, then another layer of graham crackers, then remaining pudding mixture. Refrigerate until pudding is firm. Add another layer of graham crackers and top with frosting. Refrigerate again.

title: hot jalapeno cornbread
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Bake in well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes. Remove from oven immediately so it won't dry out.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: cranberry upside-down cake(kid's recipe #2)
directions: Slice the butter into thin pieces evenly in 9 x 12-inch pan. Sprinkle the walnut halves over the butter.
Wash and dry the cranberries and put them over the nuts.
Mix the white and brown sugar and spread over cranberries, mixing slightly.
Mix the cake as directed and pour over everything.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes (it's done when a toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean).
Let cool for 10 minutes, then loosen edges and turn over onto serving plate.
Serve with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.
Enjoy!

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl.
Put wings and sauce in a Ziploc bag.
Refrigerate overnight, turning once.
Put in pan.
Spray throw-away broiler pans with Pam.
Do not put much sauce when cooking (just a spoon).
Cook at 350° to 375° for 2 hours, turning once.

title: peach fluff salad
directions: Add Jell-O and hot water.
Mix well. Drain juice from peaches. Add enough cold water to juice to equal 1 cup. Add peaches, juice and Jell-O mixture.
Put in refrigerator and start to jell. Add sour cream and return to refrigerator.
Chill well.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour and sugar; mix well.
Cut in shortening.
Add soda to buttermilk in a separate bowl.
Add yeast to warm water; let dissolve in a glass bowl.
Add buttermilk to 8 cups of flour. Stir in yeast water; stir well.
Add more flour, as needed, to make a good texture dough.
Roll out on a floured surface and knead for 2 minutes.
Roll out 1/2-inch thick and slice into squares of 2-inches.

title: bake baby lima beans
directions: Let beans set overnight in water.
Cook beans and add bacon, molasses, brown sugar, dry mustard, salt, sugar and catsup to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well. Add flavoring.
Add sifted dry ingredients slowly.
Add fruits and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 300° to 325° or until done.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Use a deep dish.
Tear cake into pieces and put in bottom of dish.
Mix Cool Whip, sour cream, evaporated milk and sugar.
Pour mixture over cake.
Spread your strawberry glaze over top of mixture and your sliced strawberries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chicken stock
directions: Cut up chicken.
Add gibblets, if avalible.
Combine all ingredients in a large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Strain.

title: noodle pudding
directions: Cook noodles as directed; cool 5 minutes.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan with margarine.
Melt remainder of stick.
Place cooled noodles in pan.
Mix all other ingredients and pour over noodles. Top with raisins if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Make a well and stir in pumpkin, oil, egg and vanilla.
Mix well and fill muffin pans 2/3 full. Yields 18 muffins.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, garlic powder and oregano and then drain.
Set aside and add spaghetti sauce to make a thick, not soupy, sauce.
Prepare noodles according to package directions and drain.
In a bowl mix cottage cheese and eggs.
Next, in a large (baking) casserole dish, layer noodles, sauce, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese until all ingredients are gone ending with Mozzarella cheese as topping.
Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: skillet chicken and corn
directions: In a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter. Cook chicken until brown on both sides. Remove and set aside. In the same skillet, combine soup, milk, broccoli, cheese and pepper. Heat to boiling. Return chicken to skillet. Reduce heat. Cover and cook 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink and broccoli is tender-crisp. Stir occasionally.

title: lima bean special
directions: Cook lima beans as directed; drain well.
In skillet, in oil, over medium heat, saute onion, celery and garlic 5 minutes to soften. Add lima beans and remaining ingredients. Cook 2 minutes or until hot.

title: crunchy chicken salad
directions: Pour sauce over meat mixture.
Refrigerate 6 hours.

title: butter crisp cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, then flour, soda, vanilla and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful (or can be made into rolls, put on aluminum foil and freeze).
Bake when desired.
Bake at 300° until light brown.

title: peach apple conserve
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, apples and 1 1/2 cups water in kettle. Stir well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until of honey consistency.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yield: 3 to 4 jars.

title: japanese fruitcake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar and vanilla until fluffy. Add beaten egg yolks and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour half of this batter in two greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
To the remaining batter add raisins, nuts, cloves and cinnamon.
Pour this batter into 2 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
When cool, spread filling between layers and on top (not on sides).

title: apple chip cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, cinnamon, eggs and vanilla together.
Add the apples to this mixture.
Mix together flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Add to the apple mixture, mixing well, but do not use electric mixer.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
While hot, butter the top of cake and sprinkle with granulated sugar.

title: myra's peanut butter pie
directions: Cream first three items together.
Slowly blend in milk and Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: so good - so easy salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sprinkle dry jello in and mix. Refrigerate overnight.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and cream in a heavy saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes.
Stir constantly to keep from sticking.
Remove from heat and add marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Pour into a glass dish sprayed with Pam.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: barbecue hamburger meatballs
directions: Roll ground beef into bite size balls.
Place in a skillet. Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown the meatballs; drain.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add the peanut butter and mix well. Add the Rice Krispies and stir.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Melt the chocolate chips and put on top.

title: knox diet squares(fat-free)
directions: In large bowl, combine Knox gelatine and flavored gelatin; add boiling water and stir until gelatin dissolves.
Pour into pan (13 x 9-inch) and chill until firm.
Makes about 100 (1-inch) squares.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Place 1/2 to 3/4 of wafer crumbs in bottom of 8-inch square pan and press down.
Cream butter and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Spread over crumbs.
Add layer of nuts and berries.
Whip the cream stiff and spread over berries.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Baking Temperature: 375°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream together the butter and sugar. Add the eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add the almond extract.
Stir in the flour and baking powder.
Mix until smooth.

title: broccoli cheese squares
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Steam broccoli until partially cooked, about 3 minutes.
Cool and press dry.
Beat eggs with milk until frothy.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into egg mixture.
Fold in broccoli, cheese and onion.
Spoon into baking dish, spreading evenly.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Cut and serve.
Freezes well.

title: kahlua
directions: Combine water, coffee and sugar and boil 1 hour, then cool. Add vodka and vanilla, then bottle.

title: super shrimp dip
directions: Use fresh or frozen shrimp (not canned) for this recipe.
Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve with chips or vegetable sticks.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Clean and slice fruit; set aside.
Cut cookie dough into circles and press out to form a crust in pizza pan.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes (according to package).

title: beef burgundy
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook uncovered 1 1/2 hours at 350°. Serve over noodles or rice.

title: pumpkin pie crunch
directions: Whip together all ingredients except the cake mix, pecans and butter.
Pour in greased glass or metal pan.
Sprinkle dry cake mix, nuts and butter over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: strawberry jam cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar slowly, creaming well.
Add egg yolks and jam.
Beat well.
Add gradually the flour and spices (which have been sifted together).
Stir in milk and soda, then fold in beaten egg whites.

title: tartar sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Chill for at least an hour before serving.
Can be made ahead 2 or 3 days if stored in airtight container and refrigerated.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix egg yolks and milk. In another bowl, mix brown sugar, salt and flour until mixed good. Then add to liquid mixture and butter. Cook until thick, stirring all the time cooking and add vanilla. Pour in baked pie crust.

title: easy italian potato bake
directions: Cook meat and onions until brown; drain and stir in tomato sauce.
Spoon in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese and arrange French fries over top of casserole.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes until done.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach as per directions on box and drain well.
Combine all ingredients and roll into balls size of walnuts.
Freeze. Keep frozen until ready to serve.
When ready to serve, heat 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until center is done.
Enjoy.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas to make 1 cup.
Cream shortening with light brown sugar.
Add well-beaten eggs and the mashed bananas.
Sift flour with salt and soda.
Add to the creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in chopped walnuts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Have all cheeses at room temperature.

title: spiced apple ring
directions: Spread apple pie filling on bottom of a round microwave Bundt cake pan.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon.

title: unbelievable lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet until crumbled.
Drain.
Add to spaghetti sauce in bowl.

title: apple slices
directions: Sprinkle on top of apples.
Roll out remaining dough.
Dot the apples with butter, then top with remaining dough.
Cut slits in dough.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Completely cool.
Frost.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix margarine, Crisco, sugar and milk.
Add 1 egg at a time; mix well after each egg.
After flour, baking powder and flavoring, mix well.
Pour into floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour; if not done, cook longer.
Put into cold oven.

title: broccoli and cheese pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly.
Mix broccoli, cheese and onion in a plate.

title: lime supreme salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-Os in boiling water.
Let cool until partially set.
Fold in whipped evaporated milk, cottage cheese, pineapple, pecans and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Refrigerate until set.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese as directed.
Brown hamburger, then add Ragu and let it simmer.
Combine macaroni and cheese with hamburger mixture in a casserole dish; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese and cover with pepperoni.
Place in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: smoked fish dip
directions: Mix together.
Chill and serve with assorted crackers.
Yields 2 cups.

title: strawberry jam
directions: Mix strawberries and sugar thoroughly.
Set aside 10 minutes. Stir Sure-Jell with water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir mixtures together until sugar is completely dissolved.
Pour into plastic containers; cover.
Let stand at room temperature for 1 day.
Jam is then ready to use.
Store in freezer or refrigerator.
Thaw in refrigerator.
Yields 8 (1 cup) containers.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Slice, dice or shred any or all veggies.
Place in Teflon pan or wok with margarine.
Stir and fry constantly until tender. Season to taste.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 375°.
Mix all ingredients; cook 70 minutes for two deep pie shells.
Cook 45 to 50 minutes for smaller ones.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in salted water.
Bone and save the broth for the dumplings.
Mix the Pet milk with enough self-rising flour to form a dough stiff enough to roll.
Roll out and cut in strips.
Drop the dumplings into the boiling broth saved from cooking the chicken.
Cover and cook about 20 minutes.
Do not lift the lid of pot while dumplings are cooking.
Return chicken to pot and heat thoroughly.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage, drain and place in 3-quart casserole.
Saute celery, onion and pepper in drippings. Add to the sausage.
Add rice. Blend soup with water. Stir until blended.
Add to sausage. Mix along with undrained mushrooms and almonds.
Mix well. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove cover, stir and sprinkle with additional sliced almonds. Bake 2 minutes more until toasted on top. Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: peanut clusters
directions: Melt almond bark, chocolate and chocolate chips in crock-pot on high temperature.
Unplug pot and stir in peanuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate together. Add sugar, eggs, flour, salt and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Keep in tightly covered tin.

title: walnut chicken salad
directions: Combine the chicken, walnuts, raisins, celery, and apple. Toss to mix.
Combine the dill and mayonnaise and mix well.
Stir just enough of this dill mayonnaise into the salad to coat the mixture.
Just before serving, spoon onto curly leaf lettuce. Serve with assorted crackers or melba toast.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: "monday night dish"
directions: Brown meat, onion and green pepper.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Pour in casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: lazy crock pot recipe(cubed steak 'n' gravy)
directions: Put all the above in pot, rinse can of mushroom soup and add about 1 can of water in all.
Cook all day (about 8 hours on high).
Serve steak 'n' gravy over rice.

title: lang's salad dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in a 1 quart jar and shake well.

title: french toast
directions: Spray skillet or griddle with nonstick cooking spray; heat utensil until hot.
Combine egg product, milk, cinnamon and vanilla; beat well.
Dip bread into mixture to coat each side. Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side until golden brown.
Serve with powdered sugar or lite syrup.

title: taco stir-fry
directions: Heat oil.
Add beef and onion; stir-fry over high heat until beef is no longer pink and onion softens.
Drain excess fat.
Stir in chili powder, corn, tomatoes, sugar, oregano, salt and pepper. Bring to boil.
Lower heat; cover and simmer about 10 minutes. Stir in cheese and chips; cook, stirring, until cheese is partially melted.
Spoon over shredded lettuce.
Garnish with avocado.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix all and refrigerate. Makes 2 cups and can be doubled.

title: pepper steak and rice
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and peppers in large skillet or wok with olive oil and Lawry's seasoning salt.
Prepare rice in separate pot as instructed on box.
Prepare steak.
Trim fat off tender chuckeye steak and cut in tiny slices.
Fry meat with butter or oil and add garlic for tenderness.
Mix steak with vegetables and add curry powder.
Stir well on low heat (simmer).
Add rice, stir.
Add soy sauce when served if desired.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain. Combine sausage with rice, soup and onion in large casserole. Bake covered for 45 minutes at 400°. Stir before serving.

title: "po-fokes" icing
directions: Cook flour and water until thickened.
Cool.
Beat sugar, shortening and vanilla until creamy.
Add cooled flour-water mixture.
Beat until fluffy and spread on cake.

title: vinegret
directions: Boil all vegetables except green peas. Let them cool down and then peel. Chop beets, potatoes, cucumbers and carrots. Add green peas, if you want. Season with vegetable oil or mayonnaise. Add salt to taste.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples and water in a 6 x 10-inch baking pan.
Sift flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt into a bowl.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over apple slices.
Bake in a moderate oven at about 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Pour water into 2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap. Microwave on High for 3 to 5 minutes until boiling.
Stir in noodles.
Re-cover and cook on Defrost for 11 to 12 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Drain and stir in remaining ingredients, except potato chips. Re-cover.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Heat in casserole dish in 350° oven until hot.
Put in fondue dish to keep warm; or serve in crock-pot on "low" setting.

title: six week bran muffins
directions: Mix boiling water and soda together and let cool.
Cream the shortening, eggs and sugar together in a very large bowl. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Keep in tightly sealed container in refrigerator; do not stir after first mixing.
Spoon out as needed.
Fill greased muffin tin 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Will keep 6 weeks in refrigerator.
Freezes great.

title: chocolate pan cake
directions: Bake 40 to
45	minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: chocolate mints
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper and set aside. In small bowl, beat together eggs and mint extract.
Set aside.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, peanut butter and oats.
Press into a greased pan; cool and cut into squares or drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.

title: cream soup powder
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate in a tightly covered container. To use, combine 1/3 cup mix and 1 1/4 cups water in a saucepan. Cook while stirring until thickened.
This equals one 10-ounce can of soup.
Add 1/4 cup chopped fresh mushrooms for mock "Cream of Mushroom."

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Use deep bowl.
Mix all ingredients.
Micro on High 6 1/2 minutes, 10 on low wattage, 10 minutes on Low.
Take out and stir in 1 teaspoon vanilla and 1 teaspoon butter.
Micro 3 more minutes, 5 on low wattage.
Add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Stir fast and spread on buttered pan.

title: elephant ears
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and shortening.
Heat until shortening melts.
But don't boil.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast and stir until dissolved.
Stir in flour 2 cups at a time, beating until smooth.
Put dough into a greased bowl.
Cover with a damp cloth and let rise until double in size of golf balls.

title: oriental chicken salad
directions: Mix the first 7 ingredients together. Add dressing and serve.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Chop onions fine.
Cook in the margarine until tender, but not brown.
Add bread crumbs, broth, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning.
Mix well.
(If not moist enough, add more broth.) Makes enough stuffing for a 12 to 15 pound turkey or may be baked in well-greased baking pan.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix butter, shortening, sugar, and eggs thoroughly. Blend flour, cream of tartar, soda, and salt. Stir into butter mixture. Shape into 1 inch balls. Roll into mixture of sugar and cinnamon. Place on an ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350 degrees for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Fold together Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Sprinkle over and fold in orange Jell-O and pineapple Jell-O.
Drain and fold in pineapple and mandarin oranges.
Mix well.
Garnish with red cherries and refrigerate.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter to consistency of mayonnaise; add sugar, gradually while continuing to cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Mix and sift the flour, salt, baking powder and soda. Add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.

title: sour cream-noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles until almost done.
Rinse and drain.
Brown steak in butter.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
In a large mixing bowl combine meat, sour cream, cheese and noodles; stir.
Pour into casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken marbella(crowd pleaser)
directions: In a large bowl, combine chicken, garlic, oregano, pepper, salt, vinegar, olive oil, prunes, olives, capers, juice and bay leaves. Cover and marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: sugarless cookies
directions: In large bowl, beat egg until light and fluffy.
Add oleo and sweetener.
Add dry ingredients, which have been mixed together. Mix well.
Add chopped apples or mashed banana.
Fold in raisins or nuts and All-Bran or oats.
Drop small teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.

title: coconut bonbons
directions: Heat syrup in a double boiler with the coconut oil.
Add coconut and form into balls. Refrigerate overnight.
Dip balls in melted chocolate.

title: peanut butter bar
directions: Mix graham cracker
crumbs, 1 cup peanut butter, margarine and
vanilla
together.
Then add powdered sugar and mix well. Pat into a jelly roll pan.
In saucepan, over low heat, mix semi-sweet chocolate and peanut butter.
When melted, pour over peanut butter mixture and cool.
This can be refrigerated or frozen.
But, do not stack!

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt, then add cream.
Beat well.
Add butter and vanilla and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° for about 30 minutes or until set.

title: key lime pie
directions: Mix the sweetened condensed milk with the limeade. Add the Cool Whip and food coloring. Stir until completely blended and the color is as you'd like, then pour into pie crust and chill for at least an hour before serving.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix bread, sugar, eggs, pineapple, and melted butter.
Add milk to moisten.
Pour into lightly buttered baking dish.
Bake 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bunelus
directions: Cut tortillas up in fourths; deep fat fry.
Dunk in cinnamon and sugar.
Let cool and they get crispy.

title: potato soup
directions: Bake potatoes, cool and cut into 1/2-inch cubes, leaving skins on.
Melt butter; add flour and stir until smooth.
Cook for 1 minute; add milk and keep stirring until thick and bubbly.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, onions, bacon, chicken base and cheese; cook until thoroughly heated.
Add sour cream.

title: stuffed cherry tomatoes with shrimp
directions: In a medium size heavy saucepan, bring 2 cups unsalted water to a boil over moderately high heat.
Add the shrimp and cook, uncovered, for 3 minutes or until they turn pink.
Drain and cool.
Whirl the shrimp in a food processor for 1 minute. Transfer to a small bowl; mix in the parsley, chives, lemon juice, olive oil and pepper.
Cover and chill in the refrigerator.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Boil squash in salt water until very tender and cool. Beat eggs until thick.
Add sour cream and flour. Add cheese, squash and bacon.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish or large iron skillet.
Melt butter and combine bread crumbs with it. Sprinkle over top of squash. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cherry or blueberry struzzle
directions: Mix together and drizzle over cake.
Tastes better when set for a day.
Freezes well.

title: chili cheese enchiladas
directions: Spread chili, cheese and onion in tortillas and roll up. Pour remaining chili over top and sprinkle with cheese.

title: my barrister's favorite carrot cake
directions: In large bowl, combine oil, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
In separate bowl, sift flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to oil-sugar-eggs-vanilla mixture and blend well. Stir in coconut, carrots, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into greased/floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes until center of cake is firm to the touch.
Cool in pan. Frost with cream cheese frosting.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: Bake sauerkraut and pork for 3 hours.
Remove from oven, mince pork and mix with sauerkraut.
Mash and whip potatoes.
Place sauerkraut and pork in casserole.
Top with mashed potatoes; dot with butter and return to oven until butter is melted and potatoes brown slightly.
Heat oven to 375°.
Serves 6.

title: hot creamed crab
directions: Beat cheese until smooth in small bowl with electric mixer. Add mayonnaise, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, flour and cayenne pepper.
Beat again until smooth; fold in crab meat, almonds and salt.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Should be served with unsalted crackers or Melba toast.
But can use any crackers if these are not available.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Boil chicken breasts in 3 qt. water for 30 minutes.
Remove and reserve stock.
Shred chicken breasts.

title: turkey-cheese hero
directions: Slice bread lengthwise in half.
On the bottom half, spread the mayonnaise.
Layer lettuce, cheese, turkey, stuffing, relish and onion.

Cover with top half of bread and cut into 4 serving pieces. Place cheese slices last, then place the sandwich open-faced in a preheated 375° oven for 5 to 10 minutes or until cheese is melted and sandwich is heated through.
Top with other half of the bread. Makes 4 servings.

title: stir-fry "roy"
directions: In wok or large frying pan, brown chicken and sausage in olive oil.
Add the carrots and onions.
Saute until wilted.
Add the 5 spice powder.
Mix until meat and vegetables are coated.
Add the tomato sauce.
Meanwhile, cook the noodles and add sprinkles of parsley.
Add rest of ingredients on top of noodles to serve.

title: slo-cooked chili
directions: Preheat pot on stove over medium heat.
Add ground turkey and brown.
Remove from heat and place pot on base.
Add onion, green pepper, garlic, tomatoes, kidney beans, salt, chili powder and pepper.
Stir to combine.
Cover and simmer at low heat 7 to 10 hours.
About 1 hour before serving, add corn.
Top with grated cheese and/or sour cream.

title: mock ravioli
directions: Prepare macaroni (white).
Prepare spinach.
Drain spinach (green).
Add eggs, cheese and parsley.
Cook hamburger, drain. Add onion, garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce (red) and Italian herbs.
Cook until onion is done.
Put layer number 1 in bottom of casserole.
Then add layer number 2 and then layer number 3.
Bake in 350° oven until done, about 1 hour.

title: carrot-raisin muffins
directions: Stir together flours, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center; set aside. Stir together eggs, undrained pineapple, carrot, raisins, corn syrup and vanilla in a small mixing bowl; add all at once to flour mixture.
Stir just until moistened.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender; drain thoroughly.
In a large skillet, saute onion in 5 tablespoons of margarine until tender.
Add soup and mix well.
Add cheese.
Heat and stir until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cabbage, salt and pepper.

title: italian broiled chicken
directions: Melt margarine in frying pan and add lemon juice and salad mix.
Dip chicken in this mixture and place, skin side up, on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 8 minutes per side.
Change oven setting to 350° and pour remaining butter mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: porcupines
directions: Mix all ingredients together except soup.
Roll into small balls and place in large boiler.
Pour soup over meat balls and add 1 can water.
Boil slowly for 1 hour.

title: seven can casserole
directions: Heat cream of mushroom soup, 1/3 can of milk and Velveta cheese.
When cheese is melted, pour over the above vegetables in a large casserole.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Boil cut up squash until tender.
Drain and mix with all ingredients, using only 1/2 of the butter.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour over top and sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about an hour.
Serves 8 or 10.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, butter, vinegar and vanilla. Beat. Add
raisins,
coconut
and
pecans.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Add vanilla, then pineapple.
Spray 10-inch tube pan with Baker's Joy.
Pour batter in pan.
Place in cold oven and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Cream butter, vanilla, milk, sugar and pecans.
Put on a platter by spoonful.
Set in refrigerator to get cold.
Melt chocolate and paraffin in top of a double boiler.
Using a toothpick, dip cream candy in chocolate.
Then chill candy until hardened.
Serve.

title: taco salad
directions: Crush enough of the chips to cover the bottom of a baking pan (1/2 or more of the bag).
Sprinkle the cooked hamburger over the chips.
Spread the beans over the hamburger.
Spread the sour cream over the beans.
Pour the salsa over the sour cream.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take the dish out of the oven.
Turn the oven off. Sprinkle cheese over the top of the hot mixture and return the dish to the oven until the cheese melts.
