Garnish the top of the mixture with fresh shredded lettuce and cubed tomatoes.

title: elvira's bow wow biscuits
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, dry milk, salt, garlic powder and sugar.
Cut in margarine or meat drippings until mixed.
Add beaten egg, broth and any other favorite ingredients.
Add water as needed to form mixture into a ball.
Pat or roll dough into 1/2-inch thickness on wax paper.
Cut with dog biscuit cutter.
Cover cookie sheet with foil and oil foil.
Place biscuits on sheet and bake at 350 for 25-30 minutes or until brown at edges.

title: josie's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar; add milk, butter, vanilla and slightly beaten eggs.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: ginger cookies(over 100 years old)
directions: Mix ingredients together; let stand 1/2 hour in refrigerator. Roll
out on floured board.
Cut out shapes.
Bake at 350°	for 12 minutes.
Cool on pan a few minutes before removing.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In ovenproof casserole dish, spray sides with nonstick spray. Place 4 pats of oleo on bottom of dish.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse and pat mushrooms dry. Set aside. Mix together cream cheese, green onions and mayo. Remove stems from mushrooms and fill mushrooms caps with cream cheese mixture using a small spoon or a decorating bag. Place mushroom caps on baking sheet and bake 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Make
syrup
of sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add butter or oleo.
Pare apples and cut in 1/8.
Sift flour, salt and baking
powder.
Cut
in shortening; add milk all at once and stir until moistened.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in 6-inch squares. Arrange apples in squares.	Sprinkle sugar, cinnamon and
nutmeg. Dot with butter.
Fold corners to center.
Pinch edges
together and place 1 inch apart in greased baking dish. Pour
syrup	over. Bake
in
moderate oven (375°) 35 minutes. Serve hot with cream.

title: no shell coconut pie
directions: Beat together flour, sugar, eggs and milk in bowl.
Add coconut and
vanilla;
pour
into
pie pan.
Bake in 350° oven about 45 minutes or until coconut is golden brown.	Serve warm or cold, plain or with whipped cream.

title: chocolate chip crispies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and brown sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla. Sift and add plain flour, salt and soda.
Mix in oatmeal, Rice Krispies, pecans and chocolate chips.
Lightly grease a cookie sheet.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: cucumber dill dip
directions: In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until soft and smooth.
Stir in mayo, cucumbers, onions, lemon juice, dill and hot pepper sauce.
Cover.
Chill.
Serve with fresh veggies, crackers or chips.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pepper pasta
directions: Heat butter and oil in a medium saucepan; add garlic, lemon rind and crushed red pepper.

Cook over low heat 2 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add chicken broth and lemon juice. Simmer over medium heat until reduced to about 1 1/4 cups (about 25 minutes). Add salt and pepper. Cook fettuccine in a large Dutch oven according to package directions; drain.
Return fettuccine to Dutch oven; add red pepper strips and broth mixture. Cook over low heat 1 minute or until thoroughly heated, tossing gently.
Serve immediately or if desired, spoon into a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover and chill. Remove from refrigerator and let stand at room temperature 1 hour.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs; sift sugar, baking powder, salt and flour together. Add corn.
Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Pour into corn mixture.
Bake for one hour at 350°.

title: longhorn cheesecake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, oil, buttermilk and vanilla; set aside.
Sift flour, soda and cinnamon.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Add pineapple, cheese and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown meat, onion and bell pepper.
Add tomatoes, rice and seasonings.
Mix well.
Cook for 1 hour.
Cover.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown beef on top of stove over medium heat.
When meat is brown, pour grease off and rinse with hot water.
Add soup, onion bits, salt and pepper.
Top with Tater Tots and bake in oven at 350° for about 30 minutes.
When Tater Tots are brown, add cheese on top and bake until cheese is melted.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook 1 cup Minute rice with onion flakes. Add soups to cooked rice and mix well. Microwave broccoli florets according to directions on box. When cool, cut up into smaller pieces (do not use the stalk part) and add to rice mixture. Microwave Cheez Whiz for about a minute and add with melted margarine to rice mixture. Mix well and microwave in a covered dish for 10 minutes.

title: chew bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with pork chops
directions: Brown chops on one side in hot fat.
Place half of potatoes in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese slices.
Add remaining potatoes.
Place pork chops, browned side up, on potatoes. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cook onions in drippings until tender.
Add soup and milk.
Heat and pour over pork chops.
Cover with foil on a baking sheet and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour. Remove cover and continue baking for 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Stir the ingredients in order given.
Pour into pans (grease and flour well).

title: chicken divan
directions: Place cooked broccoli in a long glass baking dish which has been sprayed with Pam.
Layer chicken over broccoli.

title: saucy pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet in hot shortening.
Season with salt and pepper; top with onion slices.
Combine soup, catsup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chops.
Cover skillet and simmer for 40 to 60 minutes.
Remove chops to warm platter and spoon sauce over.

title: baked potato dish
directions: Mix together sour cream, mushroom soup, potato soup, celery soup, onion salt and pepper.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: breaded dijon pork chops
directions: In a bowl, combine crackers, thyme, pepper and sage. Spread mustard on both sides of pork chops. Coat with crumb mixture. In a skillet, cook pork chops in oil on medium-high heat, for 4 to 5 minutes on each side or until brown and juices run clear. Serves 4.

title: french onion soup
directions: In a 3-quart soup pot on the stove top, melt butter and add onions, stirring constantly. Cook for 15 to 20 minutes or until soft. When onions are soft, add mushrooms and cook 2 more minutes. Sprinkle flour over and stir well. Add 2 cups of beef broth. Continue stirring until the mixture is thickened. Add remaining broth and stir in salt, pepper and brandy. Bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for 45 minutes. Add Kitchen Bouquet and stir well. Taste for seasoning and correct if necessary. Makes 6 (1 1/3 cup) servings; 3 carbs, 145 calories (per serving).

title: giant chocolate chip cookie
directions: In large bowl, cream margarine and sugars until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla; blend well.
Add chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread dough evenly in a greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool and cut into about 16 wedges.

title: delicious creamed corn
directions: While heating corn, combine all other ingredients.
Add to corn and cook slowly until it thickens.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except coconut.
Pour in blender for 10 seconds.
Add the flaked coconut.
Pour into a 9-inch buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
It makes its own crust.

title: rhubarb fruit compote - diet
directions: Cook rhubarb slowly in small amount of water until almost done.
Add strawberries and finish cooking.
Add pineapple.
Cool and add Equal.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Make liquid mixture by combining soups and Ro-Tel.
Saute onion in butter until tender and mix into liquid mixture.
Line bottom of casserole dish with tortillas, then layer in chicken pieces.
Pour mixture over layers.
Continue layering until dish is full or you run out.
Put black olives on top.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven and add grated cheese on top.

title: strawberry mold
directions: In large bowl, dissolve Jell-O in the water; gently add drained pineapple and frozen strawberries.
Pour half of mixture in mold and let set in refrigerator about 1 hour.
Let the other half stand at room temperature.
Gently spoon sour cream on the set Jell-O and gently spoon remaining Jell-O mixture into mold; return to refrigerator until firmly set.
Makes 1 large mold.
For a smaller mold, cut recipe in half.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed; drain.
Make a sauce of soup, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, margarine and cheese.
Pour broccoli in casserole; pour sauce on top and cover with cracker crumbs.
(Use Ritz or similar type crackers.) Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine soups, broth, tomatoes and onion until smooth.
Place a layer of chicken in casserole, then a layer of Tostitos, cheese and sauce.
Repeat, ending with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Can be made with hamburger instead of chicken.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef and onion and drain. Add tomato paste, mushroom and chicken soup, green peppers, taco sauce and cooked rice and simmer a few minutes. It's ready to serve over chips and cheese on top.

title: baked chicken salad(must do ahead)
directions: *I use one or the other, chips or almonds.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Cream the cream cheese; add sour cream, onion and picante sauce. Spread on flour tortillas. Roll up jelly roll fashion. Chill well. Slice into 1 inch slices. Arrange on platter around a small bowl of picante sauce.

title: kolacky
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in vanilla. Combine flour and salt.
Add in fourths to butter mixture, blending well after each addition.
Chill dough until easy to handle.
Roll dough to 3/8-inch thickness on confectioners sugar and flour.
Cut 2-inch circles or shapes.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Make a "thumbprint" about 1/4-inch deep in each cookie. Fill with jam.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until delicately browned on edges.
After cooled, sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: blonde brownies(nate emery's favorite)
directions: Melt shortening in saucepan. Remove from heat and add sugar. Mix well and cool slightly before adding eggs and vanilla. Blend well and add flour mixture, a little at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add chips and nuts.
Stir in.
Spread batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool in pan and cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: kids cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to mixture.
Roll out on floured board, cut and bake for 8 minutes at 375°.

title: miniature ham loaves
directions: Combine eggs, milk and cracker crumbs.
Mix well.
Add ham and sausage.
Shape 1/2 cupfuls into into individual loaves. Place in greased 9 x 13 baking dish.
Combine soup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over loaves.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour, basting after 30 minutes.
Serves 12 to 14.

title: sad cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes. Cake is done when it falls.

title: easy chili
directions: Brown hamburger in big pot with onion and green pepper.
Add canned tomatoes and paste, salt, chili powder and beans.
Mix together and then add 6 cans water.
Cook over medium heat for 1/2 hour.

title: biscuits
directions: Mix well the first 3 ingredients.
Roll out on floured surface to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits.
Pour melted 1/2 stick oleo in baking pan and place biscuits.
Bake at 400° to 425° until done.

title: potato soup
directions: Cook potatoes, celery and onions in the 3 cups water until tender.
Drain - save water - blend in blender - return to pot with water.
Add milk, bouillon and butter.
Mix sour cream with flour and add to soup mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bouillon cubes - dissolve.
Stir in salt and pepper. (I cook a few extra finely diced potatoes to add to the blended soup to give it extra texture.)
Serve topped with crumbled bacon, sliced green onion and finely shredded cheese.

title: chinese rice and pea salad
directions: Toss all together with dressing.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Divide sausage meat into 6 portions.
Wrap around hard-boiled eggs; cover completely.
Beat remaining raw egg with salt.
Coat eggs with beaten egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.
Turn often to retain round shape.

title: fudge frosting
directions: Let the first 4 ingredients come to a boil.
Add the sugar; let boil 1 minute.
(If you boil it less time, it makes great hot fudge sauce for ice cream.)

title: lemon pound cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream butter, shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.

title: shoney strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and cornstarch.
Stir over medium heat until bubbly. Sprinkle jello powder and sugar into mixture.
Stir well.
Cool. Add berries and put into baked pie shell.
Top with whipped cream.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown beef and onion in large saucepan, drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for at least 15 minutes.
Top with crushed tortilla chips, cheese and sour cream.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Place all ingredients in blender; blend briefly.
Texture should be lumpy.
Bake at 350° in a greased casserole for about 45 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling salted water.
Drain.
In saucepan, cook carrot and onion in 4 tablespoons oleo until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups bread crumbs, the soup and sour cream.
Gently stir in zucchini.
Turn into casserole.
Melt remaining oleo to remaining bread crumbs.
Toss and top casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable bake
directions: Soak cauliflower and broccoli according to directions. Cut up large pieces. Combine creamed corn, whole corn, cheese and soup. Fold in cooked vegetables and mushrooms.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.
Serves 20.

title: cheddar ha' pennies
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into rolls about one-inch in diameter.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
When ready to bake, slice crosswise 1/8-inch thick.
Bake in moderate oven, 375°, about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes 6 1/2 dozen.

title: great shower or party punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix oil, molasses, sugar and egg.
Combine with dry ingredients.
Chill dough for 2 hours.
Form into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Bake 6 to 8 minutes at 350°.

title: harvest bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add pumpkin (yams) and orange juice.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° until done.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Combine sugar, oleo, Karo syrup and peanuts in saucepan. Bring to a boil; boil 1 minute.
Remove from fire and add soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour over popped corn.
Spread in roasting pan and bake 1 hour at 200°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix applesauce, shortening and sugar.
Add flour, soda and spices.
Mix all together.
Flour raisins and nuts so they won't sink during baking.
Mix into the batter.
Bake at 350° in floured and greased loaf pan until it tests done.

title: braunschweiger loaf
directions: Saute onion and mushrooms in melted butter until brown; cool and mix with braunschweiger and cream cheese until well blended. Pack into 9 x 3 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Chill and unmold.
Serve with crackers, chips or toasted thin sliced rye bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie shell; refrigerate until ready to fill.

title: sunshine carrot salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Stir in sour cream; serve on lettuce leaves.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: hot tomato salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Fill into hot jars.
Cover with lids and process in water bath for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: vegetable pizza square
directions: In a large cookie sheet, lay out rolls and press seams together.
Bake according to directions on tube or until light brown.
Cool.

title: company's a comin pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy, add cream of tartar and beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually.
Fold into egg white mixture soda crackers (not too small pieces).
Add nuts (finely cut) and vanilla. Put into buttered pie pan and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool.
Whip the whipping cream and add pineapple-apricot preserves and spread on top.
Sprinkle with Angel Flake coconut. Chill.
Serves 6 to 8.
"Very rich."

title: oven fried potato slices
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Preheat oven to 425°.
Place butter in shallow baking pan. Add potatoes.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Toss until potatoes are thoroughly coated. Spread into single layer.
Bake 20 minutes. Turn with spatula. Continue baking until potatoes are tender, crusty and golden brown, about 15 more minutes.

title: codfish in the oven
directions: You first boil the codfish with the potatoes.
You cook the eggs separately.
You fry the onion in olive oil.
In an appropriate container (can go in the oven), you put one layer of potatoes, then one of codfish, one of the eggs, parsley and the onion.
You repeat this and then on top, put the oil.
You put it in the oven at 300° and then at 250° for a cooking time of 15 minutes.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: Heat all ingredients to boiling; reduce heat. Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Mix with mixer.
Pour into 4 small loaf pans.
Bake at 30 to 35 minutes or until done at 350°.
Remove from oven.
Punch holes in top of bread and pour glaze over loaves while still hot in pans.

title: meteracal cake
directions: Melt oleo, water and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Pour over dry ingredients, then add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Put in cookie sheet with a lip around it, greased.
Bake at 350° about 15 to 20 minutes, checking to see when done.
Remove from oven and ice.

title: frito pie
directions: Heat can of chili without beans.
Add large bag of Fritos and onion.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large dutch oven.
Heat 20 minutes on medium heat.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Drain corn.
Saute onion in small amount Wesson oil, add ground beef and cook until no longer red.
Then add all other ingredients and mix well.
Put can of biscuits on top and bake about 20 minutes, or until brown.

title: avocado dip
directions: Peel and slice avocado.
Chop small onion.
Mix all ingredients in a blender, adding salt, garlic salt and paprika to taste.
Add mayonnaise until a dippable consistency.
Serve with wheat crackers, tortilla chips or as a topping on your favorite Mexican recipe.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and saute onion.
Add soup and cheese to onion. After mixture melts, add broccoli.
Add cooked rice.
Mix and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: golden carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, combine mincemeat, carrots, nuts and rind; toss with 1/2 cup of flour.
Set aside. In a large mixer bowl, combine sugar and oil; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Stir together remaining 1 1/2 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; gradually add to batter, beating until smooth.
Stir in mincemeat mixture.
Turn into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt or tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool completely.
Drizzle with Orange Glaze.

title: sausage skillet supper
directions: Combine the sausage, rice, soup, water and butter in a large skillet on medium heat.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Stir in peas and mushrooms.
Simmer, covered, for approximately 20 minutes, or until rice is cooked.
Sprinkle with cheese; simmer, covered, until the cheese is melted.
Yields 4 servings.

title: glazed carrots(glaserte gulerotter)
directions: Scrape and trim carrots; cut in large pieces.
Place in saucepan and pour boiling water over, barely covering the carrots. Add salt, butter and sugar.
Cover and boil until carrots are nearly done.
Remove lid and continue boiling until most of the liquid has evaporated.
Shake the pan so that the carrots are turned and glazed all over.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley. Serves 6.

title: rice casserole
directions: Put all above ingredients in a small casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli. Chop and set aside.
Melt butter in large heavy pan. Add mushrooms and onions.
Saute until tender.
Add flour. Stir until bubbly. Gradually add 1 1/2 cups milk, stirring constantly. Add cheese. Stir until smooth.
Add remaining milk. Add broccoli and heat thoroughly.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in flour. Cook until flour is lightly browned.
Add water, bouillon and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve bouillon.
Simmer, covered, for 15 minutes.
Ladle into ovenproof bowls.
Top with French bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Broil until cheese is light brown.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: breakfast casserole ii
directions: Brown, drain and crumble sausage.
Layer bread then sausage, cheese in 9 X 13 dish.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 325 for 1 hour or until set.

title: three ingredient chocolate pie
directions: Slowly melt chocolate bars in microwave.
Do not scorch. Melt slowly.
After the chocolate has cooled for about 15 minutes, fold in Cool Whip.
The mixture will be a light milk chocolate. Pour this into the graham cracker crust.
Wait about 2-3 hours for it to set up and it is ready to eat.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in an oblong casserole dish for 20 minutes at 350°.
Can top with bread crumbs before baking, if desired.

title: mini chip brownies
directions: Cream together butter and brown sugar until light and fluffy (in a large bowl).
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into bars.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into mixing bowl. Add raisins and nuts. Combine egg, vanilla and shortening. Dissolve soda in pineapple and add to flour mixture. Stir until well blended. Pour into greased loaf pan (8 x 4 x 4-inch). Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 1 hour. Test with toothpick for doneness. Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat the pear juice and pour over the Jell-O.
Use no water. While hot, pour into cream cheese which has been mashed with 2 tablespoons milk.
When cool and thick, add mashed pears and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Chill.

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Form balls.
Bake at 300 degrees for 15 minutes.
These can be quick frozen on a cookie sheet to bake later.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. With a wooden spoon, stir until soft dough forms. Beat vigorously 30 seconds. Drop by spoonful onto ungreased pan. Bake 8 to 10 minutes.

title: roasted red potatoes(instead of baked idahos)
directions: Cover bottom of flat baking dish with olive oil.
Sprinkle garlic chips (or your choice of other forms of garlic) into the oil.
Place potatoes, cut side down, in oil and roast for 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.

title: best carrot cake ever
directions: Combine first five ingredients; beat well.
Combine flour, soda, salt and cinnamon; add to sugar mixture, stirring well.
Add carrots, walnuts, pineapple and coconut; stir well.

title: beef tips and noodles
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch squares.
Brown in skillet.
Mix gravy mix and 2 cups water.
Bring to boil, stirring constantly.
Stir in rest of ingredients except noodles.
Add sauce and meat to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cook noodles as package states.
Pour meat and sauce over noodles.
Meat and sauce can be done in crock-pot.

title: rosy strawberry pie with butter crumb crust
directions: Combine butter and sugar with pastry blender.
Add flour and blend until just combined.
Pour into 9-inch pie pan and press crumbs up sides of pan and across bottom.
Bake 15 minutes in a 375° preheated oven.

title: frosted cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple and cranberries and reserve the liquid.
Add enough water to make 2 cups.
Bring to a boil and dissolve jello. Chill until partially set.

title: spanish gazpacho soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill thoroughly, at least 4 hours.

title: frozen cranberry layer salad
directions: Beat cranberry sauce with rotary beater until saucy.
Combine with lemon juice.
Spread in the bottom of a mold or small individual molds.
Cover cranberry layer with topping.

title: crab dip helen
directions: Remove shells from crabmeat.
Mix together sour cream, mayonnaise, onion, pickle relish and rum.
Add to crabmeat and mix thoroughly, but gently, with a fork.
Chill thoroughly.
Serve with crackers.
Makes about 4 cups of dip.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients well in blender.
Makes approximately one quart.
Best if let set 2 hours or more.
Refrigerate.

title: chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Grease a pan with butter; layer on bottom of pan coconut and nuts.
Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Heat butter, cream cheese and sugar until warm.
Pour over cake.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a shallow bowl, blend together the breadcrumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt and pepper.
In a small saucepan, heat butter and garlic over low heat until butter melts.
Remove from heat.
Brush chicken pieces with garlic butter, then roll in breadcrumb mixture to coat.
Place chicken, skin side up, on a large foil-lined baking sheet.
Mix together any remaining crumb mixture and butter.
Sprinkle over chicken. Bake 1 hour.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Heat oil.
Add onions; saute for 3 minutes.
Add water and bouillon cubes.
Heat to boiling.
Add noodles and salt.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in broccoli and garlic; cook 4 minutes.
Add milk, cheese and pepper, cooking over low heat until cheese melts.
Do not boil after adding milk, or it will clabber.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain grease.
Mix with salsa. In a 2-quart microwaveproof dish, spread refried beans; add beef mixture on the top.
Cover loosely with plastic wrap and cook for 5 minutes on High.
Sprinkle cheese on top and microwave on High for 1 minute or until cheese melts.
Spread sour cream on top. Top with onions and tomatoes. Serve with tortilla chips.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: pasta with vegetables
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain and keep warm.
Heat oil in skillet; add all vegetables.
Stir and cook until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 5 minutes.
Add seasonings and
toss with cooked pasta.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Combine potatoes, carrots, celery, onion, salt, pepper and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not drain.
Make a cream sauce with margarine, flour and milk.
Add to vegetables; add corn.
Heat.
Do not boil.

title: raw vegetable pizza
directions: Spread 2 packages crescent roll dough in a jelly roll pan. Bake at 375° for 11 to 13 minutes.
Cool.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Spread over rolls.
Top with any kind of raw veggies and top with cheese.

title: microwave breakfast hot dish
directions: Microwave the sausage on high for 8 to 12 minutes or until done.
Drain sausage and mushrooms in a colander.
Place croutons in 3 quart round casserole dish.
Layer cheese over croutons, then mushrooms and last, sausage.
Beat eggs and then add milk and soup to beaten eggs.
Pour the egg mixture over the layered ingredients.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.
To cook, place a glass (bottom side down) in the center of the round casserole dish.
Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on 70% power for 20 to 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Parsley can be used as a garnish and a filling at the center of the dish.

title: spicy hot cheese dip
directions: Heat all ingredients until cheese melts.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: shirley's toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat eggs until foamy. Add flour and sugars; beat until blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into shell.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Bring to a boil and let boil until thick.
Cool 5 minutes. Pour over 1 cup strawberries already in pie shell.
This will make two pies.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.
Very Good!

title: chicken salad filling
directions: In bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Put in tart shells.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Melt margarine; cook garlic over low heat.
Stir in flour; cook 1 minute.
Slowly add milk; stir until thickened.
If it boils, remove from heat and wait a few minutes, then add cheese. (Cheese added to a liquid at boiling temperature will curdle.) Cook and stir until cheese melts and it is smooth.
Fold in crab, parsley, salt and pepper*.
Toss with fettucini.
Serve immediately.
You can also add cooked shrimp or scallops or any combination.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Make roux with oil and flour.
Cook until brown, almost black. Add shrimp.
Add water and seasoning to taste.
Simmer slowly 15 to 30 minutes.
Place over cooked rice and sprinkle with file according to taste.

title: short cake
directions: Soften butter at room temperature, add sugar and blend well. Then add eggs and milk and mix together.
Add flour last, about 1/2 cup at a time, then add vanilla and cook at 350° until done.

title: hound dog rolls
directions: Stuff each hot dog with slice of Mozzarella cheese.
Wrap half lasagna noodle around each, folding ends under.
Place in baking pan.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ann lander's meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly the ground round steak, eggs, bread crumbs, ketchup, Accent, warm water and onion soup mix.
Put into a loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon if you like that flavor.
Pour over all the tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Mix soups and broth.
Layer remainder of ingredients as listed.
Pour soup mixture on top and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Save juice.
Drain and discard juice from mandarin oranges.
Peel bananas and slice thinly.
Take large bowl.
Combine fruits, juices and bananas. Sprinkle pudding over the top and mix well.
Chill.
Add marshmallows, if desired.
If needed, add more pudding.

title: crispy chicken salad
directions: Mix all of the ingredients, except the carrots, almonds and shoestring potatoes.
Add these three items and toss immediately before serving.
So crunchy and good!

title: green bean salad(chinese style)
directions: Bring 1 quart of water to a boil and add the peanut oil.
Add green beans and let sit for 1 minute.
Drain and rinse in cold water.
Drain well.
Mix all remaining ingredients as for salad dressing.
Toss with the drained beans.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine and put in 2-quart casserole.
Spread with topping and bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: gooey butter cake or cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, 2 eggs, and butter together.
Pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and floured.

title: quick veal parmesan
directions: Cook veal patties on 1 side in frying pan lightly brushed with oil.
When brown, turn, spoon on generous coating of spaghetti sauce; top with a coating of shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Cover pan while second side browns, add sauce and cheese, heat.
Goes well with a side of spaghetti and salad or green vegetables.

title: raisin puffs
directions: Cook raisins in water until water is absorbed.
Set aside to cool.
Cream shortening, sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture with raisins and vanilla; mix well.
Shape into small balls and roll in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° (do not overbake).
Bake until puffy and remove quickly.
Wait a few minutes before removing from pan.

title: chicken divan
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and soup together.
Layer broccoli, chicken, cheese and soup mixture.
Bake, uncovered, in buttered pan at 350° for 30 minutes.
Last 5 minutes, top with canned onion rings.

title: simple apple squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together, except apples, until smooth.
Stir in apples.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured sheet cake pan.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: will's chili verde
directions: Heat the oil on medium-high and sear pork on all sides and reduce to simmer.
Cook for approximately 1 hour, adding water as needed until tender.
Add chilies, onion and cumin and simmer an additional 30 minutes.
Mix cornstarch, flour and cold water together and add to chili.
Use red chili seed to add heat to taste and simmer to preferred texture.

title: deviled cream cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve with crackers or use to stuff celery.
Makes 3/4 cup.

title: venison meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in buttered pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: cherry cream cheese pie
directions: In a bowl beat cheese until light and fluffy.
Add milk; blend thoroughly.
Stir in ReaLemon and vanilla.
Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours.
Top with cherries.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Pour warm water in large bowl; check temperature.
Should be between 105° and 115°.
Sprinkle yeast over the water, then add sugar and salt.
Stir until dissolved.
Let stand a few minutes. Add eggs, butter, potatoes and 3 cups flour.
Beat with mixer until smooth, then add 2 cups flour.
Mix with spoon until blended.
Then add the rest of the flour; mix with your hands until blended. Brush top of dough with 1 tablespoon butter.
Cover with wax paper and a towel.
Let stand in the refrigerator 2 hours.
Punch down dough with your hands.
Shape dough as desired.
Cover; let rise in warm place about 1 hour or until they double in size.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Brush tops with butter or brush tops with egg and sprinkle on seeds of your choice.
Bake 12 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook meat, onion and green pepper in skillet until meat is done.
Stir in flour, tomato paste and spices.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cheese and olives.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Prepare your favorite cornbread recipe and spread over top.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Loosen edges.
Invert and serve immediately.
Sour cream, cottage cheese or guacamole compliment nicely.

title: coconut impossible pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in a greased 9-inch pie pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Parboil peppers for 5 or so minutes.
Drain.
Brown beef with onion, salt and pepper; drain.
Remove from heat.
Add 1/2 can soup, egg, cheese and rice.
Stuff peppers with mixture, or layer with peppers in baking dish.
Mix remaining soup and water; pour over peppers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: bavarian salad
directions: Melt marshmallows in juice from pineapple and water over low heat.
Add lime jello and refrigerate until mixture is cool.
Then add other ingredients and chill until set.

title: mom's white cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth.
Add milk and cream again.
Sift flour and baking powder together and add to mixture. Add vanilla and cream again.
Beat egg whites to a peak and fold in gently.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together thoroughly. Put in greased or sprayed bread pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, cheese, mayonnaise and onion.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with bacon and olives.
Bake 1 hour at 325°, covered.

title: red cabbage
directions: Combine all ingredients; add a little water if needed.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: ham ball
directions: Let cool, then roll in nuts.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients until crumbly.
Add vinegar, egg and water.

title: chicken magnifique
directions: In bag, combine flour, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add chicken and shake.
Melt butter in skillet; brown chicken slightly.
Place in single layer in shallow baking dish; add to drippings in skillet the lemon juice, minced onion and leaf thyme. Heat 1 minute.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes; baste once.
We love this.

title: holiday delight pie
directions: Place marshmallows and milk in top of a double boiler.
Heat over hot water until marshmallows are melted.
Chill.
Meanwhile, put the cranberries through a food chopper and drain off the juice.
Fold the cranberries and the orange rind into the chilled marshmallow mixture and pour into the pie shell.
Top with whipped cream, if so desired.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine salad dressing, cream, sugar, vinegar and salt.
Dice potatoes and eggs.
Add onion and celery to salad dressing mixture.
Serve chilled.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger together with everything.
Make meatballs and fry until brown.
Put in a crock-pot with soup and soy sauce. Mix together and heat in crock-pot.
Serve over noodles.

title: skillet beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Add pork and beans, salt, pepper, chili powder, minced onions and a sprinkle of brown sugar. Stir well and serve with hamburgers or hot dogs.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Microwave potatoes.
Let cool.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Scoop out.
Melt butter in a large pot.
Add flour, stirring constantly. Gradually add milk.
Stir until thick and bubbly.
Add potatoes, salt, pepper, green onions, bacon and cheese.
Cook until heated. Stir in sour cream.
Add extra milk, if needed.
Serve with onion, bacon and cheese sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: venison-meatballs
directions: Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan with heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap. Combine all ingredients.
Press into pan.
Cut into 40 squares. Shape each square into meatball; return to pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Drain.
Makes 40 meatballs.

title: date loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk and dates in a large bowl or pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in butter and nuts.
Divide mixture in 1/2.
Place each half on a damp towel.
Shape into a 10 x 2-inch log.
Roll logs up in towel and let cool at least 30 minutes.
Unwrap and cut into slices.

title: chocolate pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cocoa and salt.
Beat egg yolks with milk. Add to sugar mixture.
Cook until thickened.
Add butter.
When cooled, add vanilla.
Pour into cooked, cooled shell, if for pie. Top with meringue.
Bake at 350°.

title: quick punch
directions: Put all ingredients into punch bowl and stir.

title: frankfurts and rice
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add flour and tomatoes.
Cook until thick.
Add ketchup and seasonings last.
Put boiled rice in bottom of baking dish.
Place split frankfurts over rice.
Pour sauce over all.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: scoodles
directions: Cook noodles or pasta according to directions on package; drain.
Add milk, a little for hot dish consistency or more for soup.
Add salt and pepper to taste and a big dollop of butter.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together; chill and serve.
Makes 75 servings.

title: post's grape-nuts bread
directions: Soak Grape-Nuts in sour milk for 20 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let stand about 10 minutes before baking.
Bake in a slow oven for 1 hour at 325°.

title: oven baked french fries(low-fat)
directions: Cut potatoes into strips. Arrange on a Teflon baking sheet, after dipping each strip into liquid Butter Buds or brushing with Butter Buds on potato pieces.
You can also try other seasonings such as garlic powder, onion powder or chili powder. Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn and bake 15 to 20 more minutes or until tender. To shorten baking time, parboil potatoes 15 minutes.

title: italian hamburger soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; drain.
Add other ingredients and cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Serve sprinkled with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, butter and milk.
Fold in bread cubes and pineapple.
Pour into greased casserole and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread refried beans in an 8 x 11-inch casserole.
Add chopped onions, hamburger seasoned with garlic salt, picante sauce and grated cheese.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool for about 5 minutes.
Spread sour cream and top with guacamole.
Serve immediately with chips.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Boil macaroni until done.
In medium casserole dish, combine ingredients, adding cooked hamburger and drained macaroni last.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Return to oven until melted.

title: grilled italian sausage kabobs
directions: Mix pizza sauce, basil and oil; reserve.
Cook sausage pieces over medium heat until partially cooked, about 10 minutes.
Drain. Alternate sausage pieces, zucchini pieces and pepper pieces on each of
6 metal skewers, leaving space between foods.
Place olive on top of each skewer.
Grill 20 to 25 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding with cold milk.
Beat 2 minutes, then blend in Eagle Brand milk and 1/2 Cool Whip.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
Ice with Cool Whip.
Makes 2 (9 x 13-inch) pans.
Very good.

title: hawaiian cookies
directions: Sift flour once, measure and sift three times with other dry ingredients.
Cream shortening, add sugar gradually.
Add beaten egg and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Drop with spoon onto slightly greased sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spice cookies
directions: Mix cake mix, oats, eggs, brown sugar, oil and milk together, then add raisins and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Makes about 6 to 7 dozen cookies.

title: creamy-onion potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour.
Stir until smooth.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until tender.
Gradually add chicken broth, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes, green onions, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to simmer.
Simmer until potatoes are done.
Add milk and heat thoroughly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix in order and bake in 3-quart casserole, uncovered, at 350° for 1 3/4 hours.

title: homemade chili
directions: In skillet, cook meat until nearly done, stirring frequently to separate.
Add remaining ingredients; cook slowly until vegetables are tender and flavors are well blended.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix.
Place in ovenproof dish with almonds on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve as dip for crackers or raw vegetables.

title: peanut butter swirl fudge
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil and boil to soft ball stage (234°).
Remove from heat and stir in marshmallow cream, peanut butter and vanilla.
Spread in greased 8 x 8-inch pan. Spoon melted chocolate chips over fudge and swirl with a knife.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar and oil.
Beat eggs and pumpkin with sugar and oil.
Sift flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder, nutmeg, allspice, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to pumpkin mixture alternately with water.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 well-greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until done. Let stand 10 minutes and remove from pans.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Line a baking pan with aluminum foil. Dip each chicken breast half into the butter and then coat with the crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350 degrees for 40 to 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.

title: jiffy cranberry muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients all at once and stir until mixed.
Spoon into paper lined pans and bake in 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: almond ice
directions: Soften vanilla ice cream and mix with Cool Whip and almond extract.
Put 1 1/2 tablespoons of crushed Heath bars in the bottom of a parfait glass.
Pour softened vanilla ice cream over Heath bars and then put 1 tablespoon of Heath bars on top.
Freeze until ready to serve.
Set out at room temperature about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onions, celery and garlic in large skillet.
Add Worcestershire, chili powder, sugar, salt, pepper and water; simmer 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and tomatoes; simmer 15 additional minutes.
Transfer to a large pot and add cooked shrimp.
Heat thoroughly.
Add rice.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Blend ingredients well until cream cheese chunks are dissolved. Use with taco chips. Better when refrigerated for 24 hours.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix together the cake mix, butter and 1 egg; press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cape cod clam pie
directions: Beat eggs in bowl; put 1 tablespoon in a cup and reserve. Drain liquid from clams; measure 3/4 cup and stir into eggs and clams, milk, cracker crumbs, salt and pepper.
Spoon into crust; dot evenly with oleo.
Top with second crust.
Tuck in edges and flute.
Cut slits in center to vent steam.
Stir cold water into 1 tablespoon reserved egg and brush over crust.
Bake at 450° (very hot!) 15 minutes.
Lower temperature and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Cool 15 minutes.
Cut into wedges.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar using mixer.
Add water and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour and pecans.
Chill and shape into balls.
Bake in slow oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: party punch
directions: Mix sugar with 5 cups water.
Boil and cool.
Mix everything together and add soda just before serving.

title: chilies rellenos bake
directions: In skillet, brown ground beef and chopped onion; drain off fat.
Sprinkle meat with salt and pepper.
Place green chilies, cut in half and seeded, in 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish; sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and top with meat.
Arrange chilies over meat.
Combine eggs, milk, flour, salt, pepper sauce and pepper; beat until smooth.
Pour over chili mixture.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.
Let cool 5 minutes and cut in squares.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage patch stew
directions: Brown beef in Dutch oven.
Add onions, cabbage and celery. Cook and stir until vegetables are lightly browned.
Stir in tomatoes, kidney beans with liquid, water, salt and pepper and chili powder.
Heat to boiling, reduce heat.

title: ava's green bean casserole
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, water and oil and boil for one minute. Pour over beans.
Slice onion over beans and leave overnight in refrigerator.
Cook 4 hours in a crock-pot on low.
(May be cooked in oven at 275° for 4 hours.)

title: green chile stew
directions: Heat olive oil, brown meat, add bacon, onion and garlic; saut. Add flour to make roux.
Cook on low heat for 10 minutes.
Add tomato, jalapeno, chile, and chicken stock and bring to a boil. Add potato, cilantro, sugar, salt and pepper.
Reduce heat and simmer until potatoes are done.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Place raspberries in a bowl; mash slightly.

Sprinkle with the sugar and let stand for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Combine orange juice and remaining ingredients in a small saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves. Remove from heat and let cool.

title: devilish good eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Remove yolks; mash.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Refill whites.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender; tear from bone.
To water, add chicken, noodles, soups, salt and pepper.
Bake in oven at 350° until thick and noodles are tender.
Add more water if needed.

title: thai hot shrimp dip
directions: In a small saucepan, cook the shrimp and save the broth.
Wrap chili peppers, garlic and onion with aluminum foil.
Roast on medium-low heat for 2 minutes.
On each side, unwrap and place in blender.
Grind until fine.
Add the shrimp.
Spin until well mixed.
Add 2 tablespoons shrimp broth.
Season with m.s.g., fish sauce, salt and lemon juice.
Spoon onto the serving dish.
Trim all the vegetables.
Wash and drain.
Cook, uncovered in boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain or serve raw.
Arrange on the serving plate.
Put the shrimp in the center.
Serve.

title: indian springs drive chocolate walnut pie
directions: Beginning with eggs, put ingredients into a slow mixer in order listed, alternating walnut pieces and chocolate morsels.
Almost as soon as the last is in, turn off mixer.
Then stir with spatula to make sure all is mixed.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate cherry cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine cookie mix, egg and water; stir until blended.
Stir in cherries and coconut.
Shape dough into 36 balls.
Roll in nuts.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 11 or 12 minutes.

title: fruited tofu
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in blender or food processor and process smooth for sauce.
Place remaining ingredients in a bowl and toss with tofu sauce.
Serve in sherbet or parfait cups garnished with a piece of the fruit and mint leaves.
Makes 6 servings, 75 calories per serving.

title: meat loaf roll
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients and 1/2 cup tomato sauce.
Shape into 14 x 10-inch rectangle on a sheet of waxed paper.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Roll, jelly roll fashion, lifting waxed paper to help make the roll easier.
Press edges and ends to seal.
Place roll, seam side down, on baking sheet.
Bake t 350° for 45 minutes.
Pour remaining sauce over meat roll.
Bake 15 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: best ever pie crust
directions: Mix the first three ingredients together and then add the shortening and mix all together.
Then add the water and vinegar to the flour mixture.
Mix till all is moistened.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Use a glass round dish.
Mix vegetables, soup, milk and cheese in a dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugars and oil.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture by hand.
Add apples, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in tube pan or sheet cake pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare pudding as directed on package except add an additional 1/2 cup of milk.
Cream together the cream cheese and butter.
Mix into prepared pudding.
Gently fold in Cool Whip.

title: simple molasses sugar cookies
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients.
Mix all ingredients and chill for several hours or overnight.
Roll in small balls.
Roll balls in sugar and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut bars
directions: Have butter at room temperature; chop nuts and grease 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Mix first 3 ingredients until well blended. Press into pan and bake for 20 minutes.
Do not brown.
Mix remaining ingredients except coconut and spread over batter in pan.
Sprinkle top with coconut and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until brown.
Cut into squares while still warm.

title: ciopinno
directions: In 3-quart saucepan cook green pepper, onion and garlic in oil until tender.
Add	undrained
tomatoes,
tomato sauce, wine, parsley,
oregano, basil, salt
and
pepper.
Bring
to boil. Reduce heat, cover and
simmer
20	minutes.
Cut
fish into 1 inch pieces, add fish,
shrimp
to	tomato	mixture and cook about 10 minutes.
Add undrained	clams
and cook about 5 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients and stir in mixture.
Roll into balls the size of small walnuts.
Roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: corn vegetable medley
directions: In saucepan, heat soup and milk to boiling, stirring often. Stir in vegetables.
Return to boiling.
Cover; cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring often. Stir in cheese.
Heat through.
Serves 6.

title: spiced cranberry ring
directions: Dissolve jello, salt, cinnamon and cloves in boiling water. Add cranberry sauce and orange rind. Chill until thickened. Fold in orange and apple. Pour into 6-cup mold. Chill about 4 hours. Makes 9 servings.

title: 12 hour salad
directions: Cut sauerkraut into small pieces and mix with sugar and stand 30 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cover tightly; refrigerate for 12 hours.

title: raspberry cheese cake
directions: Add sugar to finely crushed graham crackers.
Add melted margarine.
Press lightly into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes. Cool.

title: celery au gratin
directions: Wash and peel celery.
Cut into approximately 3-inch pieces. In pot, cover with water.
Add salt.
Simmer until tender.
Drain liquid.
In baking casserole dish, layer celery, pats of butter, cream and grated cheese.
Continue as many layers as ingredients. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until top is golden brown.

title: low calorie onion soup
directions: Blend yogurt and cottage cheese in medium bowl.
Stir in onion soup mix and chili powder.
Refrigerate, covered, for 3 hours. Place on tray with an assortment of crisp vegetables.

title: cranberry salad supreme
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix cherry jello and water.
Add whole cranberry sauce.
Pour into 8-inch square pan and chill.

title: smoked oyster roll
directions: You will need wax paper.

title: crab-stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems.
Chop.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter and add stems and chopped onions.
Saute until limp.
Remove from heat and stir in all ingredients except soy sauce.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter and add soy sauce.
Pour into pan to coat.
Mound filling into caps firmly.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: country salad
directions: Place ingredients in the order given.
Mix dressing, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Spread over top, sealing the edges. This salad will keep 24 hours or longer.
Spread grated cheese over top and serve.
Layer ingredients in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Boil eggplant until soft.
Drain the water off.
Mash eggplant and margarine.
Add all seasonings.
Cook onion and bell pepper before adding.
Boil tomatoes until mushy.
Mix well all ingredients, including egg and cheese.
Pour into baking dish. Put croutons and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Put in blender half at a time.
For use with:
celery, carrots, raw cauliflower, green pepper, mushrooms, cherry tomatoes and radishes.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix well. Add vanilla and poppy seed.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Add to poppy seed mixture alternating with milk. Pour into loaf pan. Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done. Serve with butter or cold cream cheese and pineapple.

title: graham (nut) crust
directions: Combine crumbs with cinnamon, nuts and margarine together. Reserve 3 tablespoons.
Press into bottom and partway up sides of 9-inch spring pan or Corning Ware baking dish.

title: mom's chicken parmesan
directions: Beat egg with water using fork in shallow pan. Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese and paprika in second shallow pan. Dip chicken pieces in bread crumb mixture, then egg mixture and again in bread crumb mixture.
Place coated chicken in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

Microwave on High 4 to 8 minutes or until meat is cooked. Top cooked meat with spaghetti sauce and a sprinkling of oregano. Cook on High 10 to 12 minutes or until sauce is hot. Sprinkle grated or place sliced Mozzarella over top of each piece and let stand, covered, 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: chopstick tuna(healthy diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place tuna in a medium bowl.
Combine milk, water and soup in separate bowl.
Add to tuna and stir well. Add peas, water chestnuts, half of noodles, plus tomato, celery, green onions and soy sauce.
Toss lightly to mix.
Spray 1 1/2-quart casserole with cooking spray.
Pour/spoon mixture into casserole and then top with remaining noodles.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or microwave for 8 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Makes 8 servings.

title: rice dressing
directions: Saute onion and pepper in butter until clear, not brown.
Place rice in large baking dish.
Add rest of ingredients to the rice. Cover with tight lid so steam won't escape.
Cook 45 minutes in 350° oven.
When cooking time is up, leave lid on 10 to 15 minutes to fluff up the rice.
Add chicken.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and walnuts.
In a separate bowl, blend mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Fold in whipping cream. Fold dressing into apple mixture.
Makes 6 servings.
Enjoy!

title: spinach brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in 9-inch square pan, greased. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
May be baked a day ahead and reheated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: wintery dry bean soup
directions: Rinse beans.
Cover with water; add salt and soak overnight. Drain and add 2 quarts water and meat.
Simmer 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Add onion, garlic, chili powder, tomatoes and lemon juice.
Simmer 45 minutes.

title: hunting camp pancakes
directions: In the evening, mix corn meal and 1 cup of buttermilk; let stand in refrigerator overnight.
In the morning, add the Bisquick, eggs, soda and 2 cups of buttermilk.
Mix well.
Bake on a lightly greased, hot griddle.
Serve with syrup and bacon or sausage.
Yields 12 to 14 (6-inch) pancakes.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Prepare
pudding
mix
with
milk
as per directions on package.
Then
mix Cool Whip with it.
Line the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch
pan
with whole graham crackers.
Pour one-half of the pudding mix over crackers.	Place another layer of crackers over this.
Top with remaining pudding.	Frost the remaining graham crackers
with icing and place on top of the final pudding	layer, smoothing	frosting
to give a finished look. Chill for at least one hour.

title: cheese and sausage munchies
directions: Cook sausage and drain thoroughly.
Sprinkle sausage in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover sausage with grated cheese. Mix together the eggs, chili peppers and chili powder.
Pour egg mixture over cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Cool slightly and cut into bite-size pieces.

title: prune cake
directions: Combine all together.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes in 350° oven.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix
altogether and put in refrigerator. Put the same amount of cottage cheese in as Cool Whip.

title: ta-to-tot casserole
directions: Butter 1 1/2-quart or 9-inch square baking dish.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix soup with milk, celery seed and onion flakes.
Pour over taters in bowl and mix well. Don't break up taters.
Put into baking dish and sprinkle garlic powder, salt and pepper on top. Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Take from oven and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on top.
Return to oven and bake until cheese is melted. Can add 1 can cubed cooked ham or chicken before baking if desired.

title: potato casserole
directions: Put potatoes in 9 x 13 pan; pour melted margarine over top. Mix. Mix cheese, onion, soup and salt and pepper. Pour this over the potatoes. Mix the margarine and corn flake crumbs. Pour this over the other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes COVERED and 20 minutes UNCOVERED or until it is bubbling on the sides.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash broccoli, chop and add other ingredients.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat 1 minute on low speed.
Pour into baked pie shell and chill 3 hours.

title: mexican chili rellenos
directions: Boil peppers until tender. Seed and split peppers down the side. Shred cheese or slice into thin strips.
Stuff pepper with cheese.
Roll in flour, then with egg and milk. Brown in hot oil. And then put them in a baking dish and top with salsa and extra cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes covered at 400°.

title: the ruby slipper
directions: Combine cake mix, sour cream, water and eggs in large bowl. Blend.
Then beat at medium speed
for 2 minutes until creamy. Spoon 1/3 cup of batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch fluted pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup of the gelatin.
Repeat layers. Spread remaining batter over gelatin to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: tennessee cookies
directions: Mix together with hands and make into small balls.
In a double boiler, melt 12-ounce package chocolate bits and half block of paraffin.
Dip rice balls in the mixture and put on wax paper. Put a pecan on the top.

title: brunch punch
directions: Stir drink mix and orange juice in plastic or glass pitcher until mix is dissolved.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: In mixer bowl, cream together sugar, shortening and butter. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla and lemon extract.
Mix together flour and baking soda.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.

title: cole slaw salad
directions: You will use only the flavor packet from the noodles.
Mix oil and vinegar with the flavor packet.
Toss the cabbage and sunflower seeds together.
Add mixture and toss.

title: indian fried steak
directions: Sprinkle both sides of steak generously with lemon-pepper. Let dry marinate and come to room temperature.
Heat heavy iron skillet on almost high heat.
Drop steak in skillet.
It will stick and smoke.
Press gently against side of steak with spatula until it comes loose.
Turn and repeat.
The steak will be sealed on the outside and juicy on the inside.

title: dixie tea muffins
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients together well.
Mix together the milk, eggs, butter and salt, then add dry ingredients, stirring just enough to mix evenly.
Have muffin tins buttered and floured and fill each cup half full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; check during baking.

title: blackfoot potato soup
directions: Brown sausage in a heavy kettle.
Remove and drain excess fat. Add celery, onion, thyme and salt.
Cook until onion is tender. Stir in flour.
Cook 1 minute.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces and steam. Mix next 4 ingredients and combine with cooked broccoli. Put into greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Melt margarine and mix in crushed Ritz crackers; spread mixture over top of casserole. Bake at 350°, covered, for 15 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugars and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together. Gradually add to sugar mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: english muffin pizza
directions: Toast English muffin.
Put cheese and sauce on top.
Bake for 10 minutes.

title: granny's glazed orange rolls
directions: In large bowl combine 2 cups of flour and yeast.
Heat milk, 1/2 cup sugar, 3 tablespoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt until warm (115° to 120°), stirring to melt butter.
Add to dry mixture and add eggs.
Beat at low speed with mixer for 1/2 minute, scraping bowl.
Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
Stir in enough remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough.
Knead on floured surface until smooth (3 to 5 minutes).
Place in greased bowl, turning once.
Cover dough and let rise (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Punch down; divide in half.
Cover and let rest 10 minutes.

title: baked ziti
directions: Cook ziti; drain and set aside.
Cook beef; drain.
Stir in Ricotta.
Mix in Parmesan cheese, parsley, salt, pepper and half sauce.
Add ziti and toss to coat.
Spoon into 13 x 9-inch pan and add rest of sauce.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Beat first 6 ingredients together until smooth.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased, floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix and roll in balls.
Cook in a 350° oven until brown.

title: wassail
directions: Boil sugar and water for 10 minutes.
Add spices and fruit rind.
Cover and let stand for 2 hours.
Strain.
Add orange juice, lemon juice and cider.
Reheat and serve.
Goes great in the crockpot.
A tradition with Baltimore County Girl Scouts since the 1940s.

title: coconut cake
directions: While cake bakes, cook following ingredients: milk, sugar and 1 cup coconut for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: whipped cream cake
directions: Beat oleo, sugar and eggs (1 at a time) well, until creamy. Sift together flour and soda.
Add flour, soda, sour cream and vanilla.
Do this alternately to the sugar mix.
Bake in 3 greased and floured 9-inch pans for about 40 minutes at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: cookout vegetables
directions: You will need heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: linguesa lava beans
directions: Slice linguesa in small pieces. Saute in large frying pan. Remove linguesa.
Slice onion and pepper.
Saute in fat from linguesa. When done, add can of lava beans with juice, can of tomato sauce and linguesa. Combine all together and simmer 20 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix pudding (in powder form) and pineapple. Add green coloring. Add marshmallows and chopped nuts and mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well. Chill well before serving. (Can be made the night before serving.) Decorate with candied cherries or marshmallow flowers, if desired.

title: great aunt wilda's molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening in 3 or 4-quart saucepan over low heat.
Allow to cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg; beat well.
Add flour, soda, spices and salt.
Beat well.
Make 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: oreo cookie bar
directions: Crush cookies and mix with Cool Whip.
Stir in soft ice cream with
cookie
mixture.
Put
in
square
dish and freeze until hard enough to cut with knife.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Add broccoli last.
Pour in greased casserole dish and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
You can layer dish with baked chicken breast.

title: cheesy chicken and green bean casserole(low carb)
directions: In a skillet, brown chicken breasts until almost cooked. Place chicken in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Place butter in skillet and saut onion, celery and mushrooms until soft.
Mix remaining ingredients together in a skillet with vegetables and pour over chicken breasts.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover to brown if desired.

title: aunt mildred's 7-up jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water; beat in cream cheese until smooth. Stir in pineapple, sugar, vanilla, pecans and food coloring. Blend in 7-Up.
Pour into mold and chill.
(Do not freeze).

title: lentil pilaf
directions: Melt butter over high heat in skillet that has a cover.
Add rice and pasta, stirring to coat with butter (oil).
Saute until rice is brown. Add vegetables.
Saute 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add lentils and stock.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer gently for about 20 minutes or until lentils are tender. Add seasonings as desired.

title: easy spanish casserole
directions: Mix all except cheese.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with cheese and return to oven until cheese melts. Delicious if served with coleslaw and garlic toast.

title: raspberry tea
directions: Mix together.
For each serving, place 3 teaspoons into cup of either hot or cold water.
Stir until dissolved.
Enjoy!

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until set in the center.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Mix well and freeze.
Set out about 20 minutes before serving.

title: stuffed grape leaves(dolmathes)
directions: Wash fresh leaves thoroughly.
If canned leaves are to be used, rinse in water to remove excess brine.

title: peanut butter candy
directions: Cream sugar and Karo in medium saucepan.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and peanut butter and stir until smooth.
Stir in corn flakes until coated.
Drop on wax paper by teaspoons.

title: wacky cake
directions: Sift together the flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa. Mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Add melted oleo, water, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix quickly by folding in and stirring.
Do not beat with electric mixer.
Pour in greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350` for 30 minutes.
Do not underbake.
Makes two 9-inch square pans or 3 layers or one 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan or 13 x 9-inch pan.
In large bowl, combine all bar ingredients.
By hand, stir until well mixed.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° in jelly roll pan for 20 to 30 minutes or in 13 x 9-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: apple squares
directions: Mix 3 cups flour, salt, sugar and margarine as you would for pie crust.
Mix together 1/2 cup flour, water, vinegar and egg to form a paste.
Add to first mixture.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out dough and line jelly roll pan with dough.
Spread with apples and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Roll out remaining dough and cover apples.
Glaze with powdered sugar, vanilla and enough water to be able to pour over dough.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: gumdrop cookies
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet, which has been greased.
Bake for 12 minutes at 375°.
Makes 5 to 6 dozen cookies.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In an 8 x 12-inch glass baking dish, mix sugar and corn syrup. Microwave on High for 4 minutes.
Stir with a wooden spoon. Microwave 4 minutes more.
Stir in peanuts, butter and vanilla. Microwave 2 minutes on High.
Add soda and stir until light and foamy.
Pour into a greased cookie sheet and spread thin.
Allow to cool completely.
Break into small pieces.
Store in an airtight container in a cool place.
Makes 1 pound.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve the sugar and Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water.
Add the remaining 3/4 cup water and refrigerate until partially set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into mold or square pan. Refrigerate until set.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt shortening over low heat.
Let cool.
Add sugar, molasses and egg.
Beat well.
Sift together flour, soda, cloves, ginger, cinnamon and salt.
Add to the first mixture.
Beat well.
Chill. Form in 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes or a little more if necessary.

title: grape punch
directions: Blend tea, pineapple and lemon juice in electric blender. Add to remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into pitcher partially filled with ice and stir.
Add pineapple slices to float on top.

title: hot beef dip
directions: Stir chopped dried beef into cream cheese.
Add milk and sour cream.
Stir in garlic salt and onions.
Spread in shallow casserole dish.
Brown nuts in butter and spread on top of mixture.
Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: biscotti
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs with electric mixer at high until fluffy.
Gradually beat in extracts and sugar until mixture is thick and lemon colored.
Mix cake flour with baking powder and salt.
With a wire whisk fold into egg mixture until just thoroughly combined.
Fold in nuts.
Grease a cookie sheet and form two 3 x 10-inch logs from the cookie mixture.
Bake 30 minutes. Remove from oven; leave oven on.
Let logs cool on sheets for 5 minutes or until cool enough to handle.
With a serrated knife, cut each log diagonally into slices about 1 inch thick.
Place slices, flat side down, on cookie sheet and return to oven.
Bake 7 minutes.
Turn slices over and bake 5 to 7 minutes until golden on both sides.
Cool and store in tightly covered container.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice bacon into bits.
Fry bacon in 4-quart pan.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Chop onion.
Remove bacon from pan; put potatoes and onion into bacon grease.
Salt.
Fry for 5 minutes.
Cover potatoes with water; cook until tender.
The longer you cook, the mushier they get and this makes soup base thicker.

title: lasagne
directions: In large pot brown meat and drain.
Return to pot; add tomatoes and break up.
Add tomato paste, garlic, basil and oregano.
Heat to boiling.
Stir occasionally.
Reduce heat; simmer uncovered 20 minutes or until mixture is consistency of spaghetti sauce.
Heat oven to 350°.

title: stella's tuna casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cook elbows in boiling water for 10 minutes. Drain and place in large casserole dish.
Melt Cheez Whiz and equal amount of milk in saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Add cheese mixture to elbows with tuna, peas, salt and pepper and mix together.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over entire top.
Cover and bake 30 minutes or until top is bubbling and brown.

title: dr. cooper's super soup
directions: Cut and chop all vegetables into small chunks.
Boil in water with seasoning and/or black pepper about 10 minutes.
Lower heat and simmer until vegetables reach desired consistency.
Broccoli, mushrooms, okra and cauliflower may be added to the soup as desired.
This soup may be eaten in unlimited quantities.
There are very few calories!

title: golden exotic chicken
directions: Cover and pour over.
Marinate a few hours.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: broiled stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wipe mushrooms with damp cloth.
Remove stems.
Brush caps with melted butter.
Place hollow side up in shallow pan.
Chop stems. Pan-broil bacon and drain on paper towel.
Combine stems, bacon and cheese.
Heap into mushroom caps.
Broil 3 1/2-inches below heat turned to 450° for 7 to 8 minutes.
May be prepared early and refrigerated until time to broil.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix ingredients and bake 1 hour at 300 degrees.
Make a mixture of brown sugar, nuts and raisins. Top the casserole with this mixture after the first 30 minutes of baking.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into uncooked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; reduce heat to 325° and bake 35 to 45 minutes longer.

title: christmas punch or hot russian tea
directions: Simmer tea, cinnamon and cloves in 4 cups water for 30 minutes.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
Pour Jell-O mixture into large container.
Then add 6 cups cold water.
Now add sugar and pineapple juice.
Squeeze and strain lemons and add to Jell-O mixture.
Strain tea mixture and combine with Jell-O mixture.
Makes more than one gallon.
Serve cold for punch and hot for tea.

title: cereal coconut crisps
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by spoonful onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix together and put in 2 pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: Mix all ingredients except wings.
Coat chicken with mixture. Fry in hot oil for approximately 6 minutes or until done.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, cornstarch and cream.
Mix well. Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: favorite peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream together margarine and sugars. Add peanut butter and egg.
Blend well.
Combine flour, salt and soda together.
Blend slowly into creamed mixture.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cookies
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Spread into an ungreased pan. Beat Egg White until foamy.
Spread over cookie dough.
Top with sliced Almonds.
Sprinkle the Sugar mixed with Cinnamon over cookies.
Bake at 350 for 25 minutes.
Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes.
Cut and cool thoroughly.

title: marlene's dump cake
directions: In ungreased cake pan (13 x 9-inch), spread pie filling. Next, layer crushed pineapple and cake mix, then pour melted butter or margarine on top.
Layer coconut, then nuts.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Let sit for one whole day or cake will crumble apart when cut.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Add sugar to the beaten egg whites.
Gradually beat until stiff.
Add nuts, chocolate bits, vanilla and salt.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line cookie sheet with foil and grease slightly with butter, margarine or Pam.
Drop cookies by spoonful.
Turn oven off.
Leave cookies in oven overnight.
(Do not open oven door.)

title: dill pot roast
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour with salt and pepper.
Dredge roast in flour.
Brown in oil on stove in frying pan.
Place in roaster. Add onions, dill weed, vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Cover; cook slowly for 2 hours.
Add carrots and cook 1 hour.
Remove meat to heated platter.
Pour liquid from roaster.
Mix 2 tablespoons flour and 1/2 cup water.
Add to cooking liquid, stirring constantly.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles.
Mix everything together and top with cheese. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: buster bars
directions: In saucepan, melt together the powdered sugar, chocolate chips, evaporated milk and butter.
Bring to a boil and boil for 8 minutes, stirring often. Remove from burner.
Cool for 1 hour.

title: cranberry tea
