directions: Boil ingredients for 8 minutes; cool.
Store in covered containers.
Reheat as needed.
Serve hot.
Makes approximately 4 1/2 to 5 quarts.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix water and soup together.
Put thin layer of soup mixture on the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix white rice and herb rice together (uncooked).
Spread rice evenly over thin layer of soup mixture.
Place chicken on top of rice.
Pour remaining soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Cook 1 1/2 hours (uncover the last 15 to 20 minutes for rice to absorb all the soup).

title: corn casserole
directions: Stir all together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Slice 1/2 cake in chunks.
Arrange in dish.
Combine milk, water and almond extract.
Add pudding mix.
Stir and chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour 1/2 over arranged cake chunks.
Arrange 1/2 peaches on top of that.
Repeat layers, ending with peaches.
Chill 4 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *May use cauliflower, broccoli, green peppers (diced), green onions (chopped), cucumbers, grated carrots, tomatoes (diced) and olives.

title: beef rice
directions: Melt margarine in pan over medium heat.
Add rice, stir until lightly brown.
Add onion, garlic powder, salt, pepper and broth. Stir until this comes to boil.
Cover until rice is tender and dry.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cut fine all ingredients. Season with salt, pepper and a little cayenne.
Mix well together with cooked mayonnaise and serve on top of lettuce leaves with mayonnaise on top.

title: apricot salad
directions: Run apricots through the blender.
Toss in cheese.
Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Dump jello into blender.
Pour in juice.
Blend, chill and eat.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken on top of stove.
Remove bones.
To chicken and broth, add soup, water, milk and pepper and salt to taste.
Cook over very low heat, stirring with wire whisk until blended.
Add 2 cans of biscuits, cut in fourths.
Cook slowly until biscuits are cooked.
Stir often.

title: butterscotch crackles
directions: Cream together sugars and margarine; add egg and vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and add nuts.
Add to first mixture.
Roll into balls and roll in sugars (don't flatten).
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
These cookies will be flat and cracked.

title: blue corn pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir buttermilk into egg yolks and yogurt.
Stir in melted butter and mix with dry ingredients.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Fry in butter in 3-inch rounds.
Serve with 1 tablespoon honey pecan butter and warmed maple syrup.
Garnish with pecans.

title: sally's barbecue beef
directions: Brown meat. Saute onion. Add other ingredients. Simmer until thick.

title: 4-h orange smoothie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender.
Cover and blend until smooth.
Serve immediately.
Makes 6 (3/4 cup) servings (115 calories per serving).

title: potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thaw potatoes and combine with 1/2 cup margarine, salt, pepper, onions, soup, sour cream and cheese. Place in a greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch casserole.

title: mike's chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in oats and raisins.
Drop by teaspoons onto greased cookie sheet. Bake in 325° oven 12 to 15 minutes.
Yields 3 1/2 dozen.

title: cream bread romme-bro
directions: Cream must be cold and thick.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Drain juice from blueberries
and add to it enough cold water to make a total 2
cups
of
liquid.
Heat
liquid
to a boil; pour into Jell-O and add
cup
of
cold
water.
Add blueberries and crushed pineapple.
Pour
into
a
9 x 12-inch dish or pan and congeal.
Whip cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla together with
mixer.
Spread on salad just before serving.
Garnish with chopped nuts if desired.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk, peanut butter, corn syrup and salt in a heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Cook, stirring occasionally, to 234 degrees (or until small amount dropped into cold water forms a soft ball).
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Do not stir.
Allow fudge to cool at room temperature without stirring until it reaches 110 degrees.
Beat until fudge thickens and loses some of its gloss.
Quickly pour fudge into a lightly buttered 8-inch square pan.
Makes about 1-1/2 pounds fudge.

title: rhubarb bars
directions: In a large saucepan, combine the rhubarb, sugar, cornstarch, water and baking soda.
While stirring, bring to a boil and cook until thick and bubbly (about 5 minutes).
Set aside and stir in vanilla.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and water.
Mix well. Add flour, soda and salt.
Mix.
Then add oatmeal and vanilla, mixing well.

title: easy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt 1 stick butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brown sugar. Place pineapple rings and cherries on top of butter/sugar.
Pour on yellow cake batter and bake according to box.

title: wanieta's broccoli
directions: Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: five cup fruit salad
directions: Place
the
first
four
ingredients
in a bowl and mix well. Fold
sour
cream
into fruit mixture and mix until all ingredients are well moistened.
Cover and chill in refrigerator until serving time.
Makes 3 2/3 cups or 4 to 6 servings.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Blend together cream cheese, milk and powdered sugar.
Spread over baked, cooled pie crust.
Sprinkle with chopped pecans. Spread Cool Whip over pecans.
Chill in refrigerator.
Top with fresh strawberries before serving.
Also, can use Thank You cherry pie filling for topping.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook in boiling water until soft.
Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: cran-apple salad
directions: Peel oranges and remove all membranes.
Grind cranberries, apples, nuts and oranges in food processor.
Bring apple juice concentrate to a boil in the microwave.
Dissolve jelly in this. Cool with ice cubes.
Pour over ground fruit mixture and refrigerate.

title: overnight fresh crunchy pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in eighths lengthwise.
Slice onion and separate into rings.
Put both in large glass or ceramic bowl.
Combine other ingredients in a glass or enamel pan.
Heat and stir until sugar dissolves (use wooden spoon).
Pour over cucumbers and onions.
Toss and coat.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for 24 hours, tossing occasionally.

title: chiffon salad
directions: Soak gelatin in cold water and dissolve in hot water.
Cook pineapple and sugar 5 minutes.
Mix with gelatin.
Chill in icebox until it begins to congeal.
Fold in whipped cream, nuts and cheese.
Place in square pan and put in icebox and chill.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: butterhorn rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast, 1 tablespoon lukewarm water and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Put milk in large bowl and add yeast mixture.
Add sugar, oil, eggs, salt and flour.
Mix well with spoon.
Cover and keep at room temperature overnight.
Next day, about 4 hours before serving, knead slightly on floured board.
Divide in 2 equal parts.
Roll each into 16 pie shaped pieces.
Roll each piece from big end to small.
Let rise.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: anabel's dry seasoning mix
directions: Combine all thoroughly and store in covered container.
Use in place of salt for meat, salads, dressings, etc.

title: apple casserole
directions: Into greased casserole (I use margarine for greasing), add apples and cranberries.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup sugar (this can be done the day before and refrigerated).
Mix melted margarine, oatmeal, flour, brown sugar and nuts.
Sprinkle over apples and cranberries.
Bake approximately 1 hour in 350° oven.
Serves 12 plus.
May be used as side dish or dessert.

title: seasoned tea mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Makes 1 1/2 cups tea mix. To serve, combine 1 1/2 teaspoons tea mix with each cup of water. Steep to desired strength.
Strain.

title: cheesy green bean casserole
directions: Stir together eggs, cheese and Worcestershire sauce.
Arrange drained green beans in shallow 1-quart baking dish.
Spoon cheese mixture atop.
Toss together bread crumbs and butter; sprinkle atop cheese mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cheese mixture is set.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: old fashion popcorn balls
directions: Cook until it forms soft ball in cold water.
Then add 1 teaspoon baking soda.
Beat, then pour over popped corn.
Butter hands and form balls.

title: chocolate chip pan cookies
directions: Mix first three ingredients and set aside.
Cream the rest of the ingredients.
Add first three ingredients to creamed mixture. Mix well.
Grease 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: melba's steak in mushroom gravy
directions: Brown meat on both sides in hot oil in large fry pan.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until tender.
Serves 4 to 6.
I like to cut meat into serving size pieces.

title: most marvelous guacamole
directions: Mash avocados with a fork.
Mix in lemon juice, tomatoes and salsa.
Salt and pepper to taste and garnish with cilantro.

title: pancakes (extra tender)
directions: Mix milk, egg, and butter; add flour, baking soda and sugar. Pour batter into center of hot griddle.

title: strawberry pecan cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and bake in 3 layers.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring margarine to boil. Add cocoa and water. Remove from heat. Add flour, sugar, salt, eggs and mix well. Add sour cream and baking soda. Pour into greased 1-1/2 x 9 x 13 inch sheet cake pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix flour, softened margarine and pecans.
Press in bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust.
Beat pudding and milk.
Pour over cream filling. Spread with rest of Cool Whip.
Cool 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge pie
directions: Mix well. Bake 20 minutes at 375° or 400°.

title: simple cranberry salad
directions: Mix well in order given and refrigerate until set.

title: hearty fiesta burgers
directions: Combine crumbs, eggs, onion, catsup, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add ground chuck and mix well.
Shape meat mixture into 6 patties.
In large skillet, brown patties on both sides.
Spoon soup over meat; top with beans and green pepper. Cook, covered, over low heat for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture; cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 (at my house, less)!!
Add a fruit salad and dinner rolls for a delicious meal.

title: whole wheat bread in one step
directions: Dissolve yeast and sugar in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Add quart of water and butter.
Add flour with salt and dry milk.
Mix well. Divide into 3 loaves; dough will be sticky but no kneading is necessary.
Let rise about 2 hours in warm place.
Bake at 420° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 375° for 40 minutes.
Turn heat off last 10 minutes of cooking time, making it 1 hour altogether.

title: hearty dutch hot pot
directions: Slice kielbasa into 2-inch chunks.
Slice carrots lengthwise, then chop into 2 inch pieces.
Cut potatoes into large chunks.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix Jello with boiling water. Add cream cheese and beat until smooth. Add fruit, nuts, sugar, and vanilla. Pour in 7-up slowly and stir. Place in refrigerator and stir again in 15 minutes. Serve when congealed.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix butter, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and cold water together. In another bowl, mix yeast and add warm water together.
Then mix the two mixtures and slowly stir in flour.
When finished, place dough in a buttered bowl with a damp cloth over top.
Place in refrigerator overnight to raise.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Place macaroni in 4 or 5 quarts of boiling water, stirring frequently, and boil until almost tender.
While water is boiling, grate cheese and put aside.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper and set aside.

title: chicken tonight
directions: Follow directions on label.
This is one of my favorites.

title: bertha smith's old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and beat.
Add milk, salt, vanilla, baking powder and flour, a little at a time, until stiff enough to roll out.
Pinch off dough; roll on floured board.
Add flour so that it won't stick.
Grease and flour cake pans or skillet.
Bake in oven until light brown.
Spread each layer with cooked, mashed and sweetened apples.
Leave top layer without apples.
Put 1 teaspoon ground cloves into apple mixture. Store cake 2 or 3 days before eating.

title: green rice
directions: Mix rice, soup and cheese.
Pour boiling water over broccoli, leave long enough to thaw, then drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Place in greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: blueberry treat
directions: Break cake into small pieces and put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Pour pudding mixture over cake and mix.
Spread pie filling over this.
Refrigerate and when ready to serve, spread Cool Whip over all.
You can use any pie filling you like (cherry, blackberry or lemon).

title: pickled garden relish
directions: In a 1 gallon glass jar or 4 quart jars, layer sliced cucumbers and onions, 1 inch each layer.
Repeat until just below mouth of jar.

title: raisin nut cookies
directions: Cream crisco, salt, and sugar together, add beaten eggs, nuts, and raisins.
Mix well and add cream; together.
Mix well and drop by spoonful on greased pans.
Bake 15 minutes in hot oven.

title: aunt lora's fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Stir the soda into the syrup and add to the egg mixture.
Then add the flour and wine alternately.
Put into 2 large pans which have been lined with wax paper and greased.

title: tuna pot pie
directions: In large mixing bowl mix tuna, soup and vegetables until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into pie crust.
Cover with second pie crust.
Pinch edges and bake 45 minutes at 400°.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom's cherry tart
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, oleo and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk. Spread over graham cracker mixture in pan.
Sprinkle pecans over cream cheese mixture.
Spread whipped topping over nuts.
Spoon pie filling over whipped topping.
Refrigerate.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt in pan.
Stir in water.
Cook, stirring until smooth and thick.
Remove from heat and add to beaten yolks.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove and add butter and lemon juice.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Top with meringue and place under broiler until light brown.

title: dried beans and ham hocks
directions: Wash ham hocks and put in small pressure pot.
Cover with water and cook for 45 minutes.
Let pot cool on its own.
Wash beans and put in pot you plan to cook the beans in.
Put about 1 1/2 quarts of water on the beans.
Bring to a boil; boil for a few minutes.
Cover and let stand for approximately 2 hours.
Drain water from the beans that they soaked in.
Add the water from the ham hocks to the beans.
Cut up the ham hocks and put in the pot with the beans.
Cook together over slow to moderate burner for 1 to 2 hours or until done.

title: nutty sweet potato biscuits
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
In another bowl, combine sweet potatoes, sugar, butter and vanilla; add to flour mixture and mix well.
Turn onto a lightly floured surface; knead slightly.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 450° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 dozen.

title: sauerkraut hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and salt.
Put 1/2 in small cake pan.
Spread sauerkraut over hamburger.
Layer uncooked noodles and remaining meat on top.
Mix soups together and pour over casserole. Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese and continue to bake for 30 minutes more.

title: hamburger-chili stew
directions: Saute onions and beef in oil.
Add rest of ingredients and 1/2 soup can water.
Stir and heat through.
Add another 1/2 can water for a thinner stew.

title: delmarva chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Rinse and dry chicken.
Roll crackers until crushed; combine grated onion, chopped parsley, Parmesan, salt and pepper in bowl, blending well.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken in cracker mixture.
Place chicken on aluminum foil covered baking tray.
Sprinkle onion, parsley and cheese mixture onto chicken. Pour melted butter over all pieces.
Cover chicken for 40 minutes; then remove.
Cook, uncovered, for another 25 minutes until tender.

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Combine oil and water; bring to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Add flour and blend.
Pat into 9-inch pie plate.
Fill with your favorite filling; bake until pie is done.

title: peanut butter shake
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Serve at once.

title: melt in your mouth lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine cheeses, reserving 1/2 cup Mozzarella, eggs and parsley.
Set aside.

title: pina colada pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients except pecans and put into the 2 pie shells.
Top with the pecans.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Add Wesson oil and beat until smooth.
Add eggs and beat after each one.
Add carrots and nuts and beat.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans and bake at 350° until done. (Cook about 50 minutes.)

title: baked potato casserole
directions: Melt butter with potatoes.
Then mix in other ingredients. Season with salt and pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine in a 2 qt. casserole dish.
Mix in crumbled crackers.
Leave enough crackers in dish to cover bottom.
Debone chicken and mix with sour cream, cream of chicken soup and broth. Season with salt, pepper and parsley flakes to taste.
Pour into casserole dish and top with remaining crackers.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
You may also use leftover turkey or chicken and canned broth.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together graham crackers, 2 tablespoons sugar and oleo. Put in a greased and floured 9 x 3-inch spring-form pan.
Pat on bottom and a little up the side to cover the seam of bottom circle of pan.

title: nutty buddy yam cake
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until tender; drain.
Add sugar, egg, spices, margarine and milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.

title: string bean amondine
directions: Prepare
beans in 12-inch skillet or 1 (4 quart) saucepan. Heat 1 inch of water to boiling; add beans and simmer 10 minutes. Drain
beans and transfer to bowl.	In same pan melt butter;
add almonds
and
cook	until
golden
brown.
Spoon almonds and butter mixture over beans.	Add salt and pepper.

title: spaghetti soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat, onion, green pepper, celery, carrot and garlic until tender.
Drain off fat.
Add water, tomatoes, sauce, sugar and seasonings.
Bring to boil.
Add spaghetti; reduce heat.
Boil gently, uncovered, 12 to 15 minutes until spaghetti is tender.

title: joyce's chocolate cream delight
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, pour into 2 (8-inch) round pans and bake as directed.
Cool cakes and slice each cake in half so you will have 4 (8-inch) cakes.
Place 1 cake in a glass bowl.

title: a b c d - a broccoli corn dish(serves 3 to 4)
directions: Thaw broccoli to cut into coarse pieces.
Mix broccoli with corn, onions (or juice), 4 tablespoons melted butter, egg, salt and pepper.
Pour into greased casserole or baking dish.

title: cindy's macaroni salad
directions: Cook the macaroni according to package directions and cool. Combine all ingredients in large bowl and chill.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower in small pieces.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Crumble.
Combine mayonnaise, white vinegar and sugar.
Pour over all ingredients.
Refrigerate.

title: cherry salad
directions: Pour in dish and freeze.

title: one bowl brownies
directions: Put oil in a bowl.
Stir in cocoa, eggs, sugar, Karo and vanilla.
Mix flour, baking powder and salt together; add to cocoa mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 8 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. If a glass pan is used, bake at 325°.
They are chewer if not overbeaten or overbaked.

title: for goodness sake salad
directions: In a large bowl, dissolve the gelatin in boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in the milk, pineapple (in juice), mayonnaise, cottage cheese, nuts and horseradish sauce.
Mix well. Chill until partially set.
Pour into an oiled 8 cup mold.
Chill for 6 hours or overnight.
Unmold.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: pecan cake(diabetic)
directions: Cream butter until light.
Combine egg, Sugar Twin and vanilla; beat until well blended.
Blend into butter.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to butter mixture.
Mix until well blended.
Stir in applesauce.
Beat with electric mixer for several minutes at high speed.
Blend in pecans and dates.
Turn into buttered loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 1 hour, or until cake tests done.
Yields 6 servings.

title: beefy jalapeno cornbread
directions: Combine 1 cup cornmeal, milk, egg, salt, bacon drippings and corn in large bowl; mix.
Saute beef and onion; drain.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon cornmeal in greased, preheated 12-inch iron skillet. Pour half of cornmeal mixture in skillet, then pour meat/onion mixture on top.
Grate Cheddar cheese on top of mixtures.
Pour remaining cornmeal mixture over top.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°. Crust will brown like cornbread.

title: broken glass gelatin salad
directions: Dissolve each gelatin flavor separately with 2 cups boiling water, then 2 cups cold water each.
Pour into 3 separate pans to make 1/2-inch layer.
Chill until firm; cut into small cubes (1/2-inch).
Mix pineapple juice and sugar; heat until sugar is dissolved and liquid is boiling.
Remove from heat.
Add 6 ounces strawberry gelatin; stir until dissolved.
Add cold water.
Chill until room temperature.
Add whipped topping.
Mix with strawberry gelatin syrup until you have creamy pink mixture.
Fold in cut gelatin cubes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill overnight. Serves 24.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
While oven is heating, place butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put in oven to melt.
Mix flour, milk and sugar in medium size bowl. Remove pan from oven and pour mixture over butter.
Distribute fruit and juices over mixture.
Put in oven for 30 to 35 minutes until brown.

title: pie pastry
directions: Stir together flour and salt. Cut in shortening until pieces are the size of peas.
Blend in water.

title: brief history of the sourdough pot(by barton cole)
directions: Pare and cut potato into large pieces; boil in mininum of water until well-cooked.
Mash into smooth puree; cool.
In a large bowl, beat the flour and sugar into the puree, adding water, if necessary, to make a smooth batter.
Add the yeast (if you choose), place in a 1/2 gallon jar, cover with plastic wrap and set in a warm place to ferment.
(Never cover Sourdough Pot tightly or results will resemble a bomb!)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken; debone and cut up.
In a skillet, slowly cook onions, pepper and celery in salad oil.
In a large heavy pot, place tomatoes, mushrooms and broth.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and bring to a boil.
Melt Velveeta cheese in liquid.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth from boiling chicken.
Combine with ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until heated through.

title: barbecued beans
directions: Mix all together in heavy saucepan.
Cook on medium heat until onions are done.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Melt butter in large bowl.
Stir in seasonings, then pretzels. Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Have cheese and oleo at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients with hands.
Roll and cut with cookie cutters or pinch off and flatten like biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Don't get too brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, cheese and bacon bits in large bowl. Mix together in small bowl the sugar, vinegar, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Pour this mixture into broccoli mixture and stir well to blend.
Refrigerate and serve chilled.

title: sweet potato streusel souffl
directions: Combine ingredients and mix well with electric mixer. Pour into a greased 2-quart rectangular casserole. (Sugar and butter can be reduced and it still tastes good.)

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Wrap each breast with bacon strip and brown in heavy skillet.
Remove chicken to casserole dish.
Pour diluted soup over; sprinkle with chives. Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour at 350°.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix all of the ingredients and bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: marinated italian salad
directions: Mix all together.
Let set 4 hours before serving.
Serve over greens (lettuce, endive, spinach).

title: chafing dish spinach and crab
directions: Saute the onions and garlic in butter. Cook spinach according to package directions; drain. Add all ingredients to the spinach and season to taste. Serve warm in a chafing dish with crackers.

title: broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan over medium-high heat, saute onion in margarine for 5 minutes, or until onion is almost tender.
Reduce heat to medium.
Stir in flour until completely blended.
Add water, bouillon, garlic powder and pepper.
Bring to boil; reduce heat to low.
Add broccoli and milk.
Simmer for 10 minutes, or until broccoli is done.
Stir in half and half and cheese until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix this altogether; divide in two rolls and roll over chili powder on waxed paper.
Serve on crackers after letting rolls chill a few hours.

title: grandma's potato salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Add potatoes, celery, onion and cooked eggs. Chill overnight.
Dressing alone can be stored in refrigerator for months in airtight jar.

title: candy strawberries
directions: Combine gelatin, pecans and coconut.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour.
Shape into strawberries. Roll in red decorator's sugar.
Tint almond slices with green food coloring.
Insert in tops of candy.

title: orange julius
directions: Blend 30 seconds in a blender.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken, onions and celery together.
Cut up all vegetables.
Cut chicken off bones and add vegetables.
Pour in pie pan.
Add flour, salt and pepper, if needed.
(Cook 45 minutes at 350°.)
Add broth and put top on, then cook.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Add dressing (mayo, sugar and vinegar) when ready to serve.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and oil on high speed for 4 minutes. Sift flour, baking powder, salt, soda and cinnamon together. Add sugar mixture and salt on medium speed until smooth. Stir in grated carrots and pineapple mixture only until incorporated. Turn batter into greased 13 x 9 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cake springs back when touched.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender.
Peel and slice.
Dice and pan-fry the bacon slowly until crisp.
Remove the bacon from the pan and drain on paper.
Pour off excess bacon fat, reserving three tablespoons in skillet. Add flour to fat, blending until smooth.
Add white vinegar, sugar, salt and water gradually to the flour and fat.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Boil for two minutes.
Remove from heat and allow to cool slightly.
Add a small amount of hot mixture to the beaten eggs, then a little more, gradually increasing the amount and finally blending egg and sauce mixture.
Pour dressing over the potatoes, adding chopped onions and crisp bacon.
This serves equally well hot or cold.

title: layered texas dip
directions: Layer in a small glass baking dish the bean dip and guacamole dip.
In a separate dish, mix the sour cream and mayonnaise; layer it on top of the other mixture.
Sprinkle the taco seasoning over and slice through.
Layer the onions, tomatoes, cheese and olives. It is best if you let it sit overnight before you serve.
It is great with corn chips.

title: herbed dumplings
directions: Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Add parsley, chives and butter, with pastry blender or 2 knives.
Cut in butter or margarine until mixture is the texture of small peas.
Stir as little as possible.
Drop by spoonfuls into chicken mixture; simmer 10 minutes longer.
Serve at once.

title: bacon  stuffed burgers
directions: Fry bacon crisp.
Saute onion in 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Drain and chop mushrooms.
Crumble bacon. Add with onion and mushrooms; set aside.
Combine beef, sausage, cheese, pepper, garlic powder and steak sauce.
Shape into thin patties. Put bacon mixture on half of patties, then put another patty on top and seal real good around edges.
Cook over medium heat until well done.
Serve on buns.

title: yeast dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk and pour into large mixing bowl with cover.
Add sugar and shortening.
Let cool until warm (about like milk for a baby).
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to milk mixture.
Add 4 cups flour and beat well.
(This will be thin.)
Let rise until double in bulk (about an hour).
Stir in baking powder, soda, salt and enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Cover and put in refrigerator until cold or next day.
Make in rolls and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° about 15 minutes, depending on oven. This dough will keep 2 or 3 days in refrigerator.

title: marshmallow fudge
directions: Combine Milnot and sugar in heavy saucepan (4-quart).
Add Marshmallow Creme and butter and cook over low heat until melted. (Heat may be turned to medium.)
Bring mixture to full boil and stir 4 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in chocolate chips until melted.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: Combine rice, raisins, salt and 3 cups milk in 3-quart saucepan.
Cook over medium heat for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add butter to hot mixture, mix well.
Combine sugar, eggs and remaining 1/3 cup milk; add to pudding, stirring constantly.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes, or until mixture thickens and coats a metal spoon.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Place maraschino cherries on paper towel to remove excess syrup; stir into pudding.
Spoon pudding into 8 individual dessert dishes. Serve warm or cold.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Mix all together.
Very good on crackers.

title: dirty rice
directions: Melt the margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour in the rice and onion; stir until the rice is coated with the margarine.
Add the bouillon and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sugar-free dream pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into graham cracker crust. Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: sweet and sour red cabbage(serves 4)
directions: Cook cabbage and onion in 1-inch boiling water in large saucepan for 6 minutes or until just tender.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender and mixture thickens slightly.
Stir occasionally.
Contains 151 calories per serving.

title: orange toast
directions: Mix well and spread on 6 slices buttered toast.
Put in oven or under the broiler for 2 or 3 minutes.

title: vegetable chicken bake with sweet bacon dressing
directions: Sprinkle chicken with pepper and dredge in flour.
Brown on both sides in hot in a heavy skillet; drain on paper towels and set aside.
Place potatoes and green beans in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour half of Sweet Bacon Dressing over vegetables.
Top with chicken breasts and pour remaining dressing over chicken.
Cover and bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients 15 minutes, until fluffy white. Spread over crust.
Put crushed pineapple on next, then slice bananas on top of pineapple.
Put Cool Whip on top of bananas. Top with nuts and cherries.
Let set 15 hours.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Note:
Just bring vinegar to full boil, remove from heat.

title: boiled raisin cake
directions: Boil water, raisins, sugar and butter 5 minutes.
Let stand until cool.
Add 1 heaping teaspoon soda, dissolved in 1 teaspoon of hot water.
Add 1 teaspoon all kinds of spices.
Use more cinnamon than other spices.
Add walnuts.
Combine dry ingredients with boiled mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, depending on depth of pan.
This will make 2 small loaf pans or 4 mini pans.
